{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Psalm 31 \uc1\u8211* A Prayer for Deliverance from Troubles

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\i For the leader. A psalm of David.}
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 31}In you, O {\scaps Lord}, I take refuge;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
let me never be put to shame.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Rescue me in your faithfulness;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}incline to me your ear.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Deliver me speedily.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Be to me a rock of defence,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
a fortified house, to save me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}For my rock and my fortress are you;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
lead me and guide me so your name will be honoured.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Draw me out of the net they have hid for me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
