{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Psalm 38 \uc1\u8211* A Confession and Prayer for Deliverance

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\i A Psalm of David. A lament.}
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 38}Reprove me not, {\scaps Lord}, in your anger,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and chasten me not in your wrath;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}for your arrows have sunk into me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and your hand lies heavy upon me.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}In my flesh is no soundness
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
because of your anger,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
no health in my bones,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
because of my sin.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For that my guilt
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
is gone over my head:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
it weighs like a burden
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
too heavy for me.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}My wounds stink and fester,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for my foolishness I am tormented.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Bent and bowed am I utterly,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
all the day going in mourning.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}My loins are filled with burning,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and in my flesh is no soundness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I am utterly crushed and numb;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I cry louder than lion roars.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\scaps {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Lord}, you know all that I long for,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
my groans are not hidden from you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}My heart is throbbing,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
my strength has failed me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The light of my eyes \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
even it is gone from me.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}My dear ones and friends keep aloof,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and my neighbours stand afar off.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}They who aim at my life lay their snares,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
they who seek my hurt speak of ruin,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nursing treachery all the day long.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But I turn a deaf ear and hear not;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
like the dumb I open not my mouth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}I am like one without hearing,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
with no arguments in my mouth.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}For my hope, O {\scaps Lord}, is in you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
You will answer, O {\scaps Lord} my God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}when I utter the hope that those
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who made scorn of my tottering feet
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
