{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Listen and testify against the house of Jacob,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the Lord {\scaps God}, the God of hosts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}On the day when I punish Israel for their crimes,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will also visit in judgment the altars of Bethel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the horns of the altar will be hacked off,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and they will fall to the ground.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I will destroy the winter houses
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
together with the summer houses
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the houses of ivory will perish.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Many great houses will be swept away,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}Listen to this message, women of Sameria,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you well-fed cows of Bashan,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who oppress the poor and crush the needy,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who say to your husbands, \uc1\u8216*Bring us another drink!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The Lord {\scaps God} has sworn by his holiness:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The time is coming when you will be carried away in baskets,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
your children carried away in fish-baskets,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and through the breaches in the city wall you will go,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
thrown out on the garbage dump,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Come to Bethel and transgress,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
at Gilgald increase your transgression.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Bring your sacrifices in the morning,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
every third day your tithes!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Burn some leavened bread as a thank-offering,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
proclaim aloud your voluntary offerings,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for you love to do this, Israelites!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the Lord {\scaps God}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But it was I who gave to you
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
empty stomachs in all your cities,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and lack of bread in all your towns,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
yet you have not returned to me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}It was I who withheld from you the rain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
sending rain on one city,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
while on another I allowed no rain.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
One field received rain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
while a field without rain withered.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}People from two or three cities
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
ranged as far as another city
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for drinking water,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and still they did not have enough,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
yet you did not return to me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}I struck you with blight and mildew,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I laid waste your gardens and vineyards.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The swarming locust devoured your fig and your olive trees,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
yet you did not return to me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}I sent plague among you like the plagues of Egypt,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I slew your youths with the sword, your horses raided away,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I caused the stench of your camps to rise in your nostrils,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
yet you did not return to me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}I wrought a destruction among you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
as God destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You were like a stick snatched from the fire,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
yet you did not return to me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Therefore this is what I will do to you, Israel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and because I am about to do this to you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
prepare to meet your God, Israel.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}He is here!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He who forms the mountains,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
creates the wind,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
declares to his thoughts to mortals,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
makes dawn and darkness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
treads upon the heights of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the {\scaps Lord}, the God of hosts, is his name!
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 A Funeral Song for Israel

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}Listen to the words of the funeral song
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I am singing for you, Israel:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Fallen, no more to rise, is the virgin Israel!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Hurled down upon her own soil she lies,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
with no one to lift her up!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}For the Lord {\scaps God} says this:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The city that marches out with a thousand soldiers
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
has only a hundred left,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the one that marches out with a hundred
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
has only ten left.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For the {\scaps Lord} says this to Israel:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Seek me and live,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}But do not seek Bethel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
do not enter Gilgal,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
do not go over to Beer-sheba.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For Gilgal will enter exile,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and Bethel will go to destruction.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Seek the {\scaps Lord} and live,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
or he will cast fire on the house of Joseph,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and it will devour
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and there will be no one to quench it for Bethel.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}You who turn judgment to bitter wormwood,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and cast righteousness into the dirt:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}He who made the Pleiades and Orion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who turns deep darkness into dawn,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who darkens day again into night,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who summons the waters of the sea,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and pours them out on the earth\uc1\u8217*s surface,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the {\scaps Lord} is his name!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}He causes destruction to burst over the strong.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He brings devastation on the fortress.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}You who hate the arbiters at the city gate,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and abhor anyone who speaks the truth:
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Because you trample on the weak,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and tax their grain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
although you have built houses of hewn stone,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you will not live in them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
although you have planted charming vineyards,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you will not drink their wine.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}For I know how many are your crimes,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and how great are your sins!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You persecutors of the righteous, takers of bribes!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You deny the poor their justice at the city gate.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}It would be wise to keep quiet in such an evil time.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Seek good and not evil,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
that you may live,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
so the {\scaps Lord}, God of hosts,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
may be with you, as you have claimed he is.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Hate evil and love good,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
establish justice at the city gate.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Perhaps the {\scaps Lord}, the God of hosts,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
will be gracious to a surviving remnant of Joseph.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Therefore the {\scaps Lord}, the God of hosts, says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
In all the public squares there will be wailing,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
in every street the sound of mourning.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They will summon the farmers to mourning,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and professional mourners to wailing.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}In all vineyards there will be lamenting,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
when I pass through your midst,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Fools who long for the day of the {\scaps Lord}!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
What does the day of the {\scaps Lord} mean to you?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
It is darkness, and not light.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}It is as when one flees from a lion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and is attacked by a bear,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
as when one reaches home, leans his hand on the wall,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and a snake bites him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Won\uc1\u8217*t the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s day be darkness and not light,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
murky darkness without a ray of light in it?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}I hate, I despise your feasts,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will not smell the savour of your festivals,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}I will not be pleased with your burnt offerings,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
your grain offerings,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will not accept the peace offerings
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
of your fattened calves.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Spare me the noise of your songs,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will not listen to the melody of your lyres.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}But let justice roll on as a flood of waters,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and righteousness like an unfailing stream.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Was it only sacrifices and grain offerings
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you brought me
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
during the forty years in the wilderness, Israel?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}But now you will lift up your "king" Sikkuth
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and "star god" Kiyyun,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
your idols which you have made for yourselves,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}as I drive you into exile beyond Damascus,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}, whose name is the God of hosts.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Destruction of Israel

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}Sorrow awaits who are carefree in Zion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
overconfident on the mountain of Samaria!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The elite of this, the best of nations,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
on whom the people of Israel rest their hopes!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}You say to the people:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Cross over to Calneh and see,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
go from there to Hamath the great,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
then go down to Gath of the Philistines:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Are they better than these kingdoms?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Is their territory larger than yours?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}You push away all thoughts of the evil day,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
yet have instituted a rule of violence.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}They lie on ivory couches,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
sprawl on their divans,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
eat choice lambs from the flock,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and fattened calves from the stall.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}They idly sing to the sound of the lyre,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
thinking themselves songwriters like David,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}they drink bowlfuls of wine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and anoint themselves with the finest of oil.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
But they do not grieve over the ruin of Joseph.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore now they must go into exile
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
at the head of the captives,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and hushed will be the revelry of the sprawlers.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The Lord {\scaps God},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the {\scaps Lord}, the God of hosts, has sworn by himself:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I abhor the pride of Jacob,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I hate his palaces,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
therefore I will deliver up the city
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and all that is in it to their enemies.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}If ten people remain in one house, then they will die.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}When the uncle and another member of the family of a dead man come to carry the body out of the house for burial, they will call to someone in a corner of the house, \uc1\u8220*Any more there?\uc1\u8221* and he will answer, \uc1\u8220*No\uc1\u8221*, and then he will add, \uc1\u8220*Be quiet!\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* for the name of the {\scaps Lord} must not be mentioned.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Look! The {\scaps Lord} is giving the command!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He will smash the large house to bits,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the small house into fragments.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Do horses gallop on crags?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Does one plough the sea with oxen?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Yet you turn justice into poison weed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the fruit of righteousness into bitter wormwood.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}You who are so proud
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
of capturing Lo-debar,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who say, \uc1\u8220*Have we not by our own strength
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
taken Karnaim for ourselves?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}I am now raising up against you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Israel, a nation,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}, the God of hosts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They will oppress you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
from the entrance of Hamath
\par}

