{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Not a famine of bread or thirst for water,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but for hearing the message of the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Then they will wander from sea to sea,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
from the north to the east,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
to seek a message from the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but they will not find it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}In that day beautiful girls and strong young men
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
will faint from thirst.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Those who take oaths by the shameful idol of Samaria,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who swear, \uc1\u8220*As surely as your God lives, O Dan!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and, \uc1\u8220*By the sacred way to Beer-sheba!\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they will fall and never rise again.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 9} I saw the Lord towering above the altar, and he commanded:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Strike the tops of the pillars
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
