plant vineyards and drink their wine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
make gardens and eat their fruit.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I will plant them on their own soil,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and they will never again be uprooted from their land
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
which I have given them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord} your God.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Obadiah (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Obadiah

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}The vision of Obadiah; what the {\scaps Lord} said about Edom:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
We have heard a report from the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a messenger has been sent among the nations;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Rise up, let us rise against Edom in battle!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I will make you small among the nations,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and despised by all!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Your proud heart has misled you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
you who live in the clefts of the rock,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
you who build on high your dwelling.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You say to yourselves,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Who can bring me down to earth?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Though you build high as the eagle,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
though between the stars you set your nest,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
from there will I bring you down,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}If thieves had come to you, marauders by night
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
would they not have stolen only as much as they needed?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
If grape-gatherers had come to you
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
would they not have left some gleanings?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Descendents of Esau,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
all your treasures are looted.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}To your border they have driven you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
all your allies have betrayed you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Your avowed friends have overpowered you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
they have set a trap for you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Where is your wisdom now?
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
On that day,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will destroy the wise of Edom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
drive wisdom out of Mount Esau.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Your warriors will be filled with terror, Teman,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
none will be left alive on Mount Esau.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Because of the violence done to your relatives, the people of Jacob,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
shame covers you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
you are cut off forever.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}In the day when you stood aloof,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in the day when strangers carried away their wealth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and strangers entered into their gates,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and over Jerusalem cast lots,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you were as one of those strangers.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}You should not have gloated over your relatives,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in the day of their misfortune.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You should not have exulted over the land of Judah
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in the day of their destruction.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You should not have laughed loudly
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
at their distress.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}You should not have entered in at the gate of my people
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in the day of their disaster.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You should not have gloated over their calamity,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in the day of their disaster,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
nor stretched out your hand after their wealth
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in the day of their disaster,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}nor stood at the crossroads
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
to cut down their fugitives,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
nor should you have betrayed their refugees
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in the day of distress.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Near at hand is the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s day for all the nations.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
As you have done so will it be done to you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Your deeds will come back on your own head.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}As you have drunk upon my holy mountain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so all the nations will drink in turn;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They will drink deep
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and be as though they had not been.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}But on Mount Zion some will escape,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
it will be again holy,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and those of the house of Jacob
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
will again enter into their possessions.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For the house of Jacob will be a fire,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the house of Joseph a flame,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but the house of Esau will become stubble.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
They will kindle and devour it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Not even one of the house of Esau will escape,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for the {\scaps Lord} has spoken.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}They will possess the Negeb and Mount Esau,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the Shephelah of the Philistines.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They will possess the territory of Ephraim and Samaria,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and Benjamin will possess Gilead.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}The exiles of Israel will possess the land of the Canaanites
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
as far as Zarephath.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The captives of Jerusalem who are in Sepharad
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
will possess the cities of the Negreb.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}The rescued will come up on Mount Zion to rule Mount Esau,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the kingdom will belong to the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Jonah (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Jonah

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Jonah runs away

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}This message from the {\scaps Lord} came to Jonah, the son of Amittai:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8216*Arise, go to that great city, Nineveh, and preach against it; for their wickedness is known to me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}But Jonah started to flee to Tarshish from the presence of the {\scaps Lord}. He went down to Joppa and found a ship going to Tarshish. So he paid the fare and went aboard to go with them to Tarshish from the presence of the {\scaps Lord}.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}But the {\scaps Lord} made a furious wind blow over the sea, and there was such a great storm that the ship was in danger of breaking to pieces.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The sailors were terrified and each cried for help to his own god. They threw the ship\uc1\u8217*s cargo into the sea to make the ship lighter. Meanwhile Jonah had gone down into the bottom of the ship and lay fast asleep.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}The captain of the ship went and said to him, \uc1\u8216*How can you sleep? Call on your god; perhaps that god will think of us, so that we may not be lost.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The sailors said to one another, \uc1\u8216*Come, let us cast lots to discover on whose account this evil has come upon us.\uc1\u8217* So they cast lots, and the lot indicated Jonah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}So they said to him, \uc1\u8216*Are you to blame for this? Tell us, what is your business, and where do you come from? What is your country and to what people do you belong?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}He replied, \uc1\u8216*I am a Hebrew, and a worshipper of the {\scaps Lord}, the God of heaven, who made the sea and the dry land.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Then the men were greatly frightened and said to him, \uc1\u8216*What have you done?\uc1\u8217* For they knew that he was fleeing from the presence of the {\scaps Lord}, because he had told them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Then they said to him, \uc1\u8216*What should we do to you, to make the sea calm for us?\uc1\u8217* For the sea grew more and more stormy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}He said to them, \uc1\u8216*Take me up and throw me into the sea, and the sea will be calm for you, for I know that it is because of me this fierce storm has overtaken you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But instead the men rowed hard to get back to the land; they could not, however, for the sea grew more and more stormy ahead.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}So they cried to the {\scaps Lord} and said, \uc1\u8216*We beg you, {\scaps Lord}, we beg you, don\uc1\u8217*t let us die for this man\uc1\u8217*s life, and don\uc1\u8217*t let us be guilty of shedding innocent blood, for you are the {\scaps Lord}; you have done as it pleases you.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And they took up Jonah, and threw him into the sea; and the sea became calm.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Then the men greatly feared the {\scaps Lord}, and they offered a sacrifice and made vows to him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}But the {\scaps Lord} arranged for a great fish to swallow Jonah, and Jonah was inside the fish three days and three nights.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Jonah\uc1\u8217*s song

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}Jonah prayed to the {\scaps Lord} his God, out of the belly of the fish,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I cried out of my distress, to the {\scaps Lord}
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and he answered me;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
out of the midst of Sheol I cried aloud,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and you heard my voice.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}For you cast me into the deep,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
into heart of the seas,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the great flood rolled about me;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
all your breakers and your waves
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
passed over me.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Then I said, I am driven out,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
away from your sight;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
How will I ever again
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
look towards your holy temple?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The waters surrounded me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the great deep engulfed me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the sea weeds were wrapped about my head.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}I went down to the roots of the mountains;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the prison of the earth closed over me forever.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Yet you brought up my life from destruction,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
O {\scaps Lord} my God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}As my life slipped away,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I remembered the {\scaps Lord};
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and my prayer reached you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in your holy temple.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Those who worship worthless idols
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
abandon their own mercy,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}but I will sacrifice to you
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
with loud thanksgiving!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will pay that which I have vowed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Salvation is the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And the {\scaps Lord} spoke to the fish, and it threw up Jonah upon the dry land.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The message to Nineveh

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}This message from the {\scaps Lord} came to Jonah the second time,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8216*Arise, go to that great city, Nineveh, and proclaim to it the message that I tell you.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So Jonah started for Nineveh, as the {\scaps Lord} commanded. Now Nineveh was so large a city that it took three days\uc1\u8217* journey to cross it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Jonah began by going a day\uc1\u8217*s journey into the city, and he proclaimed, \uc1\u8216*Forty days more and Nineveh shall be overthrown.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And the people of Nineveh believed God; and they ordered a fast and put on sackcloth, from the greatest to the least of them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And when word came to the king of Nineveh, he rose from his throne, took off his robe, dressed in sackcloth, and sat in ashes.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And he made this proclamation and published it in Nineveh: \uc1\u8216*By the decree of the king and his nobles: People, beast, herd, and flock shall not taste anything; let them not eat nor drink water.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Let both people and animals put on sackcloth and let them cry earnestly to God; let them each turn from their evil ways and from the deeds of violence which they are doing.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Who knows? God may relent and avert his fierce anger, so that we may not die.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}When God saw that they turned from their evil course, he relented the evil which he said he would do to them, and did not do it.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Jonah sulks

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}But this seemed very wrong to Jonah and he became angry.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}He prayed to the {\scaps Lord} and said, \uc1\u8216*Ah, {\scaps Lord}, wasn\uc1\u8217*t this what I said when I was still in my own country? That was why I fled at once to Tarshish; for I knew that you are a gracious and merciful God, patient, and loving and ready to forgive.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Therefore, {\scaps Lord}, I beg you, take my life from me; for it is better for me to die than to live!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}But the {\scaps Lord} said, \uc1\u8216*Are you doing right in being angry?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Then Jonah went out of the city and sat down on the east side, and there made a hut for himself and sat under it, waiting to see what would become of the city.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And the {\scaps Lord} arranged for a bush to grow up over Jonah as a shade for his head to make him comfortable. The bush gave Jonah great pleasure;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}but at dawn the next day God arranged for a worm which attacked the bush, so that it wilted.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And when the sun rose, God arranged a hot east wind. And the sun beat upon Jonah\uc1\u8217*s head, so that he was faint and begged that he might die, saying, \uc1\u8216*It is better for me to die than to live.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But God said to Jonah, \uc1\u8216*Are you doing right in being angry about the bush?\uc1\u8217* He replied, \uc1\u8216*I have every right to be as angry as I could possibly be!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Jonah is rebuked

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}The {\scaps Lord} said, \uc1\u8216*You care about a bush which has cost you no trouble and which you have not made grow, which came up in a night and wilted in a night.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Should I not care for the great city Nineveh, in which there are one hundred and twenty thousand people who do not know their right hand from their left; and many cattle too?\uc1\u8217*
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Micah (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Micah

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Superscription to Micah\uc1\u8217*s Sermons

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}The {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s message which came to Micah of Morsheth in the reigns of Jotham, Ahaz and Hezekiah, kings of Judah. The visions he saw about Samaria and Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Lord\uc1\u8217*s Judgment on Guilty Samaria and Judah

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Listen, all you peoples!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Pay attention, all you inhabitants of the earth!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For the Lord {\scaps God} will be a witness against you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the Lord from his holy temple!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}The {\scaps Lord} is coming from his holy place,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
he descends and treads on the heights of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}so that the mountains melt beneath
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like wax in the presence of the fire,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the valleys break apart
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like water poured down a steep descent.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}All this is because of the crime of Jacob,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and for the sin of the house of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
What was the crime of Jacob?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Was it not Samaria?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
What is the sin of Judah?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Is it not Jerusalem?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8216*I will make Samaria a ruin in an open field,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and a place where a vineyard is planted,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will hurl down her stones into the valley,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and lay bare her foundations.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}\uc1\u8216*All her images will be shattered,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and all her statues will be burned with fire,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and all her idols I will lay in ruins.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For they were acquired by prostitution,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and to prostitution they will return.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}This is why I will mourn and wail,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will go barefoot and naked,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will howl like the jackals
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and mourn like the desert owl.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For the blow that Samaria has received is incurable.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
It has spread over Judah,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
it extends even to the gate of my people,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
even to Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Don\uc1\u8217*t tell this in Gath!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Don\uc1\u8217*t even cry \uc1\u8211* but sit in the dust at Beth-leaphrah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Pass by, inhabitants of Shaphir, naked and ashamed!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The inhabitants of Zaanan cannot leave their city.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Beth-ezel laments and removes its support from you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The inhabitants of Maroth wait anxiously for good!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
But the {\scaps Lord} has sent disaster to the gates of Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Harness the horse to the chariot, inhabitants of Lachish.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You led the daughter of Zion, Jerusalem, into sin,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
in you are found the crimes of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Therefore you must give parting gifts to Moresheth-gath.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Beth-achzib will betray the kings of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I will hand you to a conqueror, people of Mareshah,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the leaders of Israel will hide in Adullam Cave!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Shave your head in morning for the children you love,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
until you are bald as vultures, because they have left you for exile.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Oppression of the Poor

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}Woe to those who lie awake planning evil,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who in the light of morning carry out their plan
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because they have the power to do it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}They covet fields and seize them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
desire houses and take them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they crush householder and his household,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
people and their possessions.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Therefore the {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*I am planning disaster from which you cannot save your neck,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
nor walk proudly because it will be a terrible time.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}On that day they will sing a taunt-song to you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
this mocking lament:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*My people\uc1\u8217*s estate is being measured for sale,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
our captors are dividing our fields.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
We are completely undone.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}There will be no one to measure out land for you
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
from the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s community.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8216*\uc1\u8220*Don\uc1\u8217*t rant!\uc1\u8221* they urge, \uc1\u8220*Of such things one does not prophesy!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Shame will not overtake us!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Is the {\scaps Lord} impatient, or are such things his deeds?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Are not his words favourable to the family of Jacob?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Aren\uc1\u8217*t my commands good for those who obey them?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}But you, you stand up as a foe against those who are peaceful;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you strip the robe from those who pass by quietly, averse to conflict.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Women of my people you drive out from their happy homes,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
from their young children you take away my glory forever.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Rise and begone, for this is no place to rest.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Your uncleanness brings destruction, severe destruction.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}If a person walking in wine and falsehood were to say,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will prophesy to you of wine and strong drink,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
then he would be the perfect prophet for this people!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Lord Leading Back His Scattered People

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8216*I will assuredly assemble all of Jacob,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will surely gather the survivors of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will herd them together as sheep in a fold,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like a flock in the pasture,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the land will resound with the sounds of multitudes.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8216*The one who breaks out goes first.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They have broken forth and passed by the gate
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and through it have they gone out.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Their king leads before them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the {\scaps Lord} at their head.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Crimes of Judah\uc1\u8217*s Civil and Spiritual Leaders

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}I also said:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*Listen now, leaders of Jacob,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
judges of the house of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Is it not your duty to know what is the right?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Haters of that which is good and lovers of evil!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8216*They devour the flesh of my people,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and their hide they strip from off them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and break in pieces and serve up their bones,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like meat in a pot or the cooking pan!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8216*Then they will cry out to the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but he will not pay attention to them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He will hide his face from them at that time
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because they have committed such crimes.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Therefore the {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*To the prophets who lead my people astray,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who when they have food between their teeth declare peace,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but against one who puts nothing in their mouths,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they proclaim an open war!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8216*Night will overtake you so that you have no vision,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and darkness so that there will be no divination,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the sun will go down on the prophets,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the day shall be dark over them.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}\uc1\u8216*The seers will be ashamed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the diviners will turn pale,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
all of them will cover their mouths.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For there will be no answer from God.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8216*But I, on the contrary am full of power,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the sense of justice and strength,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
to make known to Jacob his crime,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and to Israel his sin.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}\uc1\u8216*Hear this, leaders of the house of Jacob,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
judges of the house of Israel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you who spurn justice,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and make all that is straight crooked,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}who build Zion with acts of bloodshed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and Jerusalem with crime.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8216*The leaders render judgment for a bribe,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and her priests give oracles for a reward,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and her prophets divine for silver.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Yet they claim to rely on the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*The {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8221*, they say, \uc1\u8220*is in our midst.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Evil cannot overtake us.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8216*Therefore for your sakes
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Zion will be plowed as a field,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and Jerusalem will become a heap of ruins,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the temple mount a wooded height.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Peace and Worldwide Renown of Zion

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}In the days to come
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the mountain of the {\scaps Lord} will be established,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the house of our God on the top of the mountain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
lifted above the hills.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
All the nations will flow to it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and many peoples will go and say,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*Come, let us go up to the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s mount,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
to the house of the God of Jacob,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
so that he may instruct us in his ways,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
so that we may walk in his paths.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For from Zion proceeds instruction
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s word from Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}He will arbitrate between many peoples,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and render decisions for numerous nations,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They will beat their swords into ploughshares,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and their spears into pruning hooks.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Nation will not lift up sword against nation,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they will learn war no more.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}They will live each under his vine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and under his fig tree, with none to terrify them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For the mouth of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts has spoken.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Each nation trusts in the names of their gods,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but we will worship the {\scaps Lord} our God forever.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8216*On that day,\uc1\u8217* says the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*I will assemble the lame.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will gather exiles I punished.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}I will restore the lame as a remnant,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the exiles into a great nation.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The {\scaps Lord} will rule over them
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
on Mount Zion from that time forever.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}But you, watchtower for the flock,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
hill of the daughter of Zion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
to you will return your former rule.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}So why do you now cry aloud? Haven\uc1\u8217*t you any king?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Or has your counsellor perished, so you writhe in pain like a woman in labour?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Writhe and scream, daughter of Zion, like a woman in labour!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For now you must leave the city and camp in the open field.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You will be taken to Babylon, but there will be rescued.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
There the {\scaps Lord} will save you from the hands of your foes.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But now many nations gather against you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They say, \uc1\u8216*Let her be defiled, we will gloat over Zion.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}But they do not know the thoughts of the {\scaps Lord}.
