\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Zion\uc1\u8217*s Ultimate Vindication and Exaltation

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}But I will look to the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will wait for the God of my salvation.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
My God will hear me!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Do not rejoice over me, my enemy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
If I have fallen, I will rise.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
If I sit in darkness, the {\scaps Lord} is my light.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The anger of the {\scaps Lord} I will bear,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for against him have I sinned \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
until he champions my cause
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and gives judgment for me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He will bring me into to the light,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will see his justice.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}So my enemy will see, and shame will cover them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they who said, \uc1\u8216*Where is the {\scaps Lord} your God?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will look upon them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they will be trampled on like mud in the street!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}It is a day for rebuilding your walls,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
this day will your boundary will be extended.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}This day they will come to you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
from Assyria and the cities of Egypt,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and from Egypt even to the Euphrates River,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
from sea to sea, and from mountain to mountain.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Though the land has become a desolation
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because of its inhabitants, because of their deeds.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Shepherd your flock with your staff, the flock that belong to you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who live alone in the forest, in the midst of meadows;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
so that they may pasture in Bashon and Gilead as in the days of old,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}as in the days when you came from Egypt, gave us wonders to see.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Nations will see and be ashamed of all their might;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they will put their hands to their mouth, their ears will become deaf,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}they will lick the dust like snakes, like creatures that crawl on the earth;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they will come trembling and in terror from their hiding places, in dread and fear.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Who is a God like you, forgiving iniquity
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and passing by the rebellion of the remnant of your people?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
