{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}The {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s message, which came to Zephaniah, son of Cushi, son of Gedaliah, son of Amariah, son of Hezekiah, in the time of Josiah of Judah who was son of Amon.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Day of Judgment on Judah

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I will utterly destroy everything
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
from off the face of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}I will sweep away human and animal,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the birds of the sky
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the fish of the sea.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will cause the wicked to stumble,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I will cut off humanity from the face of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}I will stretch out my hand over Judah
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and I will cut off from this place the last remnant of Baal
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the name of the heathen priests,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}and those who worship on the housetops
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
to the stars in the sky,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and those worshippers of the {\scaps Lord}
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who also pay homage to Milcom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and those who turn back
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
from following the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
And those who do not seek the {\scaps Lord}
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
nor strive to find him.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Be silent before the Lord {\scaps God},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for near is the day of the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for the {\scaps Lord} has prepared a sacrifice,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he has sanctified his guests.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}On the day of the {\scaps Lord\uc1\u8217*s} sacrifice:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will punish the officers and the royal princes,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and all those who clothe themselves in foreign apparel.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}On that day:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will punish all who leap over the threshold,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who fill the house of their lord with violence and deceit.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Listen on that day, says the {\scaps Lord}:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
A cry will be heard from the Fish Gate,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and a wailing from the New Quarter,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and a great din from the hills.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Those who live in the Mortar wail,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for all the traders are silenced,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the money counters wiped out.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I will search Jerusalem with a lamp,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I will punish those who are at ease,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who sit comfortably with their wine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who say to themselves,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*the {\scaps Lord} brings neither prosperity nor calamity.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Their wealth will become a prey
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and their houses a desolation.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Though they build houses,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
they will not inhabit them;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
though they plant vineyards,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
they will not drink wine from them.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Near is the day of the {\scaps Lord}!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Near and rapidly approaching!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Near is the bitter day of the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the scream of the warrior.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}That day is a day of wrath,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a day of trouble and distress,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
a day of destruction and desolation,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a day of darkness and gloom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
a day of clouds and thick darkness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}a day of the trumpet and battle-cry,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
against the fortified cities
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and against the high battlements.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And I will bring distress upon the people
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and they will walk as the blind,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
because they have sinned against the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and their blood will be poured out as dust
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and their flesh as dung.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Neither their silver nor their gold will be able to save them. For in the day of the wrath of the {\scaps Lord} and in the fire of his fury the whole earth will be consumed. For he will make a speedy end of all the inhabitants of the earth.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Imminent Judgment upon the Nations

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}Be ashamed within yourselves, be ashamed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}before you become as the drifting chaff,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
before the anger of the {\scaps Lord} comes upon you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
before the day of the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s wrath comes upon you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Seek the {\scaps Lord} all you meek of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
you who obey his law;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Seek righteousness, seek meekness;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
perhaps you may be hidden in the day of the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s wrath.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For Gaza will be forsaken;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Ashkelon a desolation;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Ashdod \uc1\u8211* by noon will they rout her
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and Ekron be torn up!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Woe to those who live by the sea coast,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
people of the Cherethites!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The word of the {\scaps Lord} is against you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Canaan, land of the Philistines!
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
I will destroy you so that you will be without inhabitants,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and you will become shepherds\uc1\u8217* cots and folds for flocks.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The sea coast will belong to the survivors of the house of Judah.They will pasture their flocks there. In the house of Ashkelon they will lie down at evening. The {\scaps Lord} their God will be with them and restore their fortunes.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I have heard the taunts of Moab,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the revilings of the Ammonites,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
how they have taunted my people,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and spoken boastfully concerning their border.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Therefore as I live, says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, the God of Israel:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Moab will be like Sodom,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
and the Ammonites like Gomorrah,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a pile of nettles and saltpits,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
and a desolation, forever.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The residue of my people will plunder them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
and the survivors of my nation will inherit them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}This will they have for their pride,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
because they have taunted and spoken boastfully
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
against the people of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The {\scaps Lord} will terrify them;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he will reduce all the gods of the earth;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
then all the peoples of the nations will worship him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
each in their own land.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}You, also, Ethiopians,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
slain by his sword are you!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And he will stretch out his hand
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
against the north and destroy Assyria;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
And he will make Nineveh a desolation,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
dry as the wilderness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Herds will lie down in it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
every beast of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Desert owl and screech owl
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
will lodge in its capitals.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The owl will hoot in the window,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the raven on the doorstep,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
all stripped bare of cedar.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}This is the exultant city which sat secure. The city who said to herself, I am and there is none else! How has she become a desolation! A lair of beasts! Every passerby hisses at her, shakes their hand.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Jerusalem\uc1\u8217*s Deep-seated Corruption

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}Woe to the rebellious and unclean city of oppression,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}She has not obeyed the voice,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
she has not accepted instruction,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
In the {\scaps Lord} she has not trusted,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
to her God she has not drawn near.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Her rulers in her midst are roaring lions.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Her judges are evening wolves,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who leave nothing over until the morning,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Her prophets are braggarts, faithless men.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Her priests profane what is holy
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and do violence to the law.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The {\scaps Lord} is righteous in her midst,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he does no wrong,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Morning by morning
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he establishes his decree,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Light is not lacking,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
an oversight is unknown.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
But the unjust know no shame.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8216*I have cut off nations,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
their turrets are destroyed;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I have laid waste their broad streets,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
so that none passes over them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Desolate are their cities without people,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
without inhabitants.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}I said:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*Surely the city will fear me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
she will accept instruction.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Nothing will vanish from her eyes
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
that I have impressed upon her;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
But the more zealously have they made all their deeds corrupt.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Future Vindication and Exultation of Jerusalem

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Wait for me, is the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s message, until the day when I stand up as a witness, for it is my fixed purpose to gather the nations, to collect the kingdoms, to pour upon them my wrath and my hot anger; for by the fire of my fury will all the earth be consumed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For then I will purify the lips of all peoples, so that they will all call on the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s name, to serve him with one accord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}From beyond the rivers of Cush my worshipers will bring me offerings.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}On that day you will no longer be ashamed of all your deeds by which you rebelled against me. For I will rid you of your proudly arrogant ones, and you will never again be haughty on my holy mountain.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}But I will leave in your midst a people humble and poor, and the remnant of Israel will trust in the name of the {\scaps Lord}.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}They will not do evil, nor speak falsehood, and a deceitful tongue will not be found in their mouth; but they will pasture and lie down, and no one will make them afraid.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Cry out with joy, daughter of Zion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
shout aloud, Israel!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Rejoice and exult with all your heart,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
daughter of Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}The {\scaps Lord} has put away your adversaries,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he has turned away your foes;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the {\scaps Lord} is king in your midst,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
you will fear evil no more.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}In that day it will be said to Jerusalem:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Fear not!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Zion, let not your hands grow weak!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}The {\scaps Lord} your God is in your midst,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
a victorious hero.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He will rejoice over you with joy,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he will renew his love,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
he will exult over you with singing,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}as on a day of festival.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will take away from you your disgrace,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and put away from you your reproach.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}I will destroy at that time
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
all who afflict you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will deliver the lame,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and gather the outcast,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will make them an object of renown
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and fame in all the earth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}I will do good to you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
at the time when I gather you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For I will make you an object of fame and renown
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
among all the peoples of the earth;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
when I bring back your captivity before your eyes.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
This says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Haggai (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Haggai

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The call to rebuild the Temple

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}In the second year of Darius the king, on the first day of the sixth month, this message from the {\scaps Lord} came through Haggai the prophet to Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and to Joshua the son of Jehozadak, the high priest:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The people say that the time has not yet come to rebuild the temple of the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then this message from the {\scaps Lord} came to Haggai the prophet:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Is it a time for you yourselves to live in your own well-roofed houses,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
while this temple lies in ruins?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Consider your past experiences.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}You sow much,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but bring in little;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you eat,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but you do not have enough;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you drink,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but are not filled;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you clothe yourselves,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but not enough to be warm;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and those who earn wages,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
put those wages in a bag with holes.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Consider your experiences.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Go up to the mountains,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and bring wood
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and rebuild the temple;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
then I will be pleased with it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I will reveal my glory.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}You looked for much,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and it came to little;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and when you brought the harvest home,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I blew it away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Why?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Because my temple lies in ruins,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
while you shelter in your own houses.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}The heavens withhold the dew,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the earth withholds its fruit,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}and I have called forth a drought upon the land
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and upon the mountains,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and upon the grain and the new wine and the oil
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and upon that which the ground brings forth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and upon people and animals,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and upon all the labor of your hands.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Then Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel and Joshua the son of Jehozadak the high priest, with all the rest of the people, obeyed the command of the {\scaps Lord} their God and the words of Haggai the prophet, as the {\scaps Lord} their God had sent him to them. They showed proper respect for the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Haggai, the prophet of the {\scaps Lord}, as the {\scaps Lord} commanded him, told the people: \uc1\u8216*The {\scaps Lord} says: I am with you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And the {\scaps Lord} stirred up the spirit of Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and the spirit of Joshua the son of Jehozadak the high priest, and the spirit of all the rest of the people, so that they came and worked on the temple of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, their God,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}in the twenty-fourth day of the sixth month.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The future glory of the new Temple

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
In the second year of Darius the king,{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}on the twenty-first day of the seventh month, this message from the {\scaps Lord} came to Haggai the prophet,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}telling him to speak to Zerubbabel son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and to Joshua, the son of Jehozadak, the high priest, and to all the rest of the people:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Who is left among you that saw this temple in its former glory?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
And how do you see it now?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Doesn\uc1\u8217*t it seem as though there is nothing there?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Yet now be strong, Zerubbabel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
be strong, Joshua, son of Jehozadak, the high priest,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
be strong, all you people of the land.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The {\scaps Lord} says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Begin the work, for I am with you.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}When your ancestors left Egypt I made a promise to you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I am still with you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Do not be afraid!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
In a little while, I will shake the heavens,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the earth, and the sea, and the land.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And I will shake all nations,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the precious things of all nations shall come here;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I will fill this temple with glory.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The silver is mine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the gold is mine,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The later glory of this temple
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
shall be greater than the former.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
In this place I will grant prosperity.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
This is the message of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Former displeasure and the new promise of blessings

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}In the twenty-fourth day of the ninth month, in the second year of Darius, this message from the {\scaps Lord} came to Haggai the prophet:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says: \uc1\u8216*Ask the priests for a ruling:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8220*If one carries consecrated meat in the fold of his garment, and with that garment touches bread, or stew, or wine, or oil, or any food, will it become holy?\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
And the priests answered: \uc1\u8216*No.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then said Haggai, \uc1\u8216*If one who is unclean by reason of a dead body touches any of these, will it be unclean?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
And the priests answered: \uc1\u8216*It would be unclean.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Haggai replied: \uc1\u8216*So is this people and so is this nation before me, the {\scaps Lord} declares, and so is every work of their hands; and that which they offer there is unclean.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Think back from this day, before a stone was laid upon a stone in the temple of the {\scaps Lord}.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}How were you? When you came to a heap of grain expecting twenty measures, there were only ten; when you came to the wine vat to draw out fifty vessels, there were only twenty.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8220*I struck all the work of your hands with blasting and blight, with mildew and with hail. Yet you didn\uc1\u8217*t turn to me,\uc1\u8221* says the {\scaps Lord},{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8220*Think back from this day, think! From the twenty-fourth day of the ninth month, from the day when the foundations of the temple of the {\scaps Lord} were laid, and consider.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}The seed is in the granary, but the vine and the fig tree and the pomegranate and the olive tree have not yet brought forth fruit. From this day will I bless you.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Zerubbabel

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}This message from the {\scaps Lord} came to Haggai a second time on the twenty-fourth day of the month:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Tell Zerubbabel, governor of Judah:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will shake the heavens and the earth;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}and I will overthrow the throne of kingdoms;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I will destroy the strength of the kingdoms of the nations;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I will overthrow the chariots,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and those who ride in them;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the horses and their riders shall come down,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
each by the sword of his fellow.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}In that day,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the {\scaps Lord} of hosts says,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will take you, Zerubbabel, my servant, the son of Shealtiel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the {\scaps Lord} says,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and will make you like a signet ring, for I have chosen you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the {\scaps Lord} of hosts says.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Zechariah (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Zechariah

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Lesson from the Past

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}In the eighth month in the second year of Darius, this message of the {\scaps Lord} came to the prophet Zechariah, the son of Berechiah, the son of Iddo:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The {\scaps Lord} was furious with your ancestors.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So tell the people this message of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts: \uc1\u8216*Return to me,\uc1\u8217* says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, \uc1\u8216*and I will return to you\uc1\u8217* says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8216*Do not be like your ancestors to whom the former prophets cried, \uc1\u8220*The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says to turn now from your evil ways, and from your evil deeds\uc1\u8221*. They did not heed nor listen to me,\uc1\u8217* says the {\scaps Lord}.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*Your ancestors, where are they? And the prophets, do they live forever?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But did not my words and my statutes with which I charged my servants the prophets overtake your ancestors? And they repented and said, \uc1\u8220*Just as the {\scaps Lord} of hosts planned to do to us, according to our ways, and according to our deeds, so he has dealt with us.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Lord\uc1\u8217*s Jealous Love for Zion

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}In the twenty-fourth day of the eleventh month, which is the month Shebat, in the second year of Darius, this message of the {\scaps Lord} came to the prophet Zechariah, the son of Berechiah, the son of Iddo:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I saw in the night a man on a red horse, among the myrtle trees that were in the valley-bottom. Behind him there were horses, red, sorrel, and white.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then said I, \uc1\u8216*My Lord, what are these?\uc1\u8217* And the messenger who was talking with me said, \uc1\u8216*I will show you what they are.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And the man who was standing among the myrtle trees answered, \uc1\u8216*They are those whom the {\scaps Lord} has sent to patrol the earth.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And the riders answered the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} who was standing among the myrtle trees, \uc1\u8216*We have gone up and down through the world and behold, all the earth is still and at peace.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Then the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} said, \uc1\u8216*{\scaps Lord} of hosts, how long will you have no pity for Jerusalem and the cities of Judah with which you have been angry for seventy years?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And the {\scaps Lord} answered the messenger who was talking with me with kind and comforting words.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}So the messenger who was talking with me said to me, \uc1\u8216*Proclaim now that the {\scaps Lord} of hosts says: I am deeply concerned for Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But I am deeply angry with the arrogant, complacent nations. I was only a little angry with Israel but they made the suffering worse.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Therefore, says the {\scaps Lord}, I am turning to show mercy to Jerusalem. My temple will be rebuilt in it, says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, and a measuring line will be stretched over Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Proclaim again: Thus says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts: My cities will again overflow with prosperity and the {\scaps Lord} will again comfort Zion and choose Jerusalem.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Destruction of the Heathen Powers

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Now I looked up and saw four horns.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}I said to the messenger who was talking with me, \uc1\u8216*What are these?\uc1\u8217* He answered, \uc1\u8216*These are the horns which scattered Judah, Israel and Jerusalem.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then the {\scaps Lord} showed me four smiths.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}I said, \uc1\u8216*What are these coming to do?\uc1\u8217* He answered, \uc1\u8216*The horns scattered Judah, so that no one dared lift their head. But the smiths have come to terrify them, to crush the horns of the nations which lifted up their horn against the land of Judah to scatter its people.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Promise that Jerusalem Will be Gloriously Restored

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}Then I looked up and saw a man with a measuring line in his hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I said, \uc1\u8216*Where are you going?\uc1\u8217* He replied, \uc1\u8216*To measure Jerusalem, to see what is its breadth and length.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then the messenger who talked with me stepped forward, and another messenger went out to meet him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and said to him, \uc1\u8216*Run and tell to that young man that Jerusalem will be inhabited like a village without walls, because so many people and cattle will live there.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}For I, says the {\scaps Lord}, will be a wall of fire  her, and I will be the glory in the midst of her.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Up! Away! Flee from the land of the north, says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For I have spread you abroad as the four winds of the heavens, says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Up, escape to Zion, you who live in Babylon.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}This is what the {\scaps Lord} of hosts says to the nations which plundered you:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Whoever touches you touches the apple of my eye.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}I will raise my hand against them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They will be plunder for their own slaves; and you will know that the {\scaps Lord} of hosts has sent me.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8216*Sing and rejoice, daughter of Zion! I am coming,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will live among you, says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Many nations will join themselves to the {\scaps Lord} in that day,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and will be his people, and he will live among you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You will know that the {\scaps Lord} of hosts has sent me to you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The {\scaps Lord} will inherit Judah as his portion in the holy land.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He will again choose Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Be silent, everyone, in the presence of the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because he is coming from his holy dwelling.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Purification of the Priesthood and Nation

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
