{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}A genealogy of Jesus Christ, a descendant of David and Abraham.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Abraham was the father of Isaac, Isaac of Jacob, Jacob of Judah and his brothers,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Judah of Perez and Zerah, whose mother was Tamar, Perez of Hezron, Hezron of Aram,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Aram of Aminadab, Aminadab of Nahshon, Nahshon of Salmon,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Salmon of Boaz, whose mother was Rahab, Boaz of Obed, whose mother was Ruth, Obed of Jesse,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Jesse of David the King. David was the father of Solomon, whose mother was Uriah\uc1\u8217*s widow,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Solomon of Rehoboam, Rehoboam of Abijah, Abijah of Asa,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Asa of Jehoshaphat, Jehoshaphat of Joram, Joram of Uzziah,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Uzziah of Jotham, Jotham of Ahaz, Ahaz of Hezekiah,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Hezekiah of Manasseh, Manasseh of Amon, Amon of Josiah,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Josiah of Jechoniah and his brothers, at the time of the Exile to Babylon.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}After the Exile to Babylon \uc1\u8211* Jechoniah was the father of Salathiel, Salathiel of Zerubbabel,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Zerubbabel of Abiud, Abiud of Eliakim, Eliakim of Azor,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Azor of Zadok, Zadok of Achim, Achim of Eliud,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Eliud of Eleazar, Eleazar of Matthan, Matthan of Jacob,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Jacob of Joseph, the husband of Mary, who was the mother of Jesus, who is called \uc1\u8220*Christ\uc1\u8221*.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}So the whole number of generations from Abraham to David is fourteen; from David to the Exile to Babylon fourteen; and from the Exile to Babylon to the Christ fourteen.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}This is how Jesus Christ was born:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
His mother Mary was engaged to Joseph, but, before the marriage took place, she found herself to be pregnant by the power of the Holy Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Her husband, Joseph, was a just man and, since he did not want to disgrace her publicly, he resolved to put an end to their engagement privately.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}He had been thinking this over, when an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*Joseph, son of David,\uc1\u8217* the angel said, \uc1\u8216*do not be afraid to take Mary for your wife, for her child has been conceived by the power of the Holy Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}She will give birth to a son; name him Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}All this happened in fulfilment of these words of the Lord through the prophet, where he says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8220*The virgin will conceive and will give birth to a son, and they will give him the name Immanuel\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
\uc1\u8211* a word which means \uc1\u8220*God is with us.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}When Joseph woke up, he did as the angel of the Lord had directed him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}He made Mary his wife, but they did not sleep together before the birth of her son; and to this son he gave the name Jesus.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}After the birth of Jesus at Bethlehem in Judea, in the reign of King Herod, some astrologers from the East arrived in Jerusalem, asking,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8216*Where is the newborn king of the Jews? For we saw his star in the east, and have come to worship him.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}When King Herod heard of this, he was much troubled, and so too was all Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}He called together all the chief priests and teachers of the Law in the nation, and questioned them as to where the Christ was to be born.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*At Bethlehem in Judea,\uc1\u8217* was their answer, \uc1\u8216*for it is said in the prophet \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8220*And you, Bethlehem in Judah\uc1\u8217*s land,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
are in no way least among the chief cities of Judah,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for out of you will come a ruler \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who will shepherd my people Israel.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Then Herod secretly sent for the astrologers. He found out from them the time of the appearance of the star.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Sending them to Bethlehem he said, \uc1\u8216*Go and make a careful search for the child. When you have found him, bring word back to me, so that I, too, can go and worship him.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The astrologers heard what the king had to say, and then continued their journey. The star which they had seen in the east led them on, until it reached and stood over the place where the child was.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}At the sight of the star they were filled with joy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Entering the house, they saw the child with his mother, Mary, and fell at his feet and worshipped him. Then they opened their treasure chests, and offered to the child presents of gold, frankincense, and myrrh.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}But afterwards, having been warned in a dream not to go back to Herod, they returned to their own country by another road.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
