{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}As Jesus was walking along the shore of the Sea of Galilee, he saw two brothers \uc1\u8211* Simon, also known as Peter, and his brother Andrew \uc1\u8211* casting a net into the sea; for they were fishermen.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}\uc1\u8216*Come and follow me,\uc1\u8217* Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*and I will teach you to fish for people.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}The two men left their nets at once and followed him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Going further on, he saw two other men who were also brothers, James, Zebedee\uc1\u8217*s son, and his brother John, in their boat with their father, mending their nets. Jesus called them,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}and they at once left their boat and their father, and followed him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Jesus went all through Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, proclaiming the good news of the kingdom, and curing every kind of disease and every kind of sickness among the people;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}and his fame spread all through Syria. They brought to him all who were ill with any form of disease, or who were suffering pain \uc1\u8211* any who were either possessed by demons, or were lunatic, or paralysed; and he cured them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}He was followed by large crowds from Galilee, the district of the Ten Towns, Jerusalem, Judea, and from beyond the Jordan.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}On seeing the crowds of people, Jesus went up the hill; and, when he had taken his seat, his disciples came up to him;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and he began to teach them, saying:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8216*Blessed are the poor in spirit,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Blessed are the mourners,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for they will be comforted.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Blessed are the gentle,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for they will inherit the earth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for they will be satisfied.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Blessed are the merciful,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for they will find mercy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Blessed are the pure in heart,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for they will see God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Blessed are the peacemakers,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for they will be called children of God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Blessed are those who have been persecuted in the cause of righteousness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8216*Blessed are you when people insult you, and persecute you, and say all kinds of evil lies about you because of me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Be glad and rejoice, because your reward in heaven will be great; this is the way they persecuted the prophets who lived before you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8216*You are salt for the world. But if salt becomes tasteless, how can it be made salty again? It is no longer good for anything, but is thrown away, and trampled underfoot.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}It is you who are the light of the world. A town that stands on a hill cannot be hidden.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}People do not light a lamp and put it under a basket, but on the lamp-stand, where it gives light to everyone in the house.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Let your light so shine before the eyes of others so that, seeing your good actions, they will praise your Father who is in heaven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8216*Do not think that I have come to do away with the Law or the prophets; I have not come to do away with them, but to complete them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For I tell you, until the heavens and the earth disappear, not even the smallest letter, nor one stroke of a letter, will disappear from the Law until all is done.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Whoever, therefore, breaks one of these commandments, even the least of them, and teaches others to do so, will be the least esteemed in the kingdom of heaven; but whoever keeps them, and teaches others to do so, will be esteemed great in the kingdom of heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Indeed I tell you that, unless you obey God\uc1\u8217*s commands better than of the teachers of the Law, and Pharisees, you will never enter the kingdom of heaven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8216*You have heard that to our ancestors it was said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*You must not commit murder,\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*Whoever commits murder will be brought to trial.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}But I say to you that anyone who is angry at their brother or sister will be brought to trial; and whoever insults their brother or sister will be brought before the High Council, while whoever calls them a fool will be in danger of the fires of Gehenna.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Therefore, when presenting your gift at the altar, if even there you remember that your brother or sister has something against you,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}leave your gift there, before the altar, go and be reconciled to them, first, then come and present your gift.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Be ready to make friends with your opponent, even when you meet them on your way to the court; otherwise they might hand you over to the judge, and the judge to the judicial officer, and you will be thrown into prison.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}I tell you, you will not come out until you have paid the last cent.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}\uc1\u8216*You have heard that it was said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*You must not commit adultery.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}But I say to you that anyone who looks at a woman and desires her has already committed adultery with her in his heart.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}If your right eye causes you to sin, take it out and throw it away. It would be best for you to lose one part of your body, and not to have the whole of it thrown into Gehenna.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}And, if your right hand causes you to sin, cut it off and throw it away. It would be best for you to lose one part of your body, and not to have the whole of it go down to Gehenna.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}\uc1\u8216*It was also said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Let anyone who divorces his wife serve her with a notice of separation.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}But I say to you that anyone who divorces his wife, except on the ground of some serious sexual sin, leads to her committing adultery; while anyone who marries her after her divorce is guilty of adultery.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Again, you have heard that our ancestors were told \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Do not break your oaths, keep your vows to the Lord.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}But I say to you that you must not swear at all, either by heaven, since that is God\uc1\u8217*s throne,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}or by the earth, since that is his footstool, or by Jerusalem, since that is the city of the Great King.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Nor should you swear by your head, since you cannot make a single hair either white or black.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Let your words be simply \uc1\u8220*Yes\uc1\u8221* or \uc1\u8220*No\uc1\u8221*; anything beyond this comes from what is evil.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}\uc1\u8216*You have heard that it was said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*An eye for an eye and a tooth for a tooth.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}But I say to you that you must not resist those who wrong you; but, if anyone strikes you on the right cheek, turn the other to them also.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}If someone sues you for your shirt, let them have your cloak as well.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}If you are forced to carry a soldier\uc1\u8217*s pack for one mile, carry it two.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}Give to anyone who asks and, if someone wants to borrow from you, do not turn them away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}You have heard that it was said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*You must love your neighbour and hate your enemy.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}But what I tell you is this: love your enemies, and pray for those who persecute you,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}so that you may become children of your Father who is in heaven; for he causes his sun to rise on bad and good alike, and sends rain on the righteous and on the unrighteous.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}For, if you love only those who love you, what reward will you have? Even the tax collectors do this!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}And, if you only welcome your brothers and sisters, what are you doing more than others? Even the Gentiles do this!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}You, then, must become perfect \uc1\u8211* as your heavenly Father is perfect.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}\uc1\u8216*Take care not to perform your religious duties in public in order to be seen by others; if you do, your Father who is in heaven has no reward for you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Therefore, when you do acts of charity, do not have a trumpet blown in front of you, as hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets so that people will praise them. There, I tell you, is their reward!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}But, when you do acts of charity, do not let your left hand know what your right hand is doing,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}so that your charity may be secret; and your Father, who sees what is in secret, will reward you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*And, when you pray, you are not to behave as hypocrites do. They like to pray standing in the synagogues and at the corners of the streets, so that people will see them. There, I tell you, is their reward!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But, when one of you prays, they should go into their own room, shut the door, and pray to their Father who dwells in secret; and their Father, who sees what is secret, will reward them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}When praying, do not repeat the same words over and over again, as is done by the Gentiles, who think that by using many words they will obtain a hearing.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Do not imitate them; for God, your Father, knows what you need before you ask him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}You, therefore, should pray like this \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Our Father, who is in heaven,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
may your name be held holy,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}your kingdom come, your will be done \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
on earth, as in heaven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Give us today
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the bread that we will need;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}and forgive us our wrongdoings,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
as we have forgiven those who have wronged us;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}and take us not into temptation,
