{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}To his Excellency, Theophilus.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
Many attempts have been already made to draw up an account of those events which have reached their conclusion among us,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}just as they were reported to us by those who from the beginning were eye-witnesses, and afterwards became bearers of the message.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And, therefore, I also, since I have investigated all these events with great care from their very beginning, have resolved to write a connected history of them for you,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}in order that you may be able to satisfy yourself of the accuracy of the story which you have heard from the lips of others.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Birth, Parentage, Infancy and Boyhood

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}In the reign of Herod, king of Judea, there was a priest named Zechariah, who belonged to the division called after Abijah. His wife, whose name was Elizabeth, was also a descendant of Aaron.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}They were both righteous people, who lived blameless lives, guiding their steps by all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}But they had no child, Elizabeth being barren; and both of them were advanced in years.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}One day, when Zechariah was officiating as priest before God, during the turn of his division,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}it fell to him by lot, in accordance with the practice among the priests, to go into the Temple of the Lord and burn incense;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}and, as it was the Hour of Incense, the people were all praying outside.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And an angel of the Lord appeared to him, standing on the right of the Altar of Incense.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Zechariah was startled at the sight and was awe-struck.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But the angel said to him, \uc1\u8216*Do not be afraid, Zechariah; your prayer has been heard, and your wife Elizabeth will bear you a son, whom you will call by the name John.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}He will be to you a joy and a delight; and many will rejoice over his birth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}For he will be great in the sight of the Lord; he will not drink any wine or strong drink, and he will be filled with the Holy Spirit from the very hour of his birth,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}and will reconcile many of the Israelites to the Lord their God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}He will go before him in the spirit and with the power of Elijah, to reconcile fathers to their children and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous, and so make ready for the Lord a people prepared for him.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8216*How can I be sure of this?\uc1\u8217* Zechariah asked the angel. \uc1\u8216*For I am an old man and my wife is advanced in years.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}\uc1\u8216*I am Gabriel,\uc1\u8217* the angel answered, \uc1\u8216*who stand in the presence of God, and I have been sent to speak to you and to bring you this good news.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And now you will be silent and unable to speak until the day when this takes place, because you did not believe what I said, though my words will be fulfilled in due course.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Meanwhile the people were watching for Zechariah, wondering at his remaining so long in the Temple.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}When he came out, he was unable to speak to them, and they perceived that he had seen a vision there. But Zechariah kept making signs to them, and remained dumb.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And, as soon as his term of service was finished, he returned home.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}After this his wife, Elizabeth, became pregnant and lived in seclusion for five months.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}\uc1\u8216*The Lord has done this for me,\uc1\u8217* she said, \uc1\u8216*he has shown me kindness and taken away the public disgrace of childlessness under which I have been living.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Six months later the angel Gabriel was sent from God to a town in Galilee called Nazareth,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}to a maiden there who was engaged to a man named Joseph, a descendant of David. Her name was Mary.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Gabriel came into her presence and greeted her, saying, \uc1\u8216*You have been shown great favour \uc1\u8211* the Lord is with you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Mary was much disturbed at his words, and was wondering to herself what such a greeting could mean,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}when the angel spoke again, \uc1\u8216*Do not be afraid, Mary, for you have found favour with God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}And now, you will conceive and give birth to a son, and you will give him the name Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}The child will be great and will be called \uc1\u8220*Son of the Most High,\uc1\u8221* and the Lord God will give him the throne of his ancestor David,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}and he will reign over the descendants of Jacob for ever; And to his kingdom there will be no end.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}\uc1\u8216*How can this be?\uc1\u8217* Mary asked the angel. \uc1\u8216*For I have no husband.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}\uc1\u8216*The Holy Spirit will descend on you,\uc1\u8217* answered the angel, \uc1\u8216*and the Power of the Most High will overshadow you; and therefore the child will be called \uc1\u8220*holy,\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*Son of God.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}And Elizabeth, your cousin, is herself also expecting a son in her old age; and it is now the sixth month with her, though she is called barren;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}for no promise from God will fail to be fulfilled.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}\uc1\u8216*I am the servant of the Lord,\uc1\u8217* exclaimed Mary. \uc1\u8216*Let it be with me as you have said.\uc1\u8217* Then the angel left her.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Soon after this Mary set out, and made her way quickly into the hill-country, to a town in Judah;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}and there she went into Zechariah\uc1\u8217*s house and greeted Elizabeth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}When Elizabeth heard Mary\uc1\u8217*s greeting, the child moved within her, and Elizabeth herself was filled with the Holy Spirit,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}and cried aloud, \uc1\u8216*Blessed are you among women, and blessed is your unborn child!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}But how have I this honour, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}For, as soon as your greeting reached my ears, the child moved within me with delight!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}Happy indeed is she who believed that the promise which she received from the Lord would be fulfilled.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}And Mary said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*My soul exalts the Lord,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}and my spirit delights in God my Saviour,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}for he has looked with favour on his humble servant girl.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
From now on all generations will call me blessed!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}\uc1\u8216*For the Almighty has done great things for me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and holy is his name.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}He has mercy on those who revere him
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in every generation.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}\uc1\u8216*Mighty are the deeds of his arm!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He has scattered the self-satisfied proud,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}he has cast down the mighty from their thrones,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and he uplifts the humble,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}he has filled the hungry with good things,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the rich he has sent away empty.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}\uc1\u8216*He has stretched out his hand to his servant Israel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
ever mindful of his mercy,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}as he promised to our ancestors,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
to Abraham and his descendants for ever.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}Mary stayed with Elizabeth about three months, and then returned to her home.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 57}When Elizabeth\uc1\u8217*s time came, she gave birth to a son;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 58}and her neighbours and relatives, hearing of the great goodness of the Lord to her, came to share her joy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 59}A week later they met to circumcise the child, and were about to call him Zechariah after his father,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 60}when his mother spoke up, \uc1\u8216*No, he is to be called John.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 61}\uc1\u8216*You have no relation of that name!\uc1\u8217* they exclaimed;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 62}and they made signs to the child\uc1\u8217*s father, to find out what he wished the child to be called.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 63}Asking for a writing tablet, he wrote the words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*His name is John.\uc1\u8221* Everyone was surprised{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 64}and immediately Zechariah recovered his voice and the use of his tongue, and began to bless God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 65}All their neighbours were awe-struck at this, and throughout the hill-country of Judea the whole story was much talked about.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 66}All who heard it kept it in mind, asking one another \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*What can this child be destined to become?\uc1\u8217* For the Power of the Lord was with him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 67}Then his father Zechariah was filled with the Holy Spirit, and, speaking under inspiration, said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 68}\uc1\u8216*Blessed is the Lord, the God of Israel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
who has visited his people and wrought their deliverance,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 69}and has raised up for us the strength of our salvation
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in the house of his servant David \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 70}as he promised by the lips of his holy prophets of old \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 71}salvation from our enemies and from the hands of all who hate us,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 72}showing mercy to our ancestors,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and mindful of his sacred covenant.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 

\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 73}This was the oath which he swore to our ancestor Abraham \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 74}that we should be rescued from the hands of our enemies,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 75}and should serve him without fear in holiness and righteousness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
in his presence all our days.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 

\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 76}And you, child, will be called prophet of the Most High,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for you will go before the Lord to make ready his way,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 77}to give his people the knowledge of salvation
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
through the forgiveness of their sins,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 78}through the tender mercy of our God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
whereby the dawn will break on us from heaven,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 79}to give light to those who live in darkness and the shadow of death,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and guide our feet into the way of peace.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 80}The child grew and became strong in spirit, and he lived in the wilds until the time came for his appearance before Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}About that time an edict was issued by the Emperor Augustus that a census should be taken of the whole Empire.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}(This was the first census taken while Quirinius was Governor of Syria).{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And everyone went to his own town to be registered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Among others Joseph went up from the town of Nazareth in Galilee to Bethlehem, the town of David, in Judea \uc1\u8211* because he belonged to the family and house of David \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}to be registered with Mary, his engaged wife, who was about to become a mother.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}While they were there her time came,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and she gave birth to her first child, a son. And because there was no room for them in the inn, she swathed him round and laid him in a manger.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}In that same countryside were shepherds out in the open fields, watching their flocks that night,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}when an angel of the Lord suddenly stood by them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them; and they were seized with fear.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8216*Have no fear,\uc1\u8217* the angel said. \uc1\u8216*For I bring you good news of a great joy in store for all the nation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}This day there has been born to you, in the town of David, a Saviour, who is Christ and Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And this will be the sign for you. You will find the infant swathed, and lying in a manger.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then suddenly there appeared with the angel a multitude of the heavenly Host, praising God, and singing \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}\uc1\u8216*glory to God on high,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and on earth peace among those in whom he finds pleasure.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Now, when the angels had left them and gone back to heaven, the shepherds said to one another, \uc1\u8216*Let us go at once to Bethlehem, and see this thing that has happened, of which the Lord has told us.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}So they went quickly, and found Mary and Joseph, and the infant lying in a manger;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and, when they saw it, they told of all that had been said to them about this child.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}All who heard the shepherds were astonished at their story,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}while Mary treasured in her heart all that they said, and thought about it often.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And the shepherds went back, giving glory and praise to God for all that they had heard and seen. It had all happened as they had been told.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Eight days after the birth of the child, when it was time to circumcise him, he received the name Jesus \uc1\u8211* the name given him by the angel before his conception.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}When the period of purification of mother and child, required by the Law of Moses, came to an end, his parents took the child up to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}in compliance with the Law of the Lord that every firstborn male will be dedicated to the Lord,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}and also to offer the sacrifice required by the Law of the Lord \uc1\u8211* a pair of turtle-doves or two young pigeons.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}There was at that time in Jerusalem a man named Simeon, a righteous and devout man, who lived in constant expectation of  Israel\uc1\u8217*s consulation, and under the guidance of the Holy Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he should not die until he had seen the Lord\uc1\u8217*s Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Moved by the Spirit, Simeon came into the Temple Courts, and, when the parents brought in the child Jesus, to do for him what was customary under the Law,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Simeon himself took the child in his arms, and blessed God, and said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}\uc1\u8216*Now, Lord, you will let your servant go,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
according to your word, in peace,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}for my eyes have seen the salvation
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}which you have prepared in the sight of all nations \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}a light to bring light to the Gentiles,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and to be the glory of your people Israel.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}While the child\uc1\u8217*s father and mother were wondering at what was said about him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Simeon gave them his blessing, and said to Mary, the child\uc1\u8217*s mother, \uc1\u8216*This child is appointed to be the cause of the fall and rise of many in Israel, and to be a sign much spoken against \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Yes, the sword will pierce your own heart \uc1\u8211* and so the thoughts in many minds will be disclosed.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}There was also a prophet named Hannah, a daughter of Phanuel and of the tribe of Asher. She was far advanced in years, having lived with her husband for seven years after marriage,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}and then a widow, until she had reached the age of eighty-four. She never left the Temple Courts, but, fasting and praying, worshiped God night and day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}At that moment she came up, and began publicly to thank God and to speak about the child to all who were looking for the deliverance of Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}When the child\uc1\u8217*s parents had done everything required by the Law of the Lord, they returned to Galilee to their own town of Nazareth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}The child grew and became strong and wise, and the blessing of God was on him.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}Every year the child\uc1\u8217*s parents used to go to Jerusalem at the Passover Festival.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}When Jesus was twelve years old, they went according to custom to Jerusalem,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}and had finished their visit; but, when they started to return, the boy Jesus remained behind in Jerusalem, without their knowing it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}Thinking that he was with their fellow travellers, they went one day\uc1\u8217*s journey before searching for him among their relatives and acquaintances;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}and then, as they did not find him, they returned to Jerusalem, searching everywhere for him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}It was not until the third day that they found him in the Temple Courts, sitting among the teachers, now listening to them, now asking them questions.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}All who listened to him marvelled at his intelligence and his answers.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}His parents were amazed when they saw him, and his mother said to him, \uc1\u8216*My child, why have you treated us like this? Your father and I have been searching for you in great distress.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}\uc1\u8216*What made you search for me?\uc1\u8217* he answered. \uc1\u8216*Didn\uc1\u8217*t you know that I must be in my Father\uc1\u8217*s house?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}His parents did not understand what he meant.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}However he went down with them to Nazareth, and submitted himself to their control; and his mother treasured all that was said in her heart.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}And Jesus grew in wisdom as he grew in years, and gained the blessing of God and people.
\par}

