\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}In the fifteenth year of the reign of the Emperor Tiberius, when Pontius Pilate was governor of Judea, Herod ruler of Galilee, his brother Philip ruler of the territory comprising Ituraea and Trachonitis, and Lysanias ruler of Abilene,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and when Annas and Caiaphas were high priests, a command from God came to John, the son of Zechariah, while he was in the wilderness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And John went through the whole district of the Jordan, proclaiming a baptism of repentance, for the forgiveness of sins.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}This was in fulfilment of what is said in the writings of the prophet Isaiah \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*The voice of one crying aloud in the wilderness:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*Make ready the way of the Lord,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
make his paths straight.
