every mountain and hill will be levelled.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The winding ways will be straightened,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the rough roads made smooth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and everyone will see the salvation of God.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And John said to the crowds that went to be baptized by him, \uc1\u8216*You children of snakes! Who has prompted you to seek refuge from the coming judgment?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Let your lives, then, prove your repentance; and do not begin to say among yourselves \uc1\u8220*Abraham is our ancestor,\uc1\u8221* for I tell you that out of these stones God is able to raise descendants for Abraham!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Already, indeed, the axe is lying at the root of the trees. Therefore every tree that fails to bear good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8216*What are we to do then?\uc1\u8217* the people asked.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8216*Let anyone who has two coats,\uc1\u8217* answered John, \uc1\u8216*share with the person who has none; and anyone who has food do the same.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Even tax collectors came to be baptized, and said to John, \uc1\u8216*Teacher, what are we to do?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8216*Do not collect more than you have authority to demand,\uc1\u8217* John answered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And when some soldiers on active service asked \uc1\u8216*And we \uc1\u8211* what are we to do?\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*Never use violence, or exact anything by false accusation; and be content with your pay.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Then, while the people were in suspense, and were all debating with themselves whether John could be the Christ,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}John, addressing them all, said, \uc1\u8216*I, indeed, baptize you with water; but there is coming one more powerful than I, and I am not fit even to unfasten his sandals. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}His winnowing-fan is in his hand so that he may clear his threshing-floor, and store the grain in his barn, but the chaff he will burn with a fire that cannot be put out.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And so with many different appeals John told his good news to the people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}But when John rebuked Herod the ruler, for Herodia his brother\uc1\u8217*s wife, and for all the evil things that he had done,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Herod crowned them all by shutting John up in prison.
\par}

{\pard 

