{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Work in Galilee

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Moved by the power of the Spirit, Jesus returned to Galilee. Reports about him spread through all that region;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and he began to teach in their synagogues, and was honoured by everyone.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Coming to Nazareth, where he had been brought up, Jesus, as was his custom, went on the Sabbath into the synagogue, and stood up to read the scriptures.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}He was given the book of the prophet Isaiah; and Jesus opened the book and found the place where it says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8220*The Spirit of the Lord is on me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for he has consecrated me to bring good news to the poor,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
he has sent me to proclaim release to captives and restoration of sight to the blind,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
to set the oppressed at liberty,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
