\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then, closing the book and returning it to the attendant, he sat down. The eyes of all in the synagogue were fixed on him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}and Jesus began,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*This very day this passage has been fulfilled in your hearing.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}All who were present spoke well of him, and were astonished at the beautiful words that fell from his lips. \uc1\u8216*Isn\uc1\u8217*t Joseph\uc1\u8217*s son?\uc1\u8217* they asked.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8216*Doubtless,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus, \uc1\u8216*you will remind me of the saying \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Doctor, cure yourself;\uc1\u8221* and you will say \uc1\u8220*Do here in your own country all that we have heard that has been done at Capernaum.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}I tell you,\uc1\u8217* he continued, \uc1\u8216*that no prophet is acceptable in his own country.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}There were, doubtless, many widows in Israel in Elijah\uc1\u8217*s days, when the heavens were closed for three years and six months, and a severe famine prevailed throughout the country;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}and yet it was not to one of them that Elijah was sent, but to a widow at Zarephath in Sidonia.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And there were many lepers in Israel in the time of the prophet Elisha, yet it was not one of them who was made clean, but Naaman the Syrian.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}All the people in the synagogue, as they listened to this, became enraged.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Starting up, they drove Jesus out of the town, and led him to the brow of the hill on which their town stood, intending to hurl him down.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}But he passed through the middle of the crowd and went on his way.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Then Jesus went down to Capernaum, a city in Galilee. On the Sabbath he taught the people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}They were amazed at his teaching, because his words were spoken with authority.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}In the synagogue there was a man with the spirit of a foul demon in him, who called out loudly,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}\uc1\u8216*Stop! What do you want with us, Jesus of Nazareth? Have you come to destroy us? I know who you are \uc1\u8211* the Holy One of God!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}But Jesus rebuked the demon. \uc1\u8216*Be silent! Come out from him,\uc1\u8217* he said. The demon flung the man down in the middle of the people, and then came out from him, without causing him further harm.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}And they were all lost in amazement, and kept saying to one another, \uc1\u8216*What words are these? For he gives his commands to the foul spirits with a marvellous authority, and they come out.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}And rumours about Jesus traveled through every place in the region.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}On leaving the synagogue, Jesus went into Simon\uc1\u8217*s house. Now Simon\uc1\u8217*s mother-in-law was suffering from a severe attack of fever, and they asked Jesus to cure her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Bending over her, he rebuked the fever; the fever left her, and she immediately got up and began to take care of them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}At sunset, all who had friends suffering from various diseases took them to Jesus; and he placed his hands on everyone of them and cured them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}And even demons came out from many people, screaming \uc1\u8220*You are the Son of God.\uc1\u8221* Jesus rebuked them, and would not allow them to speak, because they knew that he was the Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}At daybreak, Jesus went out and walked to a lonely spot. But crowds of people began to look for him; and they came to where he was and tried to detain him and prevent his leaving them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}Jesus, however, said to them, \uc1\u8216*I must take the good news of the kingdom of God to the other towns too, for that was why I was sent.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}And he continued to make his proclamation in the synagogues of Judea.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}Once, when the people were pressing round Jesus as they listened to God\uc1\u8217*s message, he happened to be standing by the shore of the Lake of Gennesaret, and saw two boats close to the shore.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The fishermen had gone away from them and were washing the nets.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So, getting into one of the boats, which belonged to Simon, Jesus asked him to push off a little way from the shore, and then sat down and taught the people from the boat.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}When he had finished speaking, he said to Simon, \uc1\u8216*Push off into deep water, and throw out your nets for a haul.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*We have been hard at work all night, Sir,\uc1\u8217* answered Simon, \uc1\u8216*and have not caught anything, but, at your bidding, I will throw out the nets.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}They did so, and enclosed such a great shoal of fish that their nets began to break.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}So they signalled to their partners in the other boat to come and help them; and they came and filled both the boats so full of fish that they were almost sinking.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}When Simon Peter saw this, he threw himself down at Jesus\uc1\u8217* knees, exclaiming, \uc1\u8216*Master, leave me, for I am a sinful man!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For he and all who were with him were lost in amazement at the haul of fish which they had made;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}and so, too, were James and John, Zebedee\uc1\u8217*s sons, who were Simon\uc1\u8217*s partners. \uc1\u8216*Do not be afraid,\uc1\u8217* Jesus said to Simon, \uc1\u8216*from today you will catch people.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And, when they had brought their boats to shore, they left everything, and followed him.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}On one occasion Jesus was staying in a town, when he saw a man who was covered with leprosy. When the leper saw Jesus, he threw himself on his face and implored his help, \uc1\u8216*Master, if only you are willing, you are able to make me clean.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Stretching out his hand, Jesus touched him, saying as he did so, \uc1\u8216*I am willing; become clean.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
Instantly the leprosy left the man;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}and then Jesus impressed on him that he was not to say a word to anyone, \uc1\u8216*but,\uc1\u8217* he added, \uc1\u8216*set out and show yourself to the priest, and make the offerings for your cleansing, in the manner directed by Moses, as evidence of your cure.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}However, the story about Jesus spread all the more, and great crowds came together to listen to him, and to be cured of their illnesses;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}but Jesus used to withdraw to lonely places and pray.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}On one of those days, when Jesus was teaching, some Pharisees and Doctors of the Law were sitting near by. (They had come from all the villages in Galilee and Judea, and from Jerusalem; and the power of the Lord was on Jesus, so that he could work cures.){\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And there some men brought on a bed a man who was paralysed. They tried to get him in and lay him before Jesus;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}but, finding no way of getting him in owing to the crowd, they went up on the roof and lowered him through the tiles, with his pallet, into the middle of the people and in front of Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}When he saw their faith, Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Friend, your sins have been forgiven you.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}The teachers of the Law and the Pharisees began debating about this. \uc1\u8216*Who is this man who speaks so blasphemously?\uc1\u8217* they asked. \uc1\u8216*Who can forgive sins except God?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}When Jesus became aware of the way in which they were debating, he turned to them and exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*What are you debating with yourselves?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Which is the easier? \uc1\u8211* to say \uc1\u8220*Your sins have been forgiven you\uc1\u8221*? Or to say \uc1\u8220*Get up, and walk\uc1\u8221*?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}But so that you may know that the Son of Man has power on earth to forgive sins\uc1\u8217* \uc1\u8211* he spoke to the paralysed man \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*To you I say, Get up, and take up your pallet, and go to your home.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Instantly the man stood up before their eyes, took up what he had been lying on, and went to his home, praising God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}The people, one and all, were lost in amazement, and praised God; and in great awe they said, \uc1\u8216*We have seen marvellous things today!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}After this, Jesus went out; and he noticed a tax-gatherer, named Levi, sitting in the tax office, and said to him, \uc1\u8216*Follow me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Levi left everything and got up and followed him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}And Levi gave a great banquet at his house, in honour of Jesus; and a large number of tax collectors and others were having dinner with them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}The Pharisees and the teachers of the Law belonging to their party complained of this to the disciples of Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}In answer Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*It is not those who are well who need a doctor, but those who are ill.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}I have not come to call the religious, but the outcast, to repent.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}\uc1\u8216*John\uc1\u8217*s disciples,\uc1\u8217* they said to Jesus, \uc1\u8216*Often fast and say prayers, and so do the disciples of the Pharisees, while yours are eating and drinking!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}But Jesus answered them, \uc1\u8216*Can you make the groom\uc1\u8217*s friends fast while the groom is with them?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}But the days will come \uc1\u8211* a time when the groom will be taken away from them; and they will fast then, when those days come.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Then, as an illustration, Jesus said to them, \uc1\u8216*No one ever tears a piece from a new garment and puts it on an old one; for, if they do, they will not only tear the new garment, but the piece from the new one will not match the old.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}And no one puts new wine into old wine-skins; for, if they do, the new wine will burst the skins, and the wine itself will run out, and the skins be lost.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}But new wine must be put into fresh skins.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}No one after drinking old wine wishes for new. \uc1\u8220*No,\uc1\u8221* they say, \uc1\u8220*the old is excellent.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}One Sabbath Jesus was walking through cornfields, and his disciples were picking the ears of wheat, and rubbing them in their hands, and eating them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8216*Why are you doing what it is not allowable to do on the Sabbath?\uc1\u8217* asked some of the Pharisees.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Jesus\uc1\u8217* answer was, \uc1\u8216*Haven\uc1\u8217*t you read even of what David did, when he was hungry, he and his companions \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}That he went into the house of God, and took the consecrated bread and ate it, and gave some to his companions, though only the priests are allowed to eat it?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Then Jesus added, \uc1\u8216*The Son of Man is lord even of the Sabbath.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}On another Sabbath Jesus went into the synagogue and taught; and there was a man there whose right hand was withered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The teachers of the Law and the Pharisees watched Jesus closely, to see if he would work cures on the Sabbath, so that they might find a charge to bring against him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Jesus, however, knew what was in the their minds, and said to the man whose hand was withered, \uc1\u8216*Stand up and come out into the middle.\uc1\u8217* The man stood up;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}and Jesus said to them, \uc1\u8216*I ask you, is it allowable to do good on the Sabbath \uc1\u8211* or harm? To save a life, or let it perish?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Then, looking round at them all, he said to the man, \uc1\u8216*Stretch out your hand.\uc1\u8217* The man did so; and his hand had become sound.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But the teachers of the Law and the Pharisees were mad with rage, and consulted together what they could do to Jesus.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Now about that time, Jesus went out, up the hill, to pray, and spent the whole night in prayer to God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}When day came, he summoned his disciples, and chose twelve of them, whom he also named \uc1\u8220*apostles.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}They were Simon (whom Jesus also named Peter), and his brother Andrew, James, John, Philip, Bartholomew,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Matthew, Thomas, James son of Alphaeus, Simon known as the Zealot,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Judas son of James, and Judas Iscariot, who proved a traitor.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Afterwards Jesus came down the hill with them and took his stand on a level place. With him were a large crowd of his disciples, and great numbers of people from the whole of Judea, Jerusalem, and the coast district of Tyre and Sidon,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}who had come to hear him and to be restored to health. Those, too, who were troubled with foul spirits were cured;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and everyone in the crowd was trying to touch him, because a power went out from him which restored them all.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then, raising his eyes and looking at his disciples, Jesus said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*Blessed are you who are poor, for yours is the kingdom of God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
