{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for you will hunger.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Alas for you who laugh now,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for you will mourn and weep.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Alas for you when everyone speaks well of you;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for this is what their ancestors did to the false prophets.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 

\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}But to you who hear I say \uc1\u8211* love your enemies, show kindness to those who hate you,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}bless those who curse you, pray for those who insult you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}When someone gives one of you a blow on the cheek, offer the other cheek as well; and, when anyone takes away your cloak, do not keep back your coat either.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Give to everyone who asks of you; and, when anyone takes away what is yours, do not demand its return.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Do to others as you wish them to do to you.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 

\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}If you love only those who love you, what thanks will be due to you? Why, even the outcast love those who love them!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}For, if you show kindness only to those who show kindness to you, what thanks will be due to you? Even the outcast do that!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}If you lend only to those from whom you expect to get something, what thanks will be due to you? Even the outcast lend to the outcast in the hope of getting as much in return!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}But love your enemies, and show them kindness, and lend to them, never despairing. Then your reward will be great, and you will be sons of the Most High, for he is kind to the thankless and the bad.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 

\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Learn to be merciful \uc1\u8211* even as your Father is merciful.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Do not judge, and you will not be judged; do not condemn, and you will not be condemned. Forgive, and you will be forgiven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}Give, and others will give to you. A generous measure, pressed and shaken down, and running over, will they pour into your lap; for the standard you use will be the standard used for you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Then, speaking in parables, Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Can one blind person guide another? Will they not both fall into a ditch?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}A student is not above their teacher; yet every finished student will be like their teacher.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}And why do you look at the speck of sawdust in someone\uc1\u8217*s eye, while you pay no attention at all to the plank of wood in your own?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}How can you say to your friend \uc1\u8220*Friend, let me take out the speck in your eye,\uc1\u8221* while you yourself do not see the plank in your own? Hypocrite! Take out the plank from your own eye first, and then you will see clearly how to take out the speck in your friend\uc1\u8217*s.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}There is no such thing as a good tree bearing worthless fruit, or, on the other hand, a worthless tree bearing good fruit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}For every tree is known by its own fruit. People do not gather figs off thorn bushes, nor pick a bunch of grapes off a bramble.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}A good person, from the good stores of their heart, brings out what is good; while a bad person, from their bad stores, brings out what is bad. For what fills someone\uc1\u8217*s heart will rise to their lips.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}Why do you call me \uc1\u8220*Master! Master!\uc1\u8221* and yet fail to do what I tell you?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}Everyone who comes to me and listens to my teaching and acts on it \uc1\u8211* I will show you to whom they may be compared.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}They may be compared to a person building a house, who dug, and went deep, and laid the foundation on the rock. Then, when a flood came, the river swept down on that house, but had no power to shake it, because it had been built well.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}But those who have listened and not acted on what they have heard may be compared to a person who built a house on the ground without any foundation. The river swept down on it, and the house immediately collapsed; and great was the crash that followed.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 7}When Jesus had brought to a conclusion all that he had then had to say to the people, he entered Capernaum.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}A centurion in the Roman army had a slave whom he valued, and who was seriously ill \uc1\u8211* almost at the point of death.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And, hearing about Jesus, he sent some Jewish elders to him, with the request that he would come and save his slave\uc1\u8217*s life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}When they found Jesus, they earnestly implored him to do so. \uc1\u8216*He deserves the favour from you,\uc1\u8217* they said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*For he is devoted to our nation, and himself built our synagogue for us.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}So Jesus went with them. But, when he was no great distance from the house, the centurion sent some friends with the message \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Do not trouble yourself, Sir; for I am unworthy to receive you under my roof.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}That was why I did not even venture to come to you myself; but speak, and let my manservant be cured.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For I myself am a man under the orders of others, with soldiers under me; and if I say to one of them \uc1\u8220*Go,\uc1\u8221* he goes, and to another \uc1\u8220*Come,\uc1\u8221* he comes, and to my slave \uc1\u8220*Do this,\uc1\u8221* he does it.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Jesus was surprised to hear these words from him; and, turning to the crowd which was following him, he said, \uc1\u8216*I tell you, nowhere in Israel have I met with such faith as this!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And, when the messengers returned to the house, they found the slave recovered.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Shortly after, Jesus went to a town called Nain, his disciples and a great crowd going with him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Just as he approached the gate of the town, there was a dead man being carried out for burial \uc1\u8211* an only son, and his mother was a widow. A large number of the people of the town were with her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}When he saw her, the Master was moved with compassion for her, and he said to her, \uc1\u8216*Do not weep.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Then he went up and touched the bier, and the bearers stopped; and Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Young man, I am speaking to you \uc1\u8211* Rise!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}The dead man sat up and began to talk, and Jesus restored him to his mother.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Everyone was awe-struck and began praising God. \uc1\u8216*A great prophet has arisen among us,\uc1\u8217* they said. \uc1\u8216*God has visited his people.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And this story about Jesus spread all through Judea, and in the neighbouring countries as well.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}All these events were reported to John by his disciples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}So he summoned two of them, and sent them to the Master to ask \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Are you \uc1\u8220*the coming one,\uc1\u8221* or are we to look for someone else?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}When these men found Jesus, they said, \uc1\u8216*John the Baptist has sent us to you to ask \uc1\u8211* Are you \uc1\u8220*the coming one,\uc1\u8221* or are we to look for somebody else?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}At that very time Jesus had cured many people of diseases, afflictions, and wicked spirits, and had given many blind people their sight.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}So his answer to the question was, \uc1\u8216*Go and report to John what you have witnessed and heard \uc1\u8211* the blind recover their sight, the lame walk, the lepers are made clean, and the deaf hear, the dead are raised to life, the good news is told to the poor.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And blessed is the person who finds no hindrance in me.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}When John\uc1\u8217*s messengers had left, Jesus, speaking to the crowds, began to say with reference to John,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}\uc1\u8216*What did you go out into the wilderness to look at? A reed waving in the wind? If not, what did you go out to see? A man dressed in rich clothing? Why, those who are accustomed to fine clothes and luxury live in royal palaces.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}What then did you go to see? A prophet? Yes, I tell you, and far more than a prophet.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}This is the man of whom scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I am sending my messenger ahead of you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and he will prepare your way before you.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}There is, I tell you, no one born of a woman who is greater than John; and yet the least in the kingdom of God is greater than he.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}(All the people, when they heard this, and even the tax collectors, having accepted John\uc1\u8217*s baptism, acknowledged the justice of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}But the Pharisees and the students of the Law, having rejected John\uc1\u8217*s baptism, frustrated God\uc1\u8217*s purpose in regard to them.)
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}\uc1\u8216*To what then,\uc1\u8217* Jesus continued, \uc1\u8216*should I compare the people of the present generation? What are they like?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}They are like some little children who are sitting in the marketplace and calling out to one another \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*We have played the flute for you, but you have not danced; We have wailed, but you have not wept!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}For now that John the Baptist has come, not eating bread or drinking wine, you are saying \uc1\u8220*He has a demon in him\uc1\u8221*;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}and now that the Son of Man has come, eating and drinking, you are saying \uc1\u8220*Here is a glutton and a wine-drinker, a friend of tax collectors and outcasts.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}And yet wisdom is vindicated by all her children.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}One of the Pharisees asked Jesus to dine with him, so Jesus went to his house and took his place at the table.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Just then a woman, who was an outcast in the town, having heard that Jesus was eating in the Pharisee\uc1\u8217*s house, brought an alabaster jar of perfume,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}and placed herself behind Jesus, near his feet, weeping. Then she began to make his feet wet with her tears, and she dried them with the hair of her head, repeatedly kissing his feet and anointing them with the perfume.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}When the Pharisee who had invited Jesus saw this, he said to himself, \uc1\u8216*Had this man been \uc1\u8220*the prophet,\uc1\u8221* he would have known who, and what sort of woman, this is who is touching him, and that she is an outcast.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}But, addressing him, Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Simon, I have something to say to you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*Pray do so, teacher,\uc1\u8217* Simon answered; and Jesus began,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}\uc1\u8216*There were two people who were in debt to a moneylender; one owed five hundred silver coins, and the other fifty.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}As they were unable to pay, he forgave them both. Which of them, do you think, will love him the more?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}\uc1\u8216*I suppose,\uc1\u8217* answered Simon, \uc1\u8216*it will be the man to whom he forgave the greater debt.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*You are right,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}and then, turning to the woman, he said to Simon, \uc1\u8216*Do you see this woman? I came into your house \uc1\u8211* you gave me no water for my feet, but she has made my feet wet with her tears and dried them with her hair.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}You did not give me one kiss, but she, from the moment I came in, has not ceased to kiss my feet.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}You did not anoint even my head with oil, but she has anointed my feet with perfume.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}So I tell you, her great love shows that her sins, many as they are, have been pardoned. One who is pardoned little loves little.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}Then he said to the woman, \uc1\u8216*Your sins have been pardoned.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}The other guests began to say to one another, \uc1\u8216*Who is this man who even pardons sins?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}But Jesus said to the woman, \uc1\u8216*Your faith has delivered you; go, and peace be with you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 8}Shortly afterwards, Jesus went on a journey through the towns and villages, proclaiming the good news of the kingdom of God. With him went the Twelve,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}as well as some women who had been cured of wicked spirits and of infirmities. They were Mary, known as Mary of Magdala (from whom seven demons had been expelled),{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and Joanna (the wife of Herod\uc1\u8217*s steward, Chuza), and Susannah, and many others \uc1\u8211* all of whom provided for Jesus and his apostles out of their own resources.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Once, when a great crowd was collecting, and, when the people of town after town were flocking to Jesus, he spoke to them in the form of a parable,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*The sower went out to sow his seed; and, as he was sowing, some of the seed fell along the path and was trodden on; and the wild birds ate it up.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Other seed fell on rock, and, as soon as it began to grow, because it had no moisture, it withered away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Other seed fell in the middle of brambles, but the brambles grew up with it and choked it entirely.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Other seed fell into rich soil, and grew, and gave a hundredfold return.\uc1\u8217* After saying this, Jesus cried aloud, \uc1\u8216*Let those who have ears to hear with hear.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}His disciples asked Jesus the meaning of this parable.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8216*To you,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*the knowledge of the hidden truths of the kingdom of God has been imparted, but to others in parables only, so that though they have eyes they may not see, and though they have ears, they may not understand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}This is the parable \uc1\u8211* The seed is God\uc1\u8217*s message.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}By the seed which fell along the path are meant those who hear the message; but then comes the devil and carries away the message from their minds, to prevent their believing it and being saved.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}By the seed which fell on the rock are meant those who, as soon as they hear the message, welcome it joyfully; but they have no root, and believe it only for a time, and, when the time of temptation comes, they draw back.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}By that which fell among the brambles are meant those who hear the message, but who, as they go on their way, are completely choked by this world\uc1\u8217*s cares and wealth and pleasures, and bring nothing to perfection.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But by that in the good ground are meant those who, having heard the message, keep it in the good, rich soil of their hearts, and patiently yield a return.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8216*No one sets light to a lamp and then covers it with a bowl or puts it underneath a couch, but they put it on a lamp-stand, so that anyone who comes in may see the light.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Nothing is hidden which will not be brought into the light of day, not ever kept hidden which will not some day become known and come into the light of day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Take care, then, how you listen. For, to all those who have, more will be given; while, from all those who have nothing, even what they seem to have will be taken away.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Presently Jesus\uc1\u8217* mother and brothers came where he was, but they were not able to join him because of the crowd.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}So word was brought to him \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Your mother and your brothers are standing outside, wanting to see you.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}His reply, spoken to them all, was, \uc1\u8216*My mother and my brothers are those who listen to God\uc1\u8217*s teaching and do what it says.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}One day about that time, Jesus got into a boat with his disciples and said to them, \uc1\u8216*Let us go across the lake.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}So they put off. While they were sailing, Jesus fell asleep. A squall swept down on the lake, and their boat was filling and they were in danger.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}So the disciples came and roused him. \uc1\u8216*Sir, Sir,\uc1\u8217* they cried, \uc1\u8216*we are lost!\uc1\u8217* Jesus rose and rebuked the wind and the rushing waves, and they fell, and a calm followed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}\uc1\u8216*Where is your faith?\uc1\u8217* he exclaimed. But in great awe and amazement they said to one another, \uc1\u8216*Who can this be, who commands even the winds and the waves, and they obey him?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}They reached the region of the Gerasenes, which is on the opposite side to Galilee,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}and, on getting ashore, Jesus met a man, who had demons in him, coming out of the town. For a long time this man had worn no clothing, and he had not lived in a house, but in the tombs.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Catching sight of Jesus, he shrieked out and threw himself down before him, and in a loud voice exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*What do you want with me, Jesus, Son of the Most High God? I beg you not to torment me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}For Jesus was commanding the foul spirit to come out of the man. On many occasions it had seized him, and, even when secured with chains and fetters, and watched, he would break through anything that bound him, and be driven by the demon into the wilds.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}\uc1\u8216*What is your name?\uc1\u8217* Jesus asked.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*Legion,\uc1\u8217* he answered (for many demons had taken possession of him);{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}and the demons begged Jesus not to order them away into the bottomless pit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}There was a herd of many pigs close by feeding on the hill-side; and the demons begged Jesus to give them leave to enter into them. Jesus gave them leave.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}They came out from the man and took possession of the pigs; and the herd rushed down the steep slope into the lake and were drowned.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}When the men who tended them saw what had happened, they ran away, and carried the news to the town, and to the country round.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}The people went out to see what had happened, and, when they came to Jesus, they found the man from whom the demons had gone out, sitting, clothed and in his right mind, at Jesus\uc1\u8217* feet; and they were awe-struck.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Those who had seen it told them how the possessed man had been delivered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Then all the people in the region of the Gerasenes asked Jesus to leave them, for they were terrified. Jesus got into a boat and returned.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}The man from whom the demons had gone out begged Jesus to let him be with him; but Jesus sent him away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}\uc1\u8216*Go back to your home,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*and relate the story of all that God has done for you.\uc1\u8217* So the man went through the whole town and proclaimed, as he went, all that Jesus had done for him.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}On his return, Jesus was welcomed by the people; for everyone was looking out for him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}And a man named Jairus, who was a synagogue leader, came to Jesus, and threw himself at Jesus\uc1\u8217* feet, with entreaties that he would come to his house,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}because his only daughter, who was about twelve years old, was dying. As Jesus was going, the people were pressing closely round him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}And a woman, who had suffered from haemorrhage for twelve years, and whom no one could cure,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}came up behind and touched the tassel of his cloak. Instantly the haemorrhage ceased.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}\uc1\u8216*Who touched me?\uc1\u8217* Jesus asked; and, while everyone was denying having done so, Peter exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*Why, Sir, the people are crowding round you and pressing against you!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}\uc1\u8216*Somebody touched me,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus, \uc1\u8216*for I felt that power had gone out from me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}Then the woman, when she saw that she was discovered, came forward trembling, and threw herself down before him; and, in the presence of all the people, she told him her reason for touching him, and that she had been cured instantly.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}\uc1\u8216*Daughter,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*your faith has delivered you. Go, and peace be with you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}Before he had finished speaking, someone came from the house of the synagogue leader and said, \uc1\u8216*Your daughter is dead! Do not trouble the teacher further.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}But Jesus, hearing this, spoke to the leader, \uc1\u8216*Do not be afraid; only have faith, and she will yet be delivered.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}When he reached the house, he did not allow anyone to go in with him, except Peter, John, and James, and the child\uc1\u8217*s father and mother.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}And everyone was weeping and mourning for her.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*Do not weep,\uc1\u8217* Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*she is not dead; she is asleep.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}They began to laugh at him, for they knew that she was dead.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}But, taking her by the hand, Jesus said in a loud voice, \uc1\u8216*Child, rise!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}The child\uc1\u8217*s spirit returned to her, and she instantly stood up; and Jesus ordered them to give her something to eat.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}Her parents were amazed, but Jesus impressed on them that they were not to tell anyone what had happened.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 9}Jesus called the Twelve together, and gave them power and authority over all demons, as well as to cure diseases.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}He sent them out as his messengers, to proclaim the kingdom of God, and to work cures.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8216*Do not,\uc1\u8217* he said to them, \uc1\u8216*take anything for your journey; not even a staff, or a bag, or bread, or any silver, or a change of clothes with you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Whatever house you go to stay in, remain there, and leave from that place.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}If people do not welcome you, as you leave that town, shake even the dust off your feet, as a protest against them.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Then they set out and went from village to village, telling the good news and curing people everywhere.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Herod the ruler heard of all that was happening, and was perplexed, because it was said by some that John must be risen from the dead.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Some again said that Elijah had appeared, and others that one of the old prophets had risen again.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But Herod himself said, \uc1\u8216*John I beheaded; but who is this of whom I hear such things?\uc1\u8217* And he endeavoured to see him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}When the apostles returned, they related to Jesus all that they had done. Then Jesus went privately to a town called Bethsaida, taking the apostles with him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But the people recognised him and followed him in crowds; and Jesus welcomed them and spoke to them about the kingdom of God, while he cured those who were in need of help.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The day was drawing to a close, when the twelve came up to him, and said, \uc1\u8216*Send the crowd away, so that they may make their way to the villages and farms round about, and find themselves lodgings and provisions, for we are in a lonely spot here.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*It is for you to give them something to eat.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*We have not more than five loaves and two fish,\uc1\u8217* they answered. \uc1\u8216*Unless indeed we are to go and buy food for all these people.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}(For the men among them were about five thousand.) \uc1\u8216*Get them seated in companies,\uc1\u8217* was his reply, \uc1\u8216*about fifty in each.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}This they did, and got all the people seated.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Taking the five loaves and the two fish, Jesus looked up to heaven and said the blessing over them. Then he broke them in pieces, and gave them to his disciples to set before the people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Everyone had sufficient to eat, and what was left of the broken pieces was picked up \uc1\u8211* twelve baskets.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Afterwards, when Jesus was alone, praying, his disciples joined him, and he asked them this question \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Who do the people say that I am?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}\uc1\u8216*John the Baptist,\uc1\u8217* was their answer. \uc1\u8216*Others, however, say that you are Elijah, while others say that one of the old prophets has risen again.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}\uc1\u8216*But you,\uc1\u8217* he went on, \uc1\u8216*who do you say that I am?\uc1\u8217* And to this Peter answered, \uc1\u8216*The Christ of God.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Jesus, however, strictly charged them not to say this to anyone;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}he told them that the Son of Man must undergo much suffering, and be rejected by the elders, and chief priests, and teachers of the Law, and be put to death, and rise on the third day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And to all present he said, \uc1\u8216*If any one wishes to walk in my steps, they must renounce self, and take up their cross daily, and follow me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}For whoever wishes to save their life will lose it, and whoever, for my sake, loses his life \uc1\u8211* that person will save it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}What good does it do someone if, when they has gained the whole world, they has lost or forfeited themselves?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Whoever is ashamed of me and of my teaching, the Son of Man will be ashamed of them, when he comes in his glory and the glory of the father and of the holy angels.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Indeed, I tell you, some who are standing before me will not know death, until they have seen the kingdom of God.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}About eight days after speaking these words, Jesus went up the mountain to pray, taking with him Peter, John, and James.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}As he was praying, the aspect of his face was changed, and his clothing became a dazzling white.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}And all at once two men were talking with Jesus; they were Moses and Elijah,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}who appeared in a glorified state, and spoke of his departure, which was destined to take place at Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Peter and his companions had been overpowered by sleep but, suddenly becoming wide awake, they saw Jesus glorified and the two men who were standing beside him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}And, as Moses and Elijah were passing away from Jesus, Peter exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*Sir, it is good to be here; let us make three tents, one for you, and one for Moses, and one for Elijah.\uc1\u8217* He did not know what he was saying;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}and, while he was speaking, a cloud came down and enveloped them; and they were afraid, as they passed into the cloud;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}and from the cloud came a voice which said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*This is my Son, the Chosen One; him you must hear.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}And, as the voice ceased, Jesus was found alone. The apostles kept silence, and told no one about any of the things that they had seen.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}The next day, when they had come down from the mountain, a great crowd met Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}And just then a man in the crowd shouted out, \uc1\u8216*Teacher, I entreat you to look at my son, for he is my only child;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}all at once a spirit will seize him, suddenly shriek out, and throw him into convulsions until he foams, and will leave him only when he is utterly exhausted.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}I entreated your disciples to drive the spirit out, but they could not.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}\uc1\u8216*Faithless and perverse generation!\uc1\u8217* Jesus exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*How long must I be with you and have patience with you? Lead your son here.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}While the boy was coming up to Jesus, the demon dashed him down and threw him into convulsions. But Jesus rebuked the foul spirit, and cured the boy, and gave him back to his father.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}And all present were struck with awe at the majesty of God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
In the midst of the general astonishment at all that Jesus was doing, he said to his disciples,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}\uc1\u8216*Listen carefully to my words. For the Son of Man is destined to be betrayed into the hands of his fellow men.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}But the disciples did not understand the meaning of this; it had been concealed from them so that they did not see it, and they were afraid to question him as to what he meant.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}A discussion arose among the disciples as to which of them was the greatest;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}and Jesus, knowing of the discussion that was occupying their thoughts, took hold of a little child, and placed it beside him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}and then said to them, \uc1\u8216*Anyone who, for the sake of my name, welcomes even this little child is welcoming me; and anyone who welcomes me is welcoming him who sent me as his messenger. For whoever is least among you all \uc1\u8211* that person is great.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}John said, \uc1\u8216*Sir, we saw a man driving out demons by using your name, and we tried to prevent him, because he does not follow you with us.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}\uc1\u8216*None of you must prevent him,\uc1\u8217* Jesus said to John, \uc1\u8216*whoever is not against you is for you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Journey to Jerusalem

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}As the days before his being taken up to heaven were growing few, Jesus set his face resolutely in the direction of Jerusalem; and he sent on messengers in advance.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}On their way, they went into a Samaritan village to make preparations for him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}but the people there did not welcome him, because his face was set in the direction of Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}When James and John saw this, they said, \uc1\u8216*Master, do you wish us to call for fire to come down from the heavens and consume them?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}But Jesus turned and rebuked them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}And they made their way to another village.
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 57}And, while they were on their way, a man said to Jesus, \uc1\u8216*I will follow you wherever you go.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 58}\uc1\u8216*Foxes have holes,\uc1\u8217* he replied, \uc1\u8216*and wild birds their nests, but the Son of Man has nowhere to lay his head.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 59}To another man Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Follow me.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*Let me first go and bury my father,\uc1\u8217* said the man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 60}But Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Leave the dead to bury their dead; but go yourself and carry far and wide the news of the kingdom of God.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 61}\uc1\u8216*Master,\uc1\u8217* said another, \uc1\u8216*I will follow you; but first let me say goodbye to my family.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 62}But Jesus answered, \uc1\u8216*No one who looks back, after putting their hand to the plough, is fitted for the kingdom of God.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 10}After this, the Master appointed seventy-two other disciples, and sent them on as his messengers, two and two, in advance, to every town and place that he was himself intending to visit.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8216*The harvest,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*is abundant, but the labourers are few. Therefore pray to the owner of the harvest to send labourers to gather in his harvest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Now, go. Remember, I am sending you out as my messengers like lambs among wolves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Do not take a purse with you, or a bag, or sandals; and do not stop to greet anyone on your journey.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Whatever house you go to stay at, begin by praying for a blessing on it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Then, if anyone there is deserving of a blessing, your blessing will rest on him; but if not, it will come back on yourselves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Remain at that same house, and eat and drink whatever they offer you; for the worker is worth their wages. Do not keep changing from one house to another.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Whatever town you visit, if the people welcome you, eat what is set before you;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}cure the sick there, and tell people that the kingdom of God is close at hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}But, whatever town you go to visit, if the people do not welcome you, go out into its streets and say{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8220*We wipe off the dust of your town which has clung to Our feet; still, be assured that the kingdom of God is close at Hand.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I tell you that the doom of Sodom will be more bearable on that day than the doom of that town.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Alas for you, Chorazin! Alas for you, Bethsaida! For, if the miracles which have been done in you had been done in Tyre and Sidon, they would have sat in sackcloth and ashes and repented long ago.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Yet the doom of Tyre and Sidon will be more bearable at the judgment than yours.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And you, Capernaum! Will you exalt yourself to heaven? You will be flung down to Hades.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Anyone who listens to you is listening to me, and anyone who rejects you is rejecting me; while the person who rejects me is rejecting him who sent me as his messenger.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}When the seventy-two returned, they exclaimed joyfully, \uc1\u8216*Master, even the demons submit to us when we use your name.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And Jesus replied, \uc1\u8216*I have had visions of Satan, fallen, like lightning from the heavens.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Remember, I have given you the power to trample on snakes and scorpions, and to meet all the strength of the Enemy. Nothing will ever harm you in any way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Yet do not rejoice in the fact that the spirits submit to you, but rejoice that your names have been enrolled in heaven.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}At that same time, moved to exultation by the Holy Spirit, Jesus said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*I thank you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that, though you have hidden these things from the wise and learned, you have revealed them to the childlike! Yes, Father, I thank you that this has seemed good to you.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 

\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Everything has been committed to me by my Father; nor does anyone know who the Son is, except the Father, or who the Father is, except the Son and those to whom the Son may choose to reveal him.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Then, turning to his disciples, Jesus said to them alone, \uc1\u8216*Blessed are the eyes that see what you are seeing;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}for, I tell you, many prophets and kings wished for the sight of the things which you are seeing, yet never heard them.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Just then a student of the Law came forward to test Jesus further. \uc1\u8216*Teacher,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*what must I do if I am to gain eternal life?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}\uc1\u8216*What is said in the Law?\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus. \uc1\u8216*What do you read there?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}His reply was \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*You must love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your strength, and with all your mind; and your neighbour as you love yourself.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}\uc1\u8216*You have answered right,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus, \uc1\u8216*Do that, and you will live.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}But the man, wanting to justify himself, said to Jesus, \uc1\u8216*And who is my neighbour?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}To which Jesus replied, \uc1\u8216*A man was once going down from Jerusalem to Jericho when he fell into the hands of robbers, who stripped him of everything, and beat him, and went away leaving him half dead.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}As it chanced, a priest was going down by that road. He saw the man, but passed by on the opposite side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}A Levite, too, did the same; he came up to the spot, but, when he saw the man, passed by on the opposite side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}But a Samaritan, traveling that way, came upon the man, and, when he saw him, he was moved with compassion.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}He went to him and bound up his wounds, dressing them with oil and wine, and then put him on his own mule, and brought him to an inn, and took care of him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}The next day he took out two silver coins and gave them to the innkeeper. \uc1\u8220*Take care of him,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*and whatever more you may spend I will myself repay you on my way back.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Now which, do you think, of these three men,\uc1\u8217* asked Jesus, \uc1\u8216*proved himself a neighbour to the man who fell into the robbers\uc1\u8217* hands?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}\uc1\u8216*The one that took pity on him,\uc1\u8217* was the answer; at which Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Go and do the same yourself.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}As they continued their journey, Jesus came to a village, where a woman named Martha welcomed him to her house.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}She had a sister called Mary, who seated herself at the Master\uc1\u8217*s feet, and listened to his teaching;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}but Martha was distracted by the many preparations that she was making. So she went up to Jesus and said, \uc1\u8216*Master, do you approve of my sister\uc1\u8217*s leaving me to make preparations alone? Tell her to help me.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}\uc1\u8216*Martha, Martha,\uc1\u8217* replied the Master, \uc1\u8216*you are anxious and trouble yourself about many things;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}but only a few are necessary, or rather one. Mary has chosen the good part, and it will not be taken away from her.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 11}One day Jesus was at a certain place praying, and, when he had finished, one of his disciples said to him, \uc1\u8216*Master, teach us to pray, as John taught his disciples.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8216*When you pray,\uc1\u8217* Jesus answered, \uc1\u8216*say \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
