and take us not into temptation.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Jesus also said to them, \uc1\u8216*Suppose that one of you who has a friend were to go to him in the middle of the night and say \uc1\u8220*Friend, lend me three loaves,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}for a friend of mine has arrived at my house after a journey, and I have nothing to offer him;\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And suppose that the other should answer from inside \uc1\u8220*Do not trouble me; the door is already fastened, and my children and I are in bed; I cannot get up and give you anything\uc1\u8221*;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I tell you that, even though he will not get up and give him anything because he is a friend, yet because of his persistence he will rouse himself and give him what he wants.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}\uc1\u8216*And so I say to you \uc1\u8211* Ask, and your prayer will be granted, search, and you will find; knock, and the door will be opened to you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For the person who asks receives, everyone who searches finds, and to the person who knocks the door will be opened.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}What father among you, if his son asks him for a fish, will give him a snake instead,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}or, if he asks for an egg, will give him a scorpion?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}If you, then, naturally wicked though you are, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will the Father in heaven give the Holy Spirit to those who ask him!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Once Jesus was driving out a mute demon, and, when the demon had gone out, the mute man spoke. The people were amazed at this;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}but some of them said, \uc1\u8216*He drives out demons by the help of Beelzebul, the chief of the demons\uc1\u8217*;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}while others, to test him, asked him for some sign from the heavens.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Jesus himself, however, was aware of what they were thinking, and said to them, \uc1\u8216*Any kingdom wholly divided against itself becomes a desolation; and a divided house falls.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}So, too, if Satan is wholly divided against himself, how can his kingdom last? Yet you say that I drive out demons by the help of Beelzebul.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}But, if it is by Beelzebul\uc1\u8217*s help that I drive out demons, by whose help is it that your own sons drive them out? Therefore they will themselves be your judges.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But, if it is by the hand of God that I drive out demons, then the kingdom of God must already be upon you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}When a strong man is keeping guard, fully armed, over his own mansion, his property is in safety;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}but, when one still stronger has attacked and overpowered him, he takes away all the weapons on which the other had relied, and divides his spoil.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Whoever is not with me is against me, and the person who does not help me to gather is scattering.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}No sooner does a foul spirit leave someone, than it passes through places where there is no water, in search of rest; and finding none, it says \uc1\u8220*I will go back to the home which I left\uc1\u8221*;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}but, on coming there, it finds it unoccupied, swept, and put in order.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Then it goes and brings with it seven other spirits more wicked than itself, and they go in, and make their home there; and the last state of that person proves to be worse than the first.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}As Jesus was saying this, a woman in the crowd, raising her voice, exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*Happy was the mother who bore you and nursed you!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}But Jesus replied, \uc1\u8216*Rather, happy are those who listen to God\uc1\u8217*s message and keep it.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}As the crowds increased, Jesus began to speak, \uc1\u8216*This generation is a wicked generation. It is asking a sign, but no sign will be given it except the sign of Jonah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}For, as Jonah became a sign to the people of Nineveh, so will the Son of Man be to this generation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}At the judgment the Queen of the South will rise up with the people of this generation, and will condemn them, because she came from the ends of the earth to listen to the wisdom of Solomon; and here is more than a Solomon!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}At the judgment the men of Nineveh will stand up with this generation, and will condemn it, because they repented at Jonah\uc1\u8217*s proclamation; and here is more than a Jonah!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}No one lights a lamp, and then puts it in the cellar or under a basket, but he puts it on the lamp-stand, so that anyone who comes in may see the light.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}The lamp of the body is your eye. When your eye is unclouded, your whole body, also, is lit up; but, as soon as your eye is diseased, your body, also, is darkened.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Take care, therefore, that the inner light is not darkness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}If, then, your whole body is lit up, and no corner of it darkened, the whole will be lit up, just as when a lamp gives you light by its brilliance.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}As Jesus finished speaking, a Pharisee asked him to breakfast with him, and Jesus went in and took his place at the table.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}The Pharisee noticed, to his astonishment, that Jesus omitted the ceremonial washing before breakfast.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}But the Master said to him, \uc1\u8216*You Pharisees do, it is true, clean the outside of the cup and of the plate, but inside you yourselves are filled with greed and wickedness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}Fools! Did not the maker of the outside make the inside too?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}Only give away what is in them in charity, and at once you have the whole clean.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}But alas for you Pharisees! You pay tithes on mint, rue, and herbs of all kinds, and pass over justice and love to God. These last you ought to have put into practice without neglecting the first.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}Alas for you Pharisees! You delight to have the front seat in the synagogues, and to be greeted in the markets with respect.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}Alas for you! You are like unsuspected graves, over which men walk unawares.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}Here one of the students of the Law interrupted him by saying, \uc1\u8216*Teacher, when you say this, you are insulting us also.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}But Jesus went on, \uc1\u8216*Alas for you, too, you students of the Law! You load people with loads that are too heavy to carry, but do not, yourselves, touch them with one of your fingers.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}Alas for you! You build the monuments of the prophets whom your ancestors killed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}You are actually witnesses to your ancestors\uc1\u8217* acts and show your approval of them, because, while they killed the prophets, you build tombs for them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}That is why the wisdom of God said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*I will send to them prophets and apostles,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}some of whom they will persecute and kill, in order that the blood of all the prophets that has been spilt since the creation of the world may be exacted from this generation \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}from the blood of Abel down to the blood of Zechariah, who was slain between the altar and the house of God.\uc1\u8221* Yes, I tell you, it will be exacted from this generation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}Alas for you students of the Law! You have taken away the key of the door of knowledge. You have not gone in yourselves and you have hindered those who try to go in.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}When Jesus left the house, the teachers of the Law and the Pharisees began to press him hard and question him closely on many subjects,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}laying traps for him, so as to seize on anything that he might say.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 12}Meanwhile the people had gathered in thousands, so that they trod on one another, when Jesus, addressing himself to his disciples, began by saying to them, \uc1\u8216*Be on your guard against the leaven \uc1\u8211* that is, the hypocrisy \uc1\u8211* of the Pharisees.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}There is nothing, however covered up, which will not be uncovered, nor anything kept secret which will not become known.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So all that you have said in the dark will be heard in the light, and what you have spoken in the ear, within closed doors, will be proclaimed on the housetops.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}To you who are my friends I say, Do not be afraid of those who kill the body, but after that can do no more.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}I will show you of whom you should be afraid. Be afraid of him who, after killing you, has the power to fling you into Gehenna. Yes, I say, be afraid of him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Are not five sparrows sold for two copper coins? Yet not one of them has escaped God\uc1\u8217*s notice.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}No, even the hairs of your head are all numbered. Do not be afraid; you are of more value than many sparrows.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Everyone, I tell you, who publicly acknowledges me, the Son of Man, also, will acknowledge before God\uc1\u8217*s angels;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}but the person who publicly disowns me will be altogether disowned before God\uc1\u8217*s angels.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Everyone who will say anything against the Son of Man will be forgiven, but for the person who slanders the Holy Spirit there will be no forgiveness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Whenever they take you before the synagogue Courts or the magistrates or other authorities, do not be anxious as to how you will defend yourselves, or what your defence will be, or what you will say;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}for the Holy Spirit will show you at the moment what you ought to say.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8216*Teacher,\uc1\u8217* a man in the crowd said to Jesus, \uc1\u8216*tell my brother to share the property with me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But Jesus said to him, \uc1\u8216*Man, who made me a judge or an arbiter between you?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And then he added, \uc1\u8216*Take care to keep yourselves free from every form of covetousness; for even in the height of their prosperity a person\uc1\u8217*s true life does not depend on what they have.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Then Jesus told them this parable \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*There was once a rich man whose land was very fertile;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and he began to ask himself \uc1\u8220*What will I do, for I have nowhere to store my crops?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}This is what I will do,\uc1\u8221* he said; \uc1\u8220*I will pull down my barns and build larger ones, and store all my grain and my goods in them;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and I will say to myself, Now you have plenty of good things put by for many years; take your ease, eat, drink, and enjoy yourself.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But God said to the man \uc1\u8220*Fool! This very night your life is being demanded; and as for all you have prepared \uc1\u8211* who will have it?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}So it is with those who lay by wealth for themselves and are not rich to the glory of God.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And Jesus said to his disciples, \uc1\u8216*That is why I say to you, Do not be anxious about the life here \uc1\u8211* what you can get to eat; or about your body \uc1\u8211* what you can get to wear.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}For life is more than food, and the body than its clothes.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Think of the ravens \uc1\u8211* they neither sow nor reap; they have neither storehouse nor barn; and yet God feeds them! And how much more precious are you than birds!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}But which of you, by being anxious, can prolong your life a moment?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}And, if you cannot do even the smallest thing, why be anxious about other things?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Think of the lilies, and how they grow. They neither toil nor spin; yet, I tell you, even Solomon in all his splendour was not robed like one of these.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}If, even in the field, God so clothes the grass which is living today and tomorrow will be thrown into the oven, how much more will he clothe you, you of little faith!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}And you \uc1\u8211* do not be always seeking what you can get to eat or what you can get to drink; and do not waver.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}These are the things for which all the nations of the world are seeking, and your Father knows that you need them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}No, seek his kingdom, and these things will be added for you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}So do not be afraid, my little flock, for your Father has been pleased to give you the kingdom.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}\uc1\u8216*Sell what belongs to you, and give in charity. Make yourselves purses that will not wear out \uc1\u8211* an inexhaustible treasure in heaven, where no thief comes near, or moth works ruin.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}For where your treasure is, there also will your heart be.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Make yourselves ready, with your lamps alight;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}and be like servants who are waiting for their Master\uc1\u8217*s return from his wedding, so that, when he comes and knocks, they may open the door for him at once.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Happy are those servants whom, on his return, the Master will find watching. I tell you that he will make himself ready, and have them take their places at the table, and will come and serve them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}Whether it is late at night, or in the early morning that he comes, if he finds all as it should be, then happy are they.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}This you do know, that, had the owner of the house known at what time the thief was coming, he would have been on the watch, and would not have let his house be broken into.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}You must also prepare, for when you are least expecting him the Son of Man will come.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}\uc1\u8216*Master,\uc1\u8217* said Peter, \uc1\u8216*are you telling this parable with reference to us or to everyone?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}\uc1\u8216*Who, then,\uc1\u8217* replied the Master, \uc1\u8216*is that trustworthy steward, the careful man, who will be placed by his master over his establishment, to give them their rations at the proper time?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}Happy will that servant be whom his master, when he comes home, will find doing this.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}His master, I tell you, will put him in charge of the whole of his property.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}But should that servant say to himself \uc1\u8220*My master is a long time coming,\uc1\u8221* and begin to beat the menservants and the maidservants, and to eat and drink and get drunk,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}that servant\uc1\u8217*s master will come on a day when he does not expect him, and at an hour of which he is unaware, and will flog him severely and assign him his place among the untrustworthy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}The servant who knows his master\uc1\u8217*s wishes and yet does not prepare and act accordingly will receive many lashes;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}while one who does not know his master\uc1\u8217*s wishes, but acts so as to deserve a flogging, will receive but few. From everyone to whom much has been given much will be expected, and from the man to whom much has been entrusted the more will be demanded.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}I came to cast fire on the earth; and what more can I wish, if it is already kindled?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}There is a baptism that I must undergo, and how great is my distress until it is over!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}Do you think that I am here to bring peace on earth? No, I tell you, but to cause division.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}For from this time, if there are five people in a house, they will be divided, three against two, and two against three.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}Father will be opposed to son and son to father, mother to daughter and daughter to mother, mother-in-law to her daughter-in-law and daughter-in-law to her mother-in-law.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}And to the people Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*When you see a cloud rising in the west, you say at once \uc1\u8220*There is a storm coming,\uc1\u8221* and come it does.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}And when you see that the wind is in the south, you say \uc1\u8220*It will be burning hot,\uc1\u8221* and so it proves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}Hypocrites! You know how to judge of the earth and the sky; how is it, then, that you cannot judge of this time?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 57}Why don\uc1\u8217*t you yourselves decide what is right?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 58}When, for instance, you are going with your opponent before a magistrate, on your way to the court do your best to be quit of him; otherwise he might drag you before the judge, then the judge will hand you over to the bailiff of the court, and the bailiff throw you into prison.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 59}You will not, I tell you, come out until you have paid the very last cent.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 13}Just at that time some people had come to tell Jesus about the Galileans, whose blood Pilate had mingled with the blood of their sacrifices.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8216*Do you suppose,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*that, because these Galileans have suffered in this way, they were worse sinners than any other Galileans?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}No, I tell you; but, unless you repent, you will all perish as they did.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Or those eighteen men at Siloam on whom the tower fell, killing them all, do you suppose that they were worse offenders than any other inhabitants of Jerusalem?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}No, I tell you; but, unless you repent, you will all perish in the same manner.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And Jesus told them this parable \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*A man, who had a fig tree growing in his vineyard, came to look for fruit on it, but could not find any.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}So he said to his gardener \uc1\u8220*Three years now I have come to look for fruit on this fig tree, without finding any! Cut it down. Why should it rob the soil?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8220*Leave it this one year more, Sir,\uc1\u8221* the man answered, \uc1\u8220*until I have dug round it and manured it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then, if it bears in future, well and good; but if not, you can have it cut down.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Jesus was teaching on a Sabbath in one of the synagogues,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}and he saw before him a woman who for eighteen years had suffered from weakness owing to her having an evil spirit in her. She was bent double, and was wholly unable to raise herself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}When Jesus saw her, he called her to him, and said, \uc1\u8216*Woman, you are released from your weakness.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}He placed his hands on her, and she was instantly made straight, and began to praise God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But the synagogue leader, indignant that Jesus had worked the cure on the Sabbath, intervened and said to the people, \uc1\u8216*There are six days on which work ought to be done; come to be cured on one of those, and not on the Sabbath.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8216*You hypocrites!\uc1\u8217* the Master answered him. \uc1\u8216*Does not everyone of you let your ox or your ass loose from its manger, and take it out to drink, on the Sabbath?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}But this woman, a daughter of Abraham, who has been kept in bondage by Satan for now eighteen years, ought not she to have been released from her bondage on the Sabbath?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}As he said this, his opponents all felt ashamed; but all the people rejoiced to see all the wonderful things that he was doing.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}So Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*What is the kingdom of God like? And to what can I liken it?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}It is like a mustard seed which a man took and put in his garden. The seed grew and became a tree, and the wild birds roosted in its branches.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And again Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*To what can I liken the kingdom of God?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}It is like some yeast which a woman took and covered in three pecks of flour, until the whole had risen.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Jesus went through towns and villages, teaching as he went, and making his way towards Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8216*Master,\uc1\u8217* someone asked, \uc1\u8216*are there but few in the path of salvation?\uc1\u8217* And Jesus answered,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}\uc1\u8216*Strive to go in by the narrow door. Many, I tell you, will seek to go in, but they will not be able,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}when once the master of the house has got up and shut the door, while you begin to say, as you stand outside and knock, \uc1\u8220*Sir, open the door for us.\uc1\u8221* His answer will be \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*I do not know where you come from.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Then you will begin to say \uc1\u8220*We have eaten and drunk in your presence, and you have taught in our streets,\uc1\u8221* and his reply will be \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}\uc1\u8220*I do not know where you come from. Leave my presence, all you who are living in wickedness.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}There, there will be weeping and grinding of teeth, when you see Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and all the prophets, in the kingdom of God, while you yourselves are being driven outside.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}People will come from East and West, and from North and South, and take their places at the banquet in the kingdom of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}There are some who are last now who will then be first, and some who are first now who will then be last!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Just then some Pharisees came up to Jesus and said, \uc1\u8216*Go away and leave this place, for Herod wants to kill you.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}But Jesus answered, \uc1\u8216*Go and say to that fox \uc1\u8220*Look you, I am driving out demons and will be completing cures today and tomorrow, and on the third day I will have done.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}But today and tomorrow and the day after I must go on my way, because it cannot be that a prophet should meet his end outside Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Jerusalem! Jerusalem! You who slays the prophets and stones the messengers sent to you \uc1\u8211* Oh, how often have I wished to gather your children round me, as a hen takes her brood under her wings, and you would not come!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Verily your house is left to you desolate! And never, I tell you, will you see me, until you say \uc1\u8211*
\par}

