{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}On the way to Jerusalem Jesus passed between Samaria and Galilee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}As he was entering a village, ten lepers met him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Standing still, some distance off, they called out loudly, \uc1\u8216*Jesus! Sir! Pity us!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}When Jesus saw them, he said, \uc1\u8216*Go and show yourselves to the priest.\uc1\u8217* And, as they were on their way, they were made clean.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}One of them, finding he was cured, came back, praising God loudly,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}and threw himself on his face at Jesus\uc1\u8217* feet, thanking him for what he had done; and this man was a Samaritan.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8216*Were not all the ten made clean? exclaimed Jesus. But the nine \uc1\u8211* where are they?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Were there none to come back and praise God except this foreigner?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Get up,\uc1\u8217* he said to him, \uc1\u8216*and go on your way. Your faith has delivered you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

