{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Being once asked by the Pharisees when the kingdom of God was to come, Jesus answered, \uc1\u8216*The kingdom of God does not come in a way that can be seen,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}nor will people say \uc1\u8220*Look, here it is!\uc1\u8221* or \uc1\u8220*There it is!\uc1\u8221*; for the kingdom of God is within you!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}The day will come,\uc1\u8217* he said to his disciples, \uc1\u8216*when you will long to see but one of the days of the Son of Man, and will not see it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}People will say to you \uc1\u8220*There he is!\uc1\u8221* Or \uc1\u8220*Here he is!\uc1\u8221* Do not go and follow them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}For, just as lightning will lighten and flare from one side of the heavens to the other, so will it be with the Son of Man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}But first he must undergo much suffering, and he must be rejected by the present generation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}As it was in the days of Noah, so will it be again in the days of the Son of Man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}They were eating and drinking and marrying and being married, up to the very day on which Noah entered the ark, and then the flood came and destroyed them all.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}So, too, in the days of Lot. People were eating, drinking, buying, selling, planting, building;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}but, on the very day on which Lot came out of Sodom, it rained fire and sulphur from the skies and destroyed them all.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}It will be the same on the day on which the Son of Man reveals himself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}On that day, if a person is on their house-top and their goods in the house, they must not go down to get them; nor again must one who is on the farm turn back.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Remember Lot\uc1\u8217*s wife.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Whoever is eager to get the most out of their life will lose it; but whoever will lose it will preserve it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}On that night, I tell you, of two people on the same bed, one will be taken and the other left;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}of two women grinding grain together, one will be taken and the other left.\uc1\u8217*{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}  Some later manuscripts add: There will be two in the field; one will be taken and the other left. }
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}\uc1\u8216*Where will it be, Master?\uc1\u8217* asked the disciples. \uc1\u8216*Where there is a body,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus, \uc1\u8216*there will the vultures flock.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

