{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 18}Jesus told his disciples a parable to show them that they should always pray and never despair.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8216*There was,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*in a certain town a judge, who had no fear of God nor regard for people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}In the same town there was a widow who went to him again and again, and said \uc1\u8220*Grant me justice against my opponent.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For a time the judge refused, but afterwards he said to himself \uc1\u8220*Although I am without fear of God or regard for people,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}yet, as this widow is so troublesome, I will grant her justice, to stop her from plaguing me with her endless visits.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Then the Master added, \uc1\u8216*Listen to what this iniquitous judge says!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And God \uc1\u8211* won\uc1\u8217*t he see that his own people, who cry to him night and day, have justice done them \uc1\u8211* though he holds his hand?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}He will, I tell you, give them justice soon enough! Yet, when the Son of Man comes, will he find faith on earth?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Another time, speaking to people who were satisfied that they were religious, and who regarded everyone else with scorn, Jesus told this parable \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8216*Two men went up into the Temple Courts to pray. One was a Pharisee and the other a tax-gatherer.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The Pharisee stood forward and began praying to himself in this way \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*God, I thank you that I am not like other men \uc1\u8211* thieves, rogues, adulterers \uc1\u8211* or even like this tax-gatherer.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I fast twice a week, and give a tenth of everything I get to God.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Meanwhile the tax-gatherer stood at a distance, not venturing even to raise his eyes to heaven, but he kept striking his breast and saying \uc1\u8220*God, have mercy on me, a sinner.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}This man, I tell you, went home pardoned, rather than the other. For everyone who exalts himself will be humbled, while everyone who humbles himself will be exalted.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Some of the people were bringing even their babies to Jesus, for him to touch them; but, when the disciples saw it, they began to find fault with those who had brought them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Jesus, however, called the little children to him. \uc1\u8216*Let the little children come to me,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*and do not hinder them, for it is to the childlike that the kingdom of God belongs.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}I tell you, unless a man receives the kingdom of God like a child, he will not enter it at all.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And one of the leaders asked Jesus this question \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Good teacher, what must I do if I am to gain eternal life?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}\uc1\u8216*Why do you call me good?\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus. \uc1\u8216*No one is good but God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}You know the commandments \uc1\u8211* Do not commit adultery, Do not kill, Do not steal, Do not say what is false about others, Honour your father and your mother.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8216*I have observed all these,\uc1\u8217* he replied, \uc1\u8216*from childhood.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Hearing this, Jesus said to him, \uc1\u8216*There is one thing still lacking in you; sell everything that you have, and distribute to the poor, and you will have wealth in heaven; then come and follow me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}But the man became greatly distressed on hearing this, for he was extremely rich.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Seeing this, Jesus said to his disciples, \uc1\u8216*How hard it is for the wealthy to enter the kingdom of God!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}It is easier, indeed, for a camel to get through a needle\uc1\u8217*s eye than for a rich person to enter the kingdom of God!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}\uc1\u8216*Then who can be saved?\uc1\u8217* asked those who heard this.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}But Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*What is impossible with people is possible with God.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}\uc1\u8216*But we,\uc1\u8217* said Peter, \uc1\u8216*we left what belonged to us and followed you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}\uc1\u8216*I tell you,\uc1\u8217* he answered, \uc1\u8216*that there is no one who has left house, or wife, or brothers, or parents, or children, for the sake of the kingdom of God,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}who will not receive many times as much in the present, and in the age that is coming eternal life.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

