{\cf1\f1\fs22 19}Jesus entered Jericho and made his way through the town.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}There was a man there, known by the name of Zacchaeus, who was a senior tax collector and a rich man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}He tried to see what Jesus was like; but, being short, he was unable to do so because of the crowd.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}So he ran on ahead and climbed into a mulberry tree to see Jesus, for he knew that he must pass that way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}When Jesus came to the place, he looked up and said to him, \uc1\u8216*Zacchaeus, be quick and come down, for I must stop at your house today.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}So Zacchaeus got down quickly, and joyfully welcomed him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}On seeing this, everyone began to complain, \uc1\u8216*He has gone to stay with a man who is an outcast.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}But Zacchaeus stood forward and said to the Master, \uc1\u8216*Listen, Master! I will give half my property to the poor, and, if I have defrauded anyone of anything, I will give him back four times as much.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}\uc1\u8216*Salvation has come to this house today,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*for even this man is a son of Abraham.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}The Son of Man has come to search for those who are lost and to save them.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}As the people were listening to this, Jesus went on to tell them a parable. He did so because he was near Jerusalem, and because they thought that the kingdom of God was going to be proclaimed at once.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}He said, \uc1\u8216*A nobleman once went to a distant country to receive his appointment to a kingdom and then return.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}He called ten of his servants and gave them ten pounds of silver each, and told them to trade with them during his absence.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But his subjects hated him and sent envoys after him to say \uc1\u8220*We will not have this man as our king.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}On his return, after having been appointed king, he directed that the servants to whom he had given his money should be summoned, so that he might learn what amount of trade they had done.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}The first came up, and said \uc1\u8220*Sir, your ten pounds have made a hundred.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8220*Well done, good servant!\uc1\u8221* exclaimed the master. \uc1\u8220*As you have proved trustworthy in a very small matter, I appoint you governor over ten towns.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}When the second came, he said \uc1\u8220*Your ten pounds, Sir, have produced fifty.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}So the master said to him \uc1\u8220*And you I appoint over five towns.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Another servant also came and said \uc1\u8220*Sir, here are your ten pounds; I have kept them put away in a handkerchief.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}For I was afraid of you, because you are a stern man. You take what you have not planted, and reap what you have not sown.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}The master answered \uc1\u8220*Out of your own mouth I judge you, you worthless servant. You knew that I am a stern man, that I take what I have not planted, and reap what I have not sown?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Then why didn\uc1\u8217*t you put my money into a bank? And I, on my return, could have claimed it with interest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Take away from him the ten pounds,\uc1\u8221* he said to those standing by, \uc1\u8220*and give them to the one who has the hundred.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}\uc1\u8220*But, Sir,\uc1\u8221* they said, \uc1\u8220*he has a hundred pounds already!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}\uc1\u8220*I tell you,\uc1\u8221* he answered, \uc1\u8220*that, to him who has, more will be given, but, from him who has nothing, even what he has will be taken away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}But as for my enemies, these men who would not have me as their king, bring them here and put them to death in my presence.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}After saying this, Jesus went on in front, going up to Jerusalem.
