{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}It was when Jesus had almost reached Bethphage and Bethany, near the Mount of Olives, that he sent on two of the disciples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}\uc1\u8216*Go to the village facing us,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*and, when you get there, you will find a foal tethered, which no one has yet ridden; untie it and lead it here.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}And, if anybody asks you \uc1\u8220*Why are you untying it?\uc1\u8221*, you are to say this \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*The Master wants it.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}So the two who were sent went and found it as Jesus had told them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}While they were untying the foal, the owners asked them \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Why are you untying the foal?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}And the two disciples answered \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*The Master wants it.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Then they led it back to Jesus, and threw their cloaks on the foal and put Jesus on it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}As he went along, the people kept spreading their cloaks in the road.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}When he had almost reached the place where the road led down the Mount of Olives, everyone of the many disciples began in their joy to praise God loudly for all the miracles that they had seen:
