{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8216*I, too,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus in reply, \uc1\u8216*will ask you one question. Give me an answer to it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}It is about John\uc1\u8217*s baptism \uc1\u8211* was it of divine or of human origin?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}But they began arguing together, \uc1\u8216*If we say \uc1\u8220*divine,\uc1\u8221* he will say \uc1\u8220*Why didn\uc1\u8217*t you believe him?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But, if we say \uc1\u8220*human,\uc1\u8221* the people will all stone us, for they are persuaded that John was a prophet.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}So they answered that they did not know its origin.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8216*Then I,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus, \uc1\u8216*refuse to tell you what authority I have to do these things.\uc1\u8217*
