{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But Jesus began to tell the people this parable \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*A man once planted a vineyard, and then let it out to tenants, and went abroad for a long while.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}At the proper time he sent a servant to the tenants, so that they could give him a share of the produce of the vineyard. The tenants, however, beat him and sent him away empty-handed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The owner afterwards sent another servant; but the tenants beat and insulted this man too, and sent him away empty-handed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}He sent a third; but they wounded this man also, and threw him outside.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8220*What should I do?\uc1\u8221* said the owner of the vineyard. \uc1\u8220*I will send my son, who is very dear to me. Perhaps they will respect him.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But, on seeing him, the tenants consulted with one another. \uc1\u8220*Here is the heir!\uc1\u8221* they said. \uc1\u8220*Let us kill him, and then the inheritance will become ours.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}So they threw him outside the vineyard and killed him. Now what will the owner of the vineyard do to them?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}He will come and put those tenants to death, and will let the vineyard to others.\uc1\u8217*
