{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}After this the teachers of the Law and the chief priest were eager to lay hands on Jesus then and there, but they were afraid of the people; for they saw that it was at them that he had aimed this parable.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Having watched their opportunity, they afterwards sent some spies, who pretended to be good men, to catch Jesus in the course of conversation, and so enable them to give him up to the Governor\uc1\u8217*s jurisdiction and authority.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}These spies asked Jesus a question. They said, \uc1\u8216*Teacher, we know that you are right in what you say and teach, and that you do not take any account of a person\uc1\u8217*s position, but teach the way of God honestly;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}are we right in paying tribute to the Emperor or not?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Seeing through their deceitfulness, Jesus said to them,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}\uc1\u8216*Show me a coin. Whose head and title are on it?\uc1\u8217*
