\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}While all the people were listening, Jesus said to the disciples,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}\uc1\u8216*Be on your guard against the teachers of the Law, who delight to walk about in long robes, and like to be greeted in the streets with respect, and to have the best seats in the synagogues, and places of honour at dinner.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}These are the men who rob widows of their houses, and make a pretence of saying long prayers. Their sentence will be all the heavier.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 21}Looking up, Jesus saw the rich people putting their gifts into the chests for the Temple offerings.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}He saw, too, a widow in poor circumstances putting two small coins into them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8216*I tell you\uc1\u8217*, he said \uc1\u8216*that this poor widow has put in more than all the others;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}for everyone else here put in something from what he had to spare, while she, in her need, has put in all she had to live on.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}When some of them spoke about the Temple being decorated with beautiful stones and offerings, Jesus said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8216*As for these things that you are looking at, a time is coming when not one stone will be left on another here. Every one will be thrown down.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}So the disciples questioned Jesus, \uc1\u8216*But, teacher, when will this happen? And what sign will there be when this is near?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*See that you are not led astray; for many will take my name, and come saying \uc1\u8220*I am He,\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*The time is close at hand.\uc1\u8221* Do not follow them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}And, when you hear of wars and disturbances, do not be terrified, for these things must occur first; but the end will not be at once.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Then he said to them, \uc1\u8216*Nation will rise against nation and kingdom against kingdom,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}and there will be great earthquakes, and plagues and famines in various places, and there will be terrible appearances and signs in the heavens.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Before all this, they will lay hands on you and persecute you, and they will betray you to synagogues and put you in prison, when you will be brought before kings and governors for the sake of my name.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then will be your opportunity of witnessing for me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Make up your minds, therefore, not to prepare your defence;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}for I will myself give you words, and a wisdom which all your opponents together will be unable to resist or defy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}You will be betrayed even by your parents and brothers and sisters and relatives and friends, and they will cause some of you to be put to death,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and you will be hated by everyone because of me my name.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Yet not a single hair of your heads will be lost!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}By your endurance you will win yourselves life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}As soon, however, as you see Jerusalem surrounded by armed camps, then you may know that the hour of her desecration is at hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Then those of you who are in Judea must take refuge in the mountains, those who are in Jerusalem must leave at once, and those who are in the country places must not go into it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}For these are to be the days of vengeance, when all that scripture says will be fulfilled.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Alas for pregnant women, and for those who are nursing infants in those days! For there will be great suffering in the land, and anger against this people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}They will fall by the edge of the sword, and will be taken prisoners to every land, and Jerusalem will be under the heel of the Gentiles, until their day is over \uc1\u8211* as it will be.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}There will be signs, too, in the sun and moon and stars, and on the earth despair among the nations, in their dismay at the roar of the sea and the surge.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}People\uc1\u8217*s hearts will fail them through dread of what is coming upon the world; for the forces of the heavens will be convulsed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Then will be seen the Son of Man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}And, when these things begin to occur, look upwards and lift your heads, for your deliverance will be at hand.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Then he taught them a lesson, saying \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Look at the fig tree and all the other trees.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}As soon as they shoot, you know, as you look at them, without being told, that summer is near.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}And so may you, as soon as you see these things happening, know that the kingdom of God is near.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}I tell you that even the present generation will not pass away until all has taken place.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}The heavens and the earth will pass away, but my words will never pass away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Be on your guard or your minds will become dulled by debauches or drunkenness or the anxieties of life, and \uc1\u8220*that day\uc1\u8221* will close on you suddenly like a trap.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}For it will come on all who are living upon the face of the whole earth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Be on the watch at all times, and pray that you may have strength to escape all that is destined to happen, and to stand in the presence of the Son of Man.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}During the days, Jesus continued to teach in the Temple Courts, but he went out and spent the nights on the hill called the \uc1\u8220*Mount of Olives.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}And all the people would get up early in the morning and come to listen to him in the Temple Courts.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 22}The feast of the unleavened bread, known as the Passover, was near.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The chief priest and the teachers of the Law were looking for an opportunity of destroying Jesus, for they were afraid of the people.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Now Satan took possession of Judas, who was known as Iscariot, and who belonged to the Twelve;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and he went and discussed with the chief priests and officers in charge at the Temple the best way of betraying Jesus to them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}They were glad of this, and agreed to pay him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}So Judas assented, and looked for an opportunity to betray Jesus to them, in the absence of a crowd.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}When the day of the Festival of the unleavened bread came, on which the Passover lambs had to be killed,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Jesus sent forward Peter and John, saying to them, \uc1\u8216*Go and make preparations for our eating the Passover.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}\uc1\u8216*Where do you wish us to make preparations?\uc1\u8217* they asked.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8216*Listen,\uc1\u8217* he answered, \uc1\u8216*when you have reached the city, a man carrying a pitcher of water will meet you; follow him into whatever house he enters;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}and you will say to the owner of the house \uc1\u8220*The teacher says to you \uc1\u8211* Where is the room where I am to eat the Passover with my disciples?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The man will show you a large upstairs room, set out; there make preparations.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}So Peter and John went on, and found everything just as Jesus had told them, and they prepared the Passover.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}When the time came, Jesus took his place at the table, and the apostles with him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8216*I have most earnestly wished,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*to eat this Passover with you before I suffer.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}For I tell you that I will not eat it again, until it has had its fulfilment in the kingdom of God.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Then, on receiving a cup, after saying the thanksgiving, he said, \uc1\u8216*Take this and share it among you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For I tell you that I will not, after today, drink of the fruit of the vine, until the kingdom of God has come.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Then Jesus took some bread, and, after saying the thanksgiving, broke it and gave to them, with the words, \uc1\u8216*This is my body.{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}  Some later manuscripts add: which is now to be given on your behalf. Do this in memory of me. And in the same way with the cup, after supper, saying: \uc1\u8216*This cup is the New Covenant made by my blood which is being poured out on your behalf.\uc1\u8217* }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Yet see! The hand of the man who is betraying me is beside me on the table!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}True, the Son of Man is passing, by the way ordained for him, yet alas for that man by whom he is being betrayed!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Then they began questioning one another which of them it could be who was going to do this.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And a dispute arose among them as to which of them was to be regarded as the greatest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Jesus, however, said, \uc1\u8216*The kings of the Gentiles lord it over them, and their oppressors are styled \uc1\u8220*Benefactors.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}But with you it must not be so. No, let the greatest among you become like the youngest, and him who leads like him who serves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Which is the greater \uc1\u8211* the master at the table or his servant? Is not it the master at the table? Yet I myself am among you as one who serves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}You are the men who have stood by me in my trials;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}and, just as my Father has assigned me a kingdom, I assign you places,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}so that you may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and be seated on twelve thrones as judges of the twelve tribes of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Simon! Simon! listen. Satan demanded leave to sift you all like wheat,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}but I prayed for you, Simon, that your faith should not fail. And you, when you have returned to me, are to strengthen the others.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}\uc1\u8216*Master,\uc1\u8217* said Peter, \uc1\u8216*with you I am ready to go both to prison and to death.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}\uc1\u8216*I tell you, Peter,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*the cock will not crow today until you have disowned all knowledge of me three times.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Then he said to them all, \uc1\u8216*When I sent you out as my messengers, without either purse, or bag, or sandals, were you in need of anything?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*No; nothing,\uc1\u8217* they answered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}\uc1\u8216*Now, however,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*he who has a purse must take it and his bag as well; and he who has not must sell his cloak and buy a sword.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}For, I tell you, that passage of scripture must be fulfilled in me, which says \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*He was counted among the godless\uc1\u8221*; indeed all that refers to me is finding its fulfilment.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}\uc1\u8216*Master,\uc1\u8217* they exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*look, here are two swords!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*Enough!\uc1\u8217* said Jesus.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Jesus then went out, and made his way as usual to the Mount of Olives, followed by his disciples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}And, when he reached the spot, he said to them, \uc1\u8216*Pray that you may not fall into temptation.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}Then he withdrew about a stone\uc1\u8217*s throw, and knelt down and began to pray.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}\uc1\u8216*Father,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*if it is your pleasure, spare me this cup; only, not my will but your be done.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}Presently there appeared to him an angel from heaven, who strengthened him.{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Some later manuscripts do not contain verses 43 or 44. }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}And, as his anguish became intense, he prayed still more earnestly, while his sweat was like great drops of blood falling on the ground.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}Then he rose from praying, and came to the disciples and found them sleeping for sorrow.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}\uc1\u8216*Why are you asleep?\uc1\u8217* he asked them. \uc1\u8216*Rise and pray so that you don\uc1\u8217*t fall into temptation.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}While he was still speaking, a crowd appeared in sight, led by the man called Judas, who was one of the Twelve. Judas approached Jesus, to kiss him;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}at which Jesus said to him, \uc1\u8216*Judas, is it by a kiss that you betray the Son of Man?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}But when those who were round Jesus saw what was going to happen, they exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*Master, should we use our swords?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}And one of them struck the high priest\uc1\u8217*s servant and cut off his right ear;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}at which Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Let me at least do this\uc1\u8217*; and, touching his ear, he healed the wound.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}Then, turning to the chief priests and officers in charge at the Temple and the elders, who had come for him, he said, \uc1\u8216*Have you come out, as if after a robber, with swords and clubs?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}When I was with you day after day in the Temple Courts, you did not lay hands on me; but now your time has come, and the power of darkness.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}Those who had taken Jesus prisoner took him away into the house of the high priest. Peter followed at a distance.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}But, when they had lit a fire in the centre of the courtyard and had all sat down there, Peter seated himself in the middle of them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}Presently a maidservant saw him sitting near the blaze of the fire. She looked carefully at him and said, \uc1\u8216*Why, this man was one of his companions!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 57}But Peter denied it. \uc1\u8216*I do not know him,\uc1\u8217* he replied.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 58}A little while afterwards someone else \uc1\u8211* a man \uc1\u8211* saw him and said, \uc1\u8216*Why, you are one of them!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*No,\uc1\u8217* Peter said, \uc1\u8216*I am not.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 59}About an hour later another man declared positively, \uc1\u8216*This man also was certainly with him. Why, he is a Galilean!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 60}But Peter said, \uc1\u8216*I do not know what you are speaking about.\uc1\u8217* Instantly, while he was still speaking, a cock crowed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 61}And the Master turned and looked at Peter; and Peter remembered the words that the Master had said to him \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Before a cock has crowed today, you will disown me three times\uc1\u8217*;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 62}and he went outside and wept bitterly.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 63}The men who held Jesus kept making sport of him and beating him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 64}They blindfolded him and then questioned him. \uc1\u8216*Now play the prophet,\uc1\u8217* they said. \uc1\u8216*Who was it that struck you?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 65}And they heaped many other insults on him.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 66}At daybreak the assembly of the elders of the people met \uc1\u8211* both the chief priests and the teachers of the Law \uc1\u8211* and took Jesus before their High Council.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 67}\uc1\u8216*If you are the Christ,\uc1\u8217* they said, \uc1\u8216*tell us so.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
\uc1\u8216*If I tell you,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*you will not believe me;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 68}and, if I question you, you will not answer.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 69}But from this hour the Son of Man will be seated on the right hand of God Almighty.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 70}\uc1\u8216*Are you, then, the Son of God?\uc1\u8217* they all asked. \uc1\u8216*It is true,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*I am.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 71}At this they exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*Why do we want any more evidence? We have heard it ourselves from his own lips!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 23}Then they all rose in a body and led Jesus before Pilate.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And they began to accuse him, \uc1\u8216*This is a man whom we found misleading our people, preventing them from paying taxes to the Emperor, and giving out that he himself is \uc1\u8220*Christ, a king.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8216*Are you the king of the Jews?\uc1\u8217* Pilate asked him. \uc1\u8216*It is true,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}But Pilate, turning to the chief priests and the people, said, \uc1\u8216*I do not see anything to find fault with in this man.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}But they insisted, \uc1\u8216*He is stirring up the people by his teaching all through Judea; he began with Galilee and has now come here.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Hearing this, Pilate asked if the man was a Galilean;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and, having satisfied himself that Jesus came under Herod\uc1\u8217*s jurisdiction, he sent him to Herod, who also was at Jerusalem at the time.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}When Herod saw Jesus, he was exceedingly pleased, for he had been wanting to see him for a long time, having heard a great deal about him; and he was hoping to see some sign given by him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}So he questioned him at some length, but Jesus made no reply.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Meanwhile the chief priests and the teachers of the Law stood by and vehemently accused him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And Herod, with his soldiers, treated Jesus with scorn; he mocked him by throwing a gorgeous robe round him, and then sent him back to Pilate.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And Herod and Pilate became friends that very day, for before that there had been ill-will between them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}So Pilate summoned the chief priests, and the leading men, and the people,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}and said to them, \uc1\u8216*You brought this man before me charged with misleading the people; and yet, for my part, though I examined him before you, I did not find this man to blame for any of the things of which you accuse him;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}nor did Herod either; for he has sent him back to us. And, as a fact, he has not done anything deserving death;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}so I will have him scourged, and then release him.\uc1\u8217*{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}  Some later manuscripts add: He had to release someone to them at the feast. }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}But they began to shout as one man, \uc1\u8216*Kill this fellow, but release Barabbas for us.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}(Barabbas was a man who had been put in prison for a riot that had broken out in the city and for murder.){\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Pilate, however, wanting to release Jesus, called to them again;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}but they kept calling out, \uc1\u8216*Crucify, crucify him!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}\uc1\u8216*Why, what harm has this man done?\uc1\u8217* Pilate said to them for the third time. \uc1\u8216*I have found nothing in him for which he could be condemned to death. So I will have him scourged, and then release him.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}But they persisted in loudly demanding his crucifixion; and their clamour gained the day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Pilate decided that their demand should be granted.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}He released the man who had been put in prison for riot and murder, as they demanded, and gave Jesus up to be dealt with as they pleased.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}And, as they were leading Jesus away, they laid hold of Simon from Cyrene, who was on his way in from the country, and they put the cross on his shoulders, for him to carry it behind Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}There was a great crowd of people following him, many being women who were beating their breasts and wailing for him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}So Jesus turned and said to them, \uc1\u8216*Women of Jerusalem, do not weep for me, but weep for yourselves and for your children.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}A time, I tell you, is coming, when it will be said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Happy are the women who are barren, and those who have never borne children or nursed them!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}At that time people will begin to say to the mountains \uc1\u8220*Fall on us,\uc1\u8221* and to the hills \uc1\u8220*Cover us.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}If what you see is done while the tree is green, what will happen when it is dry?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}There were two others also, criminals, led out to be executed with Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}When they had reached the place called \uc1\u8220*The Skull,\uc1\u8221* there they crucified Jesus and the criminals, one on the right, and one on the left.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Then Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Father, forgive them; they do not know what they are doing.\uc1\u8217* His clothes they divided among them by casting lots.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Meanwhile the people stood looking on. Even the leading men said with a sneer, \uc1\u8216*He saved others, let him save himself, if he is God\uc1\u8217*s Christ, his chosen one.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}The soldiers, too, came up in mockery, bringing him common wine,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}and saying as they did so, \uc1\u8216*If you are the king of the Jews, save yourself.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}Above him were the words \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}One of the criminals who were hanging beside Jesus railed at him. \uc1\u8216*Aren\uc1\u8217*t you the Christ? Save yourself and us,\uc1\u8217* he said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}But the other rebuked him. \uc1\u8216*Haven\uc1\u8217*t you,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*any fear of God, now that you are under the same sentence?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}And we justly so, for we are only reaping our deserts, but this man has not done anything wrong.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}Jesus,\uc1\u8217* he went on, \uc1\u8216*do not forget me when you have come to your kingdom.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}And Jesus answered, \uc1\u8216*I tell you, this very day you will be with me in Paradise.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}It was nearly midday, when a darkness came over the whole country, lasting until three in the afternoon,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}the sun being eclipsed; and the Temple curtain was torn down the middle.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}Then Jesus, with a loud cry, said, \uc1\u8216*Father, into your hands I commit my spirit.\uc1\u8217* And with these words he expired.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}The Roman centurion, on seeing what had happened, praised God, exclaiming, \uc1\u8216*This must have been a good man!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}All the people who had collected to see the sight watched what occurred, and then went home beating their breasts.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}All the friends of Jesus had been standing at a distance, with the women who accompanied him from Galilee, watching all this.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}Now there was a man of the name of Joseph, who was a member of the Council, and who bore a good and upright character.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}(This man had not assented to the decision and action of the Council.) He belonged to Arimathea, a town in Judea, and lived in expectation of the kingdom of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}He now went to see Pilate, and asked for the body of Jesus;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}and, when he had taken it down, he wrapped it in a linen sheet, and laid him in a tomb cut out of stone, in which no one had yet been buried.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}It was the Preparation day, and just before the Sabbath began.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}The women who had accompanied Jesus from Galilee followed, and saw the tomb and how the body of Jesus was laid,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}and then went home, and prepared spices and perfumes.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Risen Life

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
During the Sabbath they rested, as directed by the commandment.{\cf1\f1\fs22 24}But very early on the first day of the week they went to the tomb, taking with them the spices that they had prepared.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}They found that the stone had been rolled away from the tomb;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and, on going into it, they could not find the body{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Some later manuscripts add: of the Lord Jesus. }.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}While they were at a loss to account for this, all at once two men stood beside them, in dazzling clothing.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}But, when in their fear the women bowed their faces to the ground, the men said to them, \uc1\u8216*Why are you looking among the dead for him who is living?{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}  Some later manuscripts add: He is not here but he has risen. } Remember how he spoke to you before he left Galilee \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}How he said that the Son of Man must be betrayed into the hands of wicked men, and be crucified, and rise again on the third day.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Then they remembered the words of Jesus,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}and, on returning from the tomb, they told all this to the Eleven and to all the rest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}There were Mary of Magdala, and Joanna, and Mary, the mother of James. The other women, too, spoke about this to the apostles.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}What they said seemed to the apostles mere nonsense, and they did not believe them.{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}  Some later manuscripts add: Peter got up and ran to the tomb. Stooping down he saw nothing but the linen wrappings, and he went away, wondering to himself at what had taken place. }
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}It happened that very day that two of the disciples were going to a village called Emmaus, which was about seven miles from Jerusalem,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}talking together, as they went, about all that had just taken place.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}While they were talking about these things and discussing them, Jesus himself came up and went on their way with them;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}but their eyes were blinded so that they could not recognise him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8216*What is this that you are saying to each other as you walk along?\uc1\u8217* Jesus asked. They stopped, with sad looks on their faces,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}and then one of them, whose name was Cleopas, said to Jesus, \uc1\u8216*Are you staying by yourself at Jerusalem, that you have not heard of the things that have happened there within the last few days?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}\uc1\u8216*What things do you mean?\uc1\u8217* asked Jesus. \uc1\u8216*Why, about Jesus of Nazareth,\uc1\u8217* they answered, \uc1\u8216*who, in the eyes of God and all the people, was a prophet, whose power was felt in both his words and actions;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}and how the chief priests and our leading men gave him up to be sentenced to death, and afterwards crucified him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}But we were hoping that he was the Destined Deliverer of Israel; yes, and besides all this, it is now three days since these things occurred.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And what is more, some of the women among us have greatly astonished us. They went to the tomb at daybreak{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And, not finding the body of Jesus there, came and told us that they had seen a vision of angels who told them that he was alive.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}So some of our number went to the tomb and found everything just as the women had said, but they did not see Jesus.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Then Jesus said to them, \uc1\u8216*Foolish men, slow to accept all that the prophets have said!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Was not the Christ bound to undergo this suffering before entering into his glory?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Then, beginning with Moses and all the prophets, he explained to them all through the scriptures the passages that referred to himself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}When they got near the village to which they were walking, Jesus appeared to be going further;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}but they pressed him not to do so. \uc1\u8216*Stay with us,\uc1\u8217* they said, \uc1\u8216*for it is getting towards evening, and the sun in already low.\uc1\u8217* So Jesus went in to stay with them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}After he had taken his place at the table with them, he took the bread and said the blessing, and broke it, and gave it to them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Then their eyes were opened and they recognised him; but he disappeared from their sight.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}\uc1\u8216*How our hearts glowed,\uc1\u8217* the disciples said to each other, \uc1\u8216*while he was talking to us on the road, and when he explained the scriptures to us!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Then they immediately got up and returned to Jerusalem, where they found the Eleven and their companions all together,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}who told them that the Master had really risen, and had appeared to Simon.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}So they also related what had happened during their walk, and how they had recognised Jesus at the breaking of the bread.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}While they were still talking about these things, Jesus himself stood among them.{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Some later manuscripts add: and said, \uc1\u8216*Peace be with you.\uc1\u8217* }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}In their terror and alarm they thought they saw a ghost,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}but Jesus said to them, \uc1\u8216*Why are you so startled? And why do doubts arise in your minds?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Look at my hands and my feet, and you will know that it is I. Feel me, and look at me, for a ghost has not flesh and bones, as you see that I have.\uc1\u8217*{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}  Some later manuscripts add: After saying this he showed them his hands and his feet. }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}While they were still unable to believe it all, overcome with joy, and were wondering if it were true, Jesus said to them, \uc1\u8216*Have you anything here to eat?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}They handed him a piece of broiled fish,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}and he took it and ate it before their eyes.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}\uc1\u8216*This is what I told you,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*when I was still with you \uc1\u8211* that everything that had been written about me in the Law of Moses, the prophets, and the Psalms, must be fulfilled.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}Then he enabled them to understand the meaning of the scriptures, saying to them,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}\uc1\u8216*Scripture says that the Christ will suffer, and that he will rise again from the dead on the third day,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}and that repentance for forgiveness of sins will be proclaimed on his authority to all the nations \uc1\u8211* beginning at Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}You yourselves are to be witnesses to all this.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}And now I am myself about to send you that which my Father has promised. But you must remain in the city until you have been invested with power from above.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}After this, Jesus led them out as far as Bethany, and there raised his hands and blessed them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}As he was in the act of blessing them, he left them.{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Some later manuscripts add: and was carried up into heaven. }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}They returned{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Some later manuscripts read: They bowed to the ground before him and returned. } to Jerusalem full of joy;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}and they were constantly in the Temple Courts, blessing God.
\par}
