{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Introduction

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}To the church of God in Corinth, to those who have been consecrated by union with Christ Jesus and called to become his people, and also to all, wherever they may be, who invoke the name of our Lord Jesus Christ \uc1\u8211* their Master and ours,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}from Paul, who has been called to be an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, and from Sosthenes, our fellow follower of the Lord.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}May God, our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ bless you and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}I always thank God for you. I thank him for the blessing bestowed on you in Christ Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}For through union with him you were enriched in every way \uc1\u8211* in your power to preach, and in your knowledge of the truth;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and so became yourselves a confirmation of my testimony to the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}There is no gift in which you are deficient, while waiting for our Lord Jesus Christ to be revealed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And God himself will strengthen you to the end, so that at the day of our Lord Jesus Christ you may be found blameless.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}God will not fail you, and it is he who called you into communion with his Son, Jesus Christ, our Lord.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The State of the Church at Corinth

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}But I appeal to you, my friends, by the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, to agree in what you profess, and not to allow divisions to exist among you, but to be united \uc1\u8211* of one mind and of one opinion.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}For I have been informed, my friends, by the members of Chloe\uc1\u8217*s household, that party feeling exists among you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I mean this: that every one of you says either \uc1\u8220*I follow Paul,\uc1\u8221* or \uc1\u8220*I Apollos,\uc1\u8221* or \uc1\u8220*I Cephas,\uc1\u8221* or \uc1\u8220*I Christ.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}You have torn the Christ in pieces! Was it Paul who was crucified for you? Or were you baptized in the name of Paul?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}I am thankful that I did not baptize any of you except Crispus and Gaius,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}so that no one can say that you were baptized in my name.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}I baptized also the household of Stephanas. I do not know that I baptized anyone else.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}My mission from Christ was not to baptize, but to tell the good news; not, however, in the language of philosophy, in case the cross of the Christ should be robbed of its meaning.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}The message of the cross is indeed mere folly to those who are on the path to ruin, but to us who are on the path of salvation it is the power of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}For scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will bring the philosophy of the philosophers to naught, and the shrewdness of the shrewd I will bring to nothing.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Where is the philosopher? Where the teacher of the Law? Where the disputant of today? Has not God shown the world\uc1\u8217*s philosophy to be folly?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}For since the world, in God\uc1\u8217*s wisdom, did not by its philosophy learn to know God, God saw fit, by the \uc1\u8220*folly\uc1\u8221* of our proclamation, to save those who believe in Christ!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}While Jews ask for miraculous signs, and Greeks study philosophy,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}we are proclaiming Christ crucified! \uc1\u8211* to the Jews an obstacle, to the Gentiles mere folly,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}but to those who have received the call, whether Jews or Greeks, Christ, the power of God and the wisdom of God!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}For God\uc1\u8217*s \uc1\u8220*folly\uc1\u8221* is wiser than people, and God\uc1\u8217*s \uc1\u8220*weakness\uc1\u8221* is stronger than people.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Look at the facts of your call, friends. There are not many among you who are wise, as people reckon wisdom, not many who are influential, not many who are high-born;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}but God chose what the world counts foolish to put its wise to shame, and God chose what the world counts weak to put its strong to shame,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}and God chose what the world counts poor and insignificant \uc1\u8211* things that to it are unreal \uc1\u8211* to bring its \uc1\u8220*realities\uc1\u8221* to nothing,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}so that in his presence no one should boast.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}But you, by your union with Christ Jesus, belong to God; and Christ, by God\uc1\u8217*s will, became not only our wisdom, but also our righteousness, holiness, and deliverance,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}so that \uc1\u8211* in the words of scripture \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Whoever boasts should boast of the Lord!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}For my own part, friends, when I came to you, it was with no display of eloquence or philosophy that I came to tell the hidden purpose of God;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}for I had determined that, while with you, I would forget everything except Jesus Christ \uc1\u8211* and him crucified!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Indeed, when I came among you, I was weak, and full of fears, and in great anxiety.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}My message and my proclamation were not delivered in the persuasive language of philosophy, but were accompanied by the manifestation of spiritual power,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}so that your faith should be based, not on the human wisdom, but on the power of God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Yet there is a philosophy that we teach to those whose faith is matured, but it is not the philosophy of today, or of the leaders of today \uc1\u8211* whose downfall is at hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}No, it is a divine philosophy that we teach, one concerned with the hidden purpose of God \uc1\u8211* that long hidden philosophy which God, before time began, destined for our glory.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}This philosophy is clearly not known to any of the leaders of today, since, had they known it, they would never have crucified our glorious Lord!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}It is what scripture speaks of as \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*What eye never saw, nor ear ever heard,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
what never entered people\uc1\u8217*s minds \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
all these things God has prepared for those who love him.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Yet to us God revealed it through his Spirit; for the Spirit fathoms all things, even the inmost depths of God\uc1\u8217*s being.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}For what person is there who knows what a person is, except the person\uc1\u8217*s own spirit within them? So, also, no one comprehends what God is, except the Spirit of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And as for us, it is not the spirit of the world that we have received, but the Spirit that comes from God, so that we may realize the blessings given to us by him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And we speak of these gifts, not in language taught by human philosophy, but in language taught by the Spirit, explaining spiritual things in spiritual words.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}The merely intellectual person rejects the teaching of the Spirit of God; for to them it is mere folly; they cannot grasp it, because it is to be understood only by spiritual insight.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But the person with spiritual insight is able to understand everything, although they themselves are understood by no one.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}For who has so comprehended the mind of the Lord as to be able to instruct him? We, however, have the mind of Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}But I, my friends, could not speak to you as people with spiritual insight, but only as worldly-minded \uc1\u8211* mere infants in the faith of Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I fed you with milk, not with solid food, for you were not then able to take it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
No, and even now you are not able; you are still worldly.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}While there exist among you jealousy and party feeling, is it not true that you are worldly, and are acting merely as other people do?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}When one says \uc1\u8220*I follow Paul,\uc1\u8221* and another \uc1\u8220*I follow Apollos,\uc1\u8221* aren\uc1\u8217*t you like other people?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}What, I ask, is Apollos? Or what is Paul? Servants through whom you were led to accept the faith; and that only as the Lord helped each of you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}I planted, and Apollos watered, but it was God who caused the growth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore neither the one who plants, nor the one who waters, counts for anything, but only God who causes the growth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}In this the person who plants and the person who waters are one; yet each will receive their own reward in proportion to their own labour.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For we are God\uc1\u8217*s fellow workers; you are God\uc1\u8217*s harvest field, God\uc1\u8217*s building.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}In fulfilment of the charge which God had entrusted to me, I laid the foundation like a skilful master; but someone else is now building on it. Let everyone take care how they build;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}for no one can lay any other foundation than the one already laid \uc1\u8211* Jesus Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Whatever is used by those who build on this foundation, whether gold, silver, costly stones, wood, hay, or straw,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}the quality of each man\uc1\u8217*s work will become known, for the day will make it plain; because that day is to be ushered in with fire, and the fire itself will test the quality of every man\uc1\u8217*s work.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}If anyone\uc1\u8217*s work, which they have built on that foundation, still remains, they will gain a reward.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}If anyone\uc1\u8217*s work is burnt up, they will suffer loss; though they themselves will escape, but only as one who has passed through fire.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that you are God\uc1\u8217*s Temple, and that God\uc1\u8217*s Spirit has his home in you?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}If any one destroys the Temple of God, God will destroy them; for the Temple of God is sacred, and so also are you.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Let no one deceive himself. If any one among you imagines that, as regards this world, they are wise, they should become a \uc1\u8220*fool,\uc1\u8221* that they may become wise.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}For in God\uc1\u8217*s sight this world\uc1\u8217*s wisdom is folly. Scripture tells of \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*One who catches the wise in their own craftiness,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And it says again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*The Lord sees how fruitless are the deliberations of the wise.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Therefore let no one boast about people; for all things are yours \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}whether Paul, or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life, or death, or the present, or the future \uc1\u8211* all things are yours!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}But you are Christ\uc1\u8217*s and Christ is God\uc1\u8217*s.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}Let people look on us as Christ\uc1\u8217*s servants, and as stewards of the hidden truths of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Now what we look for in stewards is that they should be trustworthy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}But it weighs very little with me that I am judged by you or by any human tribunal. No, I do not even judge myself;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}for, though I am conscious of nothing against myself, that does not prove me innocent. It is the Lord who is my judge.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Therefore do not pass judgment before the time, but wait until the Lord comes. He will throw light on what is now dark and obscure, and will reveal the motives in people\uc1\u8217*s minds; and then everyone will receive due praise from God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}All this, friends, I have, for your sakes, applied to Apollos and myself, so that, from our example, you may learn to observe the precept \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Keep to what is written,\uc1\u8221* that none of you may speak boastfully of one teacher to the disparagement of another.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}For who makes any one of you superior to others? And what have you that was not given you? But if you received it as a gift, why do you boast as if you had not?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Are you all so soon satisfied? Are you so soon rich? Have you begun to reign without us? Would indeed that you had, so that we also might reign with you!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For, as it seems to me, God has exhibited us, the apostles, last of all, as people doomed to death. We are made a spectacle to the universe, both to angels and to people!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}We, for Christ\uc1\u8217*s sake, are fools, but you, by your union with Christ, are people of discernment. We are weak, but you are strong. You are honoured, but we are despised.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}To this very hour we go hungry, thirsty, and naked; we are beaten; we are homeless;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}we work hard, toiling with our own hands. We meet abuse with blessings, we meet persecution with endurance,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}we meet slander with gentle appeals. We have been treated as the scum of the earth, the vilest of the vile, to this very hour.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}It is with no wish to shame you that I am writing like this; but to warn you as my own dear children.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Though you may have thousands of instructors in the faith of Christ, yet you have not many fathers. It was I who, through union with Christ Jesus, became your father by means of the good news.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Therefore I entreat you \uc1\u8211* Follow my example.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}This is my reason for sending Timothy to you. He is my own dear faithful child in the Master\uc1\u8217*s service, and he will remind you of my methods of teaching the faith of Christ Jesus \uc1\u8211* methods which I follow everywhere in every church.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Some, I hear, are puffed up with pride, thinking that I am not coming to you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}But come to you I will, and that soon, if it please the Lord; and then I will find out, not what words these people use who are so puffed up, but what power they possess;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}for the kingdom of God is based, not on words, but on power.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}What do you wish? Am I to come to you with a rod, or in a loving and gentle spirit?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}There is a wide-spread report respecting a case of immorality among you, and that, too, of a kind that does not occur even among the Gentiles \uc1\u8211* a man, I hear, is living with his father\uc1\u8217*s wife!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Instead of grieving over it and taking steps for the expulsion of the man who has done this thing, is it possible that you are still puffed up?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}For I myself, though absent in body, have been present with you in spirit, and in the name of our Lord Jesus I have already passed judgment, just as if I had been present, on the man who has acted in this way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}I have decided \uc1\u8211* having been present in spirit at your meetings, when the power of the Lord Jesus was with us \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}to deliver such a man as this over to Satan, that what is sensual in him may be destroyed, so that his spirit may be saved at the day of the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Your boasting is unseemly. Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that even a little yeast leavens all the dough?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Get rid entirely of the old leaven, so that you may be like new dough \uc1\u8211* free from leaven, as in truth you are. For our passover lamb is already sacrificed \uc1\u8211* Christ himself;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}therefore let us keep our festival, not with the leaven of former days, nor with the leaven of vice and wickedness, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}I told you, in my letter, not to associate with immoral people \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}not, of course, meaning people of the world who are in immoral, or who are covetous and grasping, or who worship idols; for then you would have to leave the world altogether.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But, as things are, I say that you are not to associate with anyone who, although a follower of Christ in name, is immoral, or covetous, or an idolater, or abusive, or a drunkard, or grasping \uc1\u8211* no, not even to sit down to eat with such people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}What have I to do with judging those outside the church? Is it not for you to judge those who are within the church,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}while God judges those who are outside? Put away the wicked from among you.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}Can it be that, when one of you has a dispute with another, they dare to have their case tried before the heathen, instead of before Christ\uc1\u8217*s people?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that Christ\uc1\u8217*s people will try the world? And if the world is to be tried by you, are you unfit to try the most trivial cases?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that we are to try angels \uc1\u8211* to say nothing of the affairs of this life?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Why, then, if you have cases relating to the affairs of this life, do you set to try them those who carry no weight with the church? To your shame I ask it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Can it be that there is not one among you wise enough to decide between two of their fellow followers?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Must a follower sue a fellow follower? In front of unbelievers?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}To begin with, it is undoubtedly a loss to you to have lawsuits with one another. Why not rather let yourselves be wronged? Why not rather let yourselves be cheated?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Instead of this, you wrong and cheat others yourselves \uc1\u8211* yes, even other followers!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that wrongdoers will have no share in God\uc1\u8217*s kingdom? Do not be deceived. No one who is immoral, or an idolater, or an adulterer, or licentious, or a sexual pervert,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}or a thief, or covetous, or a drunkard, or abusive, or grasping, will have any share in God\uc1\u8217*s kingdom.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Such some of you used to be; but you washed yourselves clean. You became Christ\uc1\u8217*s people! You were pronounced righteous through the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, and through the Spirit of our God!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Everything is allowable for me! Yes, but everything is not profitable. Everything is allowable for me! Yes, but for my part, I will not let myself be enslaved by anything.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Food exists for the stomach, and the stomach for food; but God will put an end to both the one and the other. The body, however, exists, not for immorality, but for the Lord, and the Lord for the body;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}and, as God has raised the Lord, so he will raise us up also by the exercise of his power.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that your bodies are Christ\uc1\u8217*s members? Am I, then, to take the members that belong to the Christ and make them the members of a prostitute? Heaven forbid!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Or don\uc1\u8217*t you know that a man who unites himself with a prostitute is one with her in body (for \uc1\u8220*the two,\uc1\u8221* it is said, \uc1\u8220*will become one\uc1\u8221*);{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}while a man who is united with the Lord is one with him in spirit?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Shun all immorality. Every other sin that people commit is something outside the body; but an immoral person sins against their own body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Again, don\uc1\u8217*t you know that your body is a shrine of the Holy Spirit that is within you \uc1\u8211* the Spirit which you have from God?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Moreover, you are not your own masters; you were bought, and the price was paid. Therefore, honour God in your bodies.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Answers to Questions Asked by the Church at Corinth

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 7}With reference to the subjects about which you wrote to me: It is good for a man to remain single.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}But, owing to the prevalence of immorality, I advise every man to have his own wife, and every woman her husband.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}A husband should give his wife her due, and a wife her husband.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}It is not the wife, but the husband, who exercises power over her body; and so, too, it is not the husband, but the wife, who exercises power over his body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Do not deprive each other of what is due \uc1\u8211* unless it is only for a time and by mutual consent, so that your minds may be free for prayer until you again live as man and wife \uc1\u8211* otherwise Satan might take advantage of your want of self-control and tempt you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}I say this, however, as a concession, not as a command.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}I should wish everyone to be just what I am myself. But everyone has his own gift from God \uc1\u8211* one in one way, and one in another.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}My advice, then, to those who are not married, and to widows, is this: It would be good for them to remain as I am myself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But, if they cannot control themselves, they should marry, for it is better to marry than to be consumed with passion.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}To those who are married my direction is \uc1\u8211* yet it is not mine, but the Master\uc1\u8217*s \uc1\u8211* that a woman is not to leave her husband{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}(If she has done so, she should remain as she is, or else be reconciled to her husband) and also that a man is not to divorce his wife.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}To all others I say \uc1\u8211* I, not the Master \uc1\u8211* If a follower of the Lord is married to a woman, who is an unbeliever but willing to live with him, he should not divorce her;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}and a woman who is married to a man, who is an unbeliever but willing to live with her, should not divorce her husband.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For, through his wife, the husband who is an unbeliever has become associated with Christ\uc1\u8217*s people; and the wife who is an unbeliever has become associated with Christ\uc1\u8217*s people through the Lord\uc1\u8217*s follower whom she has married. Otherwise your children would be \uc1\u8220*defiled,\uc1\u8221* but, as it is, they belong to Christ\uc1\u8217*s people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}However, if the unbeliever wishes to be separated, let them be so. Under such circumstances neither is bound; God has called you to live in peace.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}How can you tell, wife, whether you may not save your husband? And how can you tell, husband, whether you may not save your wife?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}In any case, a person should continue to live in the condition which the Lord has allotted to them, and in which they were when God called them. This is the rule that I lay down in every church.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Was a man already circumcised when he was called? Then he should not efface his circumcision. Has a man been called when uncircumcised? Then he should not be circumcised.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Circumcision is nothing; the want of it is nothing; but to keep the commands of God is everything.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Let everyone remain in that condition of life in which they were when the call came to them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Were you a slave when you were called? Do not let that trouble you. No, even if you are able to gain your freedom, still do your best.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}For the person who was a slave when they were called to the master\uc1\u8217*s service is the Master\uc1\u8217*s freedman; so, too, the person who was free when called is Christ\uc1\u8217*s slave.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}You were bought, and the price was paid. Do not let yourselves become slaves to people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Friends, let everyone remain in the condition in which they were when they were called, in close communion with God.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}With regard to unmarried women, I have no command from the Master to give you, but I tell you my opinion, and the Master in his mercy has made me worthy to be trusted.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}I think, then, that, in view of the time of suffering that has now come upon us, what I have already said is best \uc1\u8211* that a man should remain as he is.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Are you married to a wife? Then do not seek to be separated. Are you separated from a wife? Then do not seek for a wife.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Still, if you should marry, that is not wrong; nor, if a young woman marries, is that wrong. But those who marry will have much trouble to bear, and my wish is to spare you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}What I mean, friends, is this \uc1\u8211* the time is short. Meanwhile, let those who have wives live as if they had none,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}those who are weeping as if not weeping, those who are rejoicing as if not rejoicing, those who buy as if not possessing,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}and those who use the good things of the world as using them sparingly; for this world as we see it is passing away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}I want you to be free from anxiety. The unmarried man is anxious about the Master\uc1\u8217*s cause, desiring to please him;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}while the married man is anxious about worldly matters, desiring to please his wife;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}and so his interests are divided. Again, the unmarried woman, whether she is old or young, is anxious about the Master\uc1\u8217*s cause, striving to be pure both in body and in spirit, while the married woman is anxious about worldly matters, desiring to please her husband.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}I say this for your own benefit, not with any intention of putting a halter round your necks, but in order to secure for the Master seemly and constant devotion, free from all distraction.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}If, however, a father thinks that he is not acting fairly by his unmarried daughter, when she is past her youth, and if under these circumstances her marriage ought to take place, he should act as he thinks right. He is doing nothing wrong \uc1\u8211* let the marriage take place.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}On the other hand, a father, who has definitely made up his mind, and is under no compulsion, but is free to carry out his own wishes, and who has come to the decision, in his own mind, to keep his unmarried daughter at home will be doing right.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}In short, the one who consents to his daughter\uc1\u8217*s marriage is doing right, and yet the other will be doing better.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}A wife is bound to her husband as long as he lives; but, if the husband should pass to his rest, the widow is free to marry anyone she wishes, provided he is a believer.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}Yet she will be happier if she remains as she is \uc1\u8211* in my opinion, for I think that I also have the Spirit of God.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 8}With reference to food that has been offered in sacrifice to idols \uc1\u8211* We are aware that all of us have knowledge! Knowledge breeds conceit, while love builds up character.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}If someone thinks that they know anything, they have not yet reached that knowledge which they ought to have reached.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}On the other hand, if a person loves God, they are known by God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}With reference, then, to eating food that has been offered to idols \uc1\u8211* we are aware that an idol is nothing in the world, and that there is no God but one.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Even supposing that there are so-called \uc1\u8220*gods\uc1\u8221* either in heaven or on earth \uc1\u8211* and there are many such \uc1\u8220*gods\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*lords\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Yet for us there is only one God, the Father, from whom all things come (and for him we live), and one Lord, Jesus Christ, through whom all things come (and through him we live).{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Still, it is not everyone that has this knowledge. Some people, because of their association with idols, continued down to the present time, eat the food as food offered to an idol; and their consciences, while still weak, are dulled.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}What we eat, however, will not bring us nearer to God. We lose nothing by not eating this food, and we gain nothing by eating it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But take care that this right of yours does not become in any way a stumbling-block to the weak.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For if someone should see you who possess this knowledge, feasting in an idol\uc1\u8217*s temple, will not their conscience, if they are weak, become so hardened that they, too, will eat food offered to idols?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And so, through this knowledge of yours, the weak person is ruined \uc1\u8211* someone for whose sake Christ died!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}In this way, by sinning against your fellow followers of the Lord and injuring their consciences, while still weak, you sin against Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Therefore, if what I eat makes a follower of the Lord fall, rather than make them fall, I will never eat meat again.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 9}Am I not free? Am I not an apostle? Have I not seen our Lord Jesus? Aren\uc1\u8217*t you yourselves my work achieved in union with the Lord?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}If I am not an apostle to others, yet at least I am to you; for you are the seal that stamps me as an apostle in union with the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}The defence that I make to my critics is this:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Haven\uc1\u8217*t we a right to food and drink?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Haven\uc1\u8217*t we a right to take a wife with us, if she is a Christian, as the other apostles and the Master\uc1\u8217*s brothers and Cephas all do?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Or is it only Barnabas and I who have no right to give up working for our bread?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Does anyone ever serve as a soldier at his own expense? Does anyone plant a vineyard and not eat its produce? Or does anyone look after a herd and not drink the milk?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Am I, in all this, speaking only from the human standpoint? Does not the Law also say the same?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For in the Law of Moses it is said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

