{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
Is it the bullocks that God is thinking of?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Or is not is said entirely for our sakes? Surely it was written for our sakes, for the ploughman ought not to plough, nor the thrasher to thrash, without expecting a share of the grain.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Since we, then, sowed spiritual seed for you, is it too much that we should reap from you an earthly harvest?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}If others share in this right over you, don\uc1\u8217*t we even more? Still we did not avail ourselves of this right. No, we endure anything rather than impede the progress of the good news of the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that those who do the work of the Temple live on what comes from the Temple, and that those who serve at the altar share the offerings with the altar?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}So, too, the Master has appointed that those who tell the good news should get their living from the good news.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I, however, have not availed myself of any of these rights. I am not saying this to secure such an arrangement for myself; indeed, I would far rather die \uc1\u8211* Nobody will make my boast a vain one!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}If I proclaim the good news, I have nothing to boast of, for I am compelled to do so. Woe is me if I do not share it!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}If I do this work willingly, I have a reward; but, if unwillingly, I have been charged to perform a duty.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}What is my reward, then? To present the good news free of all cost, and so make but a sparing use of the rights which it gives me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Although I was entirely free, yet, to win as many converts as possible, I made myself everyone\uc1\u8217*s slave.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}To the Jews I became like a Jew, to win Jews. To those who are subject to Law I became like a man subject to Law \uc1\u8211* though I was not myself subject to Law \uc1\u8211* to win those who are subject to Law.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}To those who have no Law I became like a man who has no Law \uc1\u8211* not that I am free from God\uc1\u8217*s Law; no, for I am under Christ\uc1\u8217*s Law \uc1\u8211* to win those who have no law.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}To the weak I became weak, to win the weak. I have become all things to all people, so as at all costs to save some.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And I do everything for the sake of the good news, so that with them I may share in its blessings.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that on a racecourse, though all run, yet only one wins the prize? Run in such a way that you may win.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Every athlete exercises self-restraint in everything; they, indeed, for a crown that fades, we for one that is unfading.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}I, therefore, do not run aimlessly. I do not box like a man hitting the air.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}No, I bruise my body and make it my slave, so that I, who have called others to the contest, will not myself be rejected.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 10}I want you to bear in mind, friends, that all our ancestors were beneath the cloud, and all passed through the sea;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}that in the cloud and in the sea they all underwent baptism as followers of Moses;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and that they all ate the same supernatural food,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and all drank the same supernatural water, for they used to drink from a supernatural rock which followed them, and that rock was the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Yet with most of them God was displeased; for they were struck down in the desert.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Now these things happened as warnings to us, to teach us not to long for evil things as our ancestors longed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Do not become idolaters, as some of them became. Scripture says \uc1\u8211*
