{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Nor let us act immorally, as some of them acted, with the result that twenty-three thousand of them fell dead in a single day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Nor let us try the patience of the Lord too far, as some of them tried it, with the result that they were, one after another, destroyed by snakes.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And do not murmur, as some of them murmured, and so were destroyed by the angel of death.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}These things happened to them by way of warning, and were recorded to serve as a caution to us, in whose days the close of the ages has come.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Therefore let the person who thinks that they stand take care that they do not fall.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}No temptation has come upon you that is not common to all humanity. God will not fail you, and he will not allow you to be tempted beyond your strength; but, when he sends the temptation, he will also provide the way of escape, so that you may have strength to endure.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Therefore, my dear friends, shun the worship of idols.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I speak to you as man of discernment; form your own judgment about what I am saying.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}In the cup of blessing which we bless, is not there a sharing in the blood of the Christ? And in the bread which we break, is not there a sharing in the body of the Christ?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}The bread is one, and we, though many, are one body; for we all partake of that one bread.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Look at the people of Israel. Do not those who eat the sacrifices share with the altar?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}What do I mean? That an offering made to an idol, or the idol itself, is anything?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}No; what I say is that the sacrifices offered by the Gentiles are offered to demons and to a being who is no God, and I do not want you to share with demons.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}You cannot drink both the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You cannot partake at the table of the Lord and at the table of demons.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Or are we to rouse the jealousy of the Lord? Are we stronger than he?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Everything is allowable! Yes, but everything is not profitable. Everything is allowable! Yes, but everything does not build up character.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}A person must not study their own interests, but the interests of others.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Eat anything that is sold in the market, without making inquiries to satisfy your scruples;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}for the earth, with all that is in it, belongs to the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}If an unbeliever invites you to his house and you consent to go, eat anything that is put before you, without making inquiries to satisfy your scruples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}But, if anyone should say to you \uc1\u8220*This has been offered in sacrifice to an idol,\uc1\u8221* then, for the sake of the speaker and his scruples, do not eat it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}I do not say your scruples, but his. For why should the freedom that I claim be condemned by the scruples of another?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}If, for my part, I take the food thankfully, why should I be abused for eating that for which I give thanks?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Whether, then, you eat or drink or whatever you do, do everything to the honour of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Do not cause offence either to Jews or Greeks or to the church of God;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}for I, also, try to please everybody in everything, not seeking my own advantage, but do what is best for others, so that they may be saved.{\cf1\f1\fs22 11}Imitate me, as I myself imitate Christ.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I praise you, indeed, because you never forget me, and are keeping my injunctions in mind, exactly as I laid them on you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}But I am anxious that you should understand that the Christ is the head of every man, that man is the head of woman, and that God is the head of the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Any man who keeps his head covered, when praying or preaching in public, dishonours him who is his head;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}while any woman, who prays or preaches in public bare-headed, dishonours him who is her head; for that is to make herself like one of the shameless women who shave their heads.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Indeed, if a woman does not keep her head covered, she may as well cut her hair short. But, since to cut her hair short, or shave it off, marks her as one of the shameless women, she should keep her head covered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}A man ought not to have his head covered, for he has been from the beginning the likeness of God and the reflection of his glory, but woman is the reflection of man\uc1\u8217*s glory.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For it was not man who was taken from woman, but woman who was taken from man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Besides, man was not created for the sake of woman, but woman for the sake of man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And, therefore, a woman ought to wear on her head a symbol of her subjection, because of the presence of the angels.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Still, when in union with the Lord, woman is not independent of man, or man of woman;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}for just as woman came from man, so man comes by means of woman; and all things come from God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Judge for yourselves. Is it fitting that a woman should pray to God in public with her head uncovered?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Does not nature herself teach us that, while for a man to wear his hair long is degrading to him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}a woman\uc1\u8217*s long hair is her glory? Her hair has been given her to serve as a covering.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}If, however, anyone still thinks it right to contest the point \uc1\u8211* well, we have no such custom, nor have the churches of God.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}In giving directions on the next subject, I cannot praise you; because your meetings do more harm than good.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}To begin with, I am told that when you meet together as a church there are divisions among you. In part I believe this,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}indeed, there must be parties among you, so that the people of real worth become known.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}When you meet together, as I understand, it is not possible to eat the Lord\uc1\u8217*s Supper;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}for, as you eat, each of you tries to secure his own supper first, with the result that one has too little to eat, and another has too much to drink!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Have you no houses in which you can eat and drink? Or are you trying to show your contempt for the church of God, and to humiliate the poor? What can I say to you? Should I praise you? In this matter I cannot praise you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}For I myself received from the Lord the account which I have in turn given to you \uc1\u8211* how the Lord Jesus, on the very night of his betrayal, took some bread,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}and, after saying the thanksgiving, broke it and said \uc1\u8216*This is my own body given on your behalf. Do this in memory of me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And in the same way with the cup, after supper, saying \uc1\u8216*This cup is the new covenant made by my blood. Do this, whenever you drink it, in memory of me.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}For whenever you eat this bread and drink the cup, you proclaim the Lord\uc1\u8217*s death \uc1\u8211* until he comes.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Therefore, whoever eats the bread, or drinks the Lord\uc1\u8217*s cup, in an irreverent spirit, will have to answer for an offence against the Lord\uc1\u8217*s body and blood.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Let everyone look into their own heart, and only then eat of the bread and drink from the cup.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}For the person who eats and drinks brings a judgment on themselves by their eating and drinking, when they do not discern the body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}That is why so many among you are weak and ill, and why some are sleeping.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}But, if we judged ourselves rightly, we should not be judged.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Yet, in being judged by the Lord, we are undergoing discipline, so that we may not have judgment passed on us with the rest of the world.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Therefore, my friends, when you meet together to eat the Supper, wait for one another.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}If anyone is hungry, they should eat at home, so that your meetings may not bring a judgment on you. The other details I will settle when I come.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 12}In the next place, friends, I do not want you to be ignorant about spiritual gifts.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}You know that there was a time when you were Gentiles, going astray after idols that could not speak, just as you happened to be led.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Therefore I tell you plainly that no one who speaks under the influence of the Spirit of God says \uc1\u8220*JESUS IS ACCURSED,\uc1\u8221* and that no one can say \uc1\u8220*JESUS IS LORD,\uc1\u8221* except under the influence of the Holy Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Gifts differ, but the Spirit is the same;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}ways of serving differ, yet the Master is the same;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}results differ, yet the God who brings about every result is in every case the same.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}To each of us there is given spiritual illumination for the general good.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}To one is given the power to speak with wisdom through the Spirit; to another the power to speak with knowledge, due to the same Spirit;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}to another faith by the same Spirit; to another power to cure diseases by the one Spirit; to another supernatural powers;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}to another the gift of preaching; to another the gift of distinguishing between true and false inspiration; to another varieties of the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues\uc1\u8221*; to another the power to interpret \uc1\u8220*tongues.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}All these result from one and the same Spirit, who distributes his gifts to each individually as he wills.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}For just as the human body is one whole, and yet has many parts, and all its parts, many though they are, form but one body, so it is with the Christ;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}for it was by one Spirit that we were all baptized to form one body, whether Jews or Greeks, slaves or free, and were all imbued with one Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}The human body, I repeat, consists not of one part, but of many.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}If the foot says \uc1\u8220*Since I am not a hand, I do not belong to the body,\uc1\u8221* it does not because of that cease to belong to the body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Or if the ear says \uc1\u8220*Since I am not an eye, I do not belong to the body,\uc1\u8221* it does not because of that cease to belong to the body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}If all the body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If it were all hearing, where would the sense of smell be?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}But in fact God has placed each individual part just where he thought fit in the body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}If, however, they all made up only one part, where would the body be?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But in fact, although it has many parts, there is only one body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}The eye cannot say to the hand \uc1\u8220*I do not need you,\uc1\u8221* nor, again, the head to the feet \uc1\u8220*I do not need you.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}No! Those parts of the body that seem naturally the weaker are indispensable;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}and those parts which we deem less honourable we surround with special honour; and our ungraceful parts receive a special grace which our graceful parts do not require.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Yes, God has so constructed the body \uc1\u8211* by giving a special honour to the part that lacks it \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}As to secure that there should be no disunion in the body, but that the parts should show the same care for one another.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}If one part suffers, all the others suffer with it, and if one part has honour done to it, all the others share its joy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Together you are the body of Christ, and individually its parts.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}In the church God has appointed, first, apostles, secondly preachers, thirdly teachers; then he has given supernatural powers, then power to cure diseases, aptness for helping others, capacity to govern, varieties of the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Can everyone be an apostle? Can everyone be a preacher? Can everyone be a teacher? Can everyone have supernatural powers?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Can everyone have power to cure diseases? Can everyone speak in \uc1\u8220*tongues\uc1\u8221*? Can everyone interpret them?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Strive for the greater gifts.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
Yet I can still show you a way beyond all comparison the best.{\cf1\f1\fs22 13}Though I speak in the \uc1\u8220*tongues\uc1\u8221* of people, or even of angels, yet have not love, I have become mere echoing brass, or a clanging cymbal!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Even though I have the gift of preaching, and fathom all hidden truths and all the depths of knowledge; even though I have such faith as might move mountains, yet have not love, I am nothing!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Even though I dole my substance to the poor, even though I sacrifice my body in order to boast, yet have not love, it avails me nothing!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Love is long-suffering, and kind; love is never envious, never boastful, never conceited, never behaves unbecomingly;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}love is never self-seeking, never provoked, never reckons up her wrongs;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}love never rejoices at evil, but rejoices in the triumph of truth;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}love bears with all things, ever trustful, ever hopeful, ever patient.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Love never fails. But, whether it be the gift of preaching, it will end; whether it be the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues,\uc1\u8221* it will cease; whether it be knowledge, it, too, will vanish.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For our knowledge is incomplete, and our preaching is incomplete,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}but, when the perfect has come, that which is incomplete will end.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}When I was a child, I talked as a child, I felt as a child, I reasoned as a child; now that I am a man, I have done with childish ways.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}As yet we see, in a mirror, dimly, but then \uc1\u8211* face to face! As yet my knowledge is incomplete, but then I will know in full, as I have been fully known.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Meanwhile faith, hope, and love endure \uc1\u8211* these three, but the greatest of these is love.{\cf1\f1\fs22 14}Seek this love earnestly, and strive for spiritual gifts, above all for the gift of preaching.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The person who, when speaking, uses the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues\uc1\u8221* is speaking, not to people, but to God, for no one understands them; yet in spirit they are speaking of hidden truths.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}But those who preach are speaking to their fellow men and women words that will build up faith, and give them comfort and encouragement.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Those who, when speaking, use the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues\uc1\u8221* builds up their own faith, while those who preach build up the faith of the church.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Now I want you all to speak in \uc1\u8220*tongues,\uc1\u8221* but much more I wish that you should preach. A preacher is worth more than one who speaks in \uc1\u8220*tongues,\uc1\u8221* unless they interprets their words, so that the faith of the church may be built up.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}This being so, friends, what good will I do you, if I come to you and speak in \uc1\u8220*tongues,\uc1\u8221* unless my words convey some revelation, or knowledge, or take the form of preaching or teaching?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Even with inanimate things, such as a flute or a harp, though they produce sounds, yet unless the notes are quite distinct, how can the tune played on the flute or the harp be recognised?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}If the bugle sounds a doubtful call, who will prepare for battle?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}And so with you; unless, in using the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues,\uc1\u8221* you utter intelligible words, how can what you say be understood? You will be speaking to the winds!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}There are, for instance, a certain number of different languages in the world, and not one of them fails to convey meaning.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}If, however, I do not happen to know the language, I will be a foreigner to those who speak it, and they will be foreigners to me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And so with you; since you are striving for spiritual gifts, be eager to excel in such as will build up the faith of the church.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Therefore anyone who, when speaking, uses the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues\uc1\u8221* should pray for ability to interpret them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}If, when praying, I use the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues,\uc1\u8221* my spirit indeed prays, but my mind is a blank.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}What, then, is my conclusion? Simply this \uc1\u8211* I will pray with my spirit, but with my mind as well; I will sing with my spirit, but with my mind as well.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}If you bless God with your spirit only, how can people in the congregation who are without your gift say \uc1\u8220*Amen\uc1\u8221* to your thanksgiving? They do not know what you are saying!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Your thanksgiving may be excellent, but the other is not helped by it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Thank God, I use the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues\uc1\u8221* more than any of you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}But at a meeting of the church I would rather speak five words with my mind, and so teach others, than ten thousand words when using the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}My friends, do not show yourselves children in understanding. In wickedness be infants, but in understanding show yourselves adults.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}It is said in the Law \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*In strange tongues and by the lips of strangers will I speak to this people, but even then they will not listen to me, says the Lord.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Therefore the gift of the \uc1\u8220*tongues\uc1\u8221* is intended as a sign, not for those who believe in Christ, but for those who do not, while the gift of preaching is intended as a sign, not for those who do not believe in Christ, but for those who do.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}So, when the whole church meets, if all present use the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues,\uc1\u8221* and some people who are without the gift, or who are unbelievers, come in, will not they say that you are mad?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}While, if all those present use the gift of preaching, and an unbeliever, or someone without the gift, comes in, they are convinced of their sinfulness by them all, they are called to account by them all;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}the secrets of their heart are revealed, and then, throwing themselves on their face, they will worship God, and declare \uc1\u8220*God is indeed among you!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}What do I suggest, then, friends? Whenever you meet for worship, each of you comes, either with a hymn, or a lesson, or a revelation, or the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues,\uc1\u8221* or the interpretation of them; let everything be directed to the building up of faith.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}If any of you use the gift of \uc1\u8220*tongues,\uc1\u8221* not more than two, or at the most three, should do so \uc1\u8211* each speaking in his turn \uc1\u8211* and someone should interpret them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}If there is no one able to interpret what is said, they should remain silent at the meeting of the church, and speak to themselves and to God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Of preachers two or three should speak, and the rest should weigh well what is said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}But, if some revelation is made to another person as he sits there, the first speaker should stop.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}For you can all preach in turn, so that all may learn some lesson and all receive encouragement.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}(The spirit that moves the preachers is within the preachers\uc1\u8217* control;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}for God is not a God of disorder, but of peace.) This custom prevails in all the churches of Christ\uc1\u8217*s people.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}At the meetings of the church married women should remain silent, for they are not allowed to speak in public; they should take a subordinate place, as the Law itself directs.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}If they want information on any point, they should ask their husbands about it at home; for it is unbecoming for a married woman to speak at a meeting of the church.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}What! Did God\uc1\u8217*s message to the world originate with you? Or did it find its way to none but you?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}If anyone thinks that he has the gift of preaching or any other spiritual gift, he should recognise that what I am now saying to you is a command from the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}Anyone who ignores it may be ignored.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Therefore, my friends, strive for the gift of preaching, and yet do not forbid speaking in \uc1\u8220*tongues.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}Let everything be done in a proper and orderly manner.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Apostle\uc1\u8217*s Teaching as to the Resurrection of the Dead

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 15}Next, friends, I would like to remind you of the good news which I told you, and which you received \uc1\u8211* the good news on which you have taken your stand,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and by means of which you are being saved. I would like to remind you of the words that I used in telling it to you, since you are still holding fast to it, and since it was not in vain that you became believers in Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}For at the very beginning of my teaching I gave you the account which I had myself received \uc1\u8211* that Christ died for our sins (as the scriptures had foretold),{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}that he was buried, that on the third day he was raised (as the scriptures had foretold),{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}and that he appeared to Cephas, and then to the Twelve.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}After that, he appeared to more than five hundred of his followers at one time, most of whom are still alive, though some have gone to their rest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}After that, he appeared to James, and then to all the apostles.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Last of all, he appeared even to me, who am, as it were, a miscarried baby - born untimely.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For I am the least of the apostles, I who am unworthy of the name of \uc1\u8220*apostle,\uc1\u8221* because I persecuted the church of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}But it is through the love of God that I am what I am, and the love that he showed me has not been wasted. No, I have toiled harder than any of them, and yet it was not I, but the love of God working with me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Whether, then, it was I or whether it was they, this we proclaim, and this you believed.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Now, if it is proclaimed of Christ that he has been raised from the dead, how is it that some of you say that there is no such thing as a resurrection of the dead?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But, if there is no such thing as a resurrection of the dead, then even Christ has not been raised;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}and, if Christ has not been raised, then our proclamation is without meaning, and our faith without meaning also!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Yes, and we are being proved to have borne false testimony about God; for we testified of God that he raised the Christ, whom he did not raise, if, indeed, the dead do not rise!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}For, if the dead do not rise, then even Christ himself has not been raised,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and, if Christ has not been raised, your faith is folly \uc1\u8211* your sins are on you still!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Yes, and they, who have passed to their rest in union with Christ, perished!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}If all that we have done has been to place our hope in Christ for this life, then we of all people are the most to be pitied.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But, in truth, Christ has been raised from the dead, the first-fruits of those who are at rest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}For, since through a man there is death, so, too, through a man there is a resurrection of the dead.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}For, as through union with Adam all die, so through union with the Christ will all be made to live.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}But each in their proper order \uc1\u8211* Christ the first-fruits; afterwards, at his coming, those who belong to the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Then will come the end \uc1\u8211* when he surrenders the kingdom to his God and Father, having overthrown all other rule and all other authority and power.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}For he must reign until God \uc1\u8220*has put all his enemies under his feet.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}The last enemy to be overthrown is death;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}for God has placed all things under Christ\uc1\u8217*s feet. (But, when it is said that all things have been placed under Christ, it is plain that God is excepted who placed everything under him.){\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}And, when everything has been placed under him, the Son will place himself under God who placed everything under him, so that God may be all in all!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Again, what good will they be doing who are baptized on behalf of the dead? If it is true that the dead do not rise, why are people baptized on their behalf?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Why, too, do we risk our lives every hour?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Daily I face death \uc1\u8211* I swear it, friends, by the pride in you that I feel through my union with Christ Jesus, our Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}If with only human hopes I had fought in the arena at Ephesus, what should I have gained by it? If the dead do not rise, then let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we will die!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Do not be deceived.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Good character is marred by evil company.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Wake up to a righteous life, and cease to sin. There are some who have no true knowledge of God. I speak in this way to shame you.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Someone, however, may ask \uc1\u8220*How do the dead rise? And in what body will they come?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}You foolish person! The seed you yourself sow does not come to life, unless it dies!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}And when you sow, you sow not the body that will be, but a mere grain \uc1\u8211* perhaps of wheat, or something else.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}God gives it the body that he pleases \uc1\u8211* to each seed its special body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}All forms of life are not the same; there is one for people, another for beasts, another for birds, and another for fish.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}There are heavenly bodies, and earthly bodies; but the beauty of the heavenly bodies is not the beauty of the earthly.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}There is a beauty of the sun, and a beauty of the moon, and a beauty of the stars; for even star differs from star in beauty.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}It is the same with the resurrection of the dead. Sown a mortal body, it rises immortal; sown disfigured, it rises beautiful;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}sown weak, it rises strong; sown a human body, it rises a spiritual body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}As surely as there is a human body, there is also a spiritual body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}That is what is meant by the words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Adam, the first man, became a human being\uc1\u8221*; the last Adam became a life-giving spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}That which comes first is not the spiritual, but the human; afterwards comes the spiritual;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}the first man was from the dust of the earth; the second man from heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}Those who are of the dust are like him who came from the dust; and those who are of heaven are like him who came from heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}And as we have borne the likeness of him who came from the dust, so let us bear the likeness of him who came from heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}This I say, friends \uc1\u8211* Flesh and blood can have no share in the kingdom of God, nor can the perishable share the imperishable.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}Listen, I will tell you God\uc1\u8217*s hidden purpose! We will not all have passed to our rest, but we will all be transformed \uc1\u8211* in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}at the last trumpet-call; for the trumpet will sound, and the dead will rise immortal, and we, also, will be transformed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}For this perishable body of ours must put on an imperishable form, and this dying body a deathless form.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}And, when this dying body has put on its deathless form, then indeed will the words of scripture come true \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}\uc1\u8220*death has been swallowed up in victory! Where, Death, is your victory? Where, death, is your sting?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}It is sin that gives death its sting, and it is the Law that gives sin its power.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 57}But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory, through Jesus Christ, our Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 58}Therefore, my dear friends, stand firm, unshaken, always diligent in the Lord\uc1\u8217*s work, for you know that, in union with him, your toil is not in vain.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 16}With reference to the collection for Christ\uc1\u8217*s people, I want you to follow the instructions that I gave to the churches in Galatia.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}On the first day of every week each of you should put by what he can afford, so that no collections need be made after I have come.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}On my arrival, I will send any persons, whom you may authorise by letter, to carry your gift to Jerusalem;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and, if it appears to be worth while for me to go also, they will go with me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}I will come to you as soon as I have been through Macedonia \uc1\u8211* for I am going through Macedonia \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And I will probably make some stay with you or, perhaps, remain for the winter, so that you may yourselves send me on my way, wherever I may be going.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}I do not propose to pay you a visit in passing now, for I hope to stay with you for some time, if the Lord permits.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I intend, however, staying at Ephesus until the Festival at the close of the Harvest;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}for a great opening for active work has presented itself, and there are many opponents.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}If Timothy comes, take care that he has no cause for feeling anxious while he is with you. He is doing the Master\uc1\u8217*s work no less than I am.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}No one, therefore, should slight him. See him safely on his way to me, for I am expecting him with some of our friends.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}As for our friend Apollos, I have often urged him to go to you with the others. He has, however, been very unwilling to do so as yet; but he will go as soon as he finds a good opportunity.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Be watchful; stand firm in your faith; be brave; be strong.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Let everything you do be done in a loving spirit.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I have another request to make of you, friends. You remember Stephanas and his household, and that they were the first-fruits gathered in from Greece, and set themselves to serve Christ\uc1\u8217*s people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}I want you, on your part, to show deference to such people as these, as well as to every fellow labourer and earnest worker.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}I am glad Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus have come, for they have made up for your absence;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}they have cheered my heart, and your hearts also. Recognise the worth of such people as these.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}The churches in Roman Asia send you their greetings. Aquila and Prisca and the church that meets at their house send you many Christian greetings.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}All of the Lord\uc1\u8217*s followers send you greetings. Greet one another with a sacred kiss.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}I, Paul, add this greeting in my own handwriting.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Accursed be anyone who has no love for the Lord. THE LORD IS COMING.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}May the blessing of the Lord Jesus be with you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}My love to all of you who are in union with Christ Jesus.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 2 Corinthians (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs56 Paul\uc1\u8217*s Second Letter to the

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Corinthians

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Introduction

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}To the church of God in Corinth, and to all Christ\uc1\u8217*s people throughout Greece, from Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus, by the will of God, and from Timothy, who is also a follower.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}May God, our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ bless you and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Blessed is the God and Father of Jesus Christ our Lord, the all-merciful Father, the God ever ready to console,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}who consoles us in all our troubles, so that we may be able to console those who are in any trouble with the consolation that we ourselves receive from him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}It is true that we have our full share of the sufferings of the Christ, but through the Christ we have also our full share of consolation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}If we meet with trouble, it is for the sake of your consolation and salvation; and, if we find consolation, it is for the sake of the consolation that you will experience when you are called to endure the sufferings that we ourselves are enduring;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and our hope for you remains unshaken. We know that, as you are sharing our sufferings, you will also share our consolation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}We want you, friends, to know that, in the troubles which befell us in Roman Asia, we were burdened altogether beyond our strength, so much so that we even despaired of life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Indeed, we had the presentiment that we must die, so that we might rely, not on ourselves, but on God who raises the dead.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And from so imminent a death God delivered us, and will deliver us again; for in him we have placed our hopes of future deliverance, while you, also, help us by your prayers.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And then many lips will give thanks on our behalf for the blessing granted us in answer to many prayers.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Apostle\uc1\u8217*s Relations with his Converts

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Indeed, our main ground for satisfaction is this \uc1\u8211* Our conscience tells us that our conduct in the world, and still more in our relations with you, was marked by a purity of motive and a sincerity that were inspired by God, and was based, not on worldly policy, but on the help of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}We never write anything to you other than what you will acknowledge to the very end \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And, indeed, you have already partly acknowledged it about us \uc1\u8211* that you have a right to be proud of us, as we will be proud of you, on the day of our Lord Jesus.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}With this conviction in my mind, I planned to come to see you first, so that your pleasure might be doubled \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}To visit you both on my way to Macedonia, and to come to you again on my return from Macedonia, and then to get you to send me on my way into Judea.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}As this was my plan, where, pray, did I show any fickleness of purpose? Or do you think that my plans are formed on mere impulse, so that in the same breath I say \uc1\u8220*Yes\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*No\uc1\u8221*?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}As God is true, the message that we brought you does not waver between \uc1\u8220*Yes\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*No\uc1\u8221*!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}The Son of God, Christ Jesus, whom we \uc1\u8211* Silas, Timothy, and I \uc1\u8211* proclaimed among you, never wavered between \uc1\u8220*Yes\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*No.\uc1\u8221* With him it has always been \uc1\u8220*Yes.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}For, many as were the promises of God, in Christ is the \uc1\u8220*Yes\uc1\u8221* that fulfils them. Therefore, through Christ again, let the \uc1\u8220*Amen\uc1\u8221* rise, through us, to the glory of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}God who brings us, with you, into close union with Christ, and who consecrated us,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}also set his seal on us, and gave us his Spirit in our hearts as a pledge of future blessings.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}But, as my life will answer for it, I call God to witness that it was to spare you that I deferred my visit to Corinth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}I do not mean that we are to dictate to you with regard to your faith; on the contrary, we work with you for your true happiness; indeed, it is through your faith that you are standing firm.{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}For my own sake, as well, I decided not to pay you another painful visit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}If it is I who cause you pain, why, who is there to cheer me, except the person whom I am paining?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So I wrote as I did because I was afraid that if I had come, I should have been pained by those who ought to have made me glad; for I felt sure that it was true of you all that my joy was in every case yours also.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}I wrote to you in sore trouble and distress of heart and with many tears, not to give you pain, but to let you see how intense a love I have for you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Now whoever has caused the pain has not so much pained me, as he has, to some extent \uc1\u8211* not to be too severe \uc1\u8211* pained every one of you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}The man to whom I refer has been sufficiently punished by the penalty inflicted by the majority of you;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}so that now you must take the opposite course, and forgive and encourage him, or else he may be overwhelmed by the intensity of his pain.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}So I entreat you to assure him of your love.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}I had this further object, also, in what I wrote \uc1\u8211* to find out whether you might be relied on to be obedient in everything.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Anyone you forgive, I forgive them, too. Indeed, for my part, whatever I have forgiven (if I have had to forgive anything), I have forgiven for your sakes, in the presence of Christ,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}so as to prevent Satan from taking advantage of us; for we are not ignorant of his devices.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}When I went to the district round Troas to tell the good news of the Christ, even though there was an opening for serving the Master,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}I could get no peace of mind because I failed to find Titus, my friend; so I took leave of the people there, and went on to Macedonia.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}All thanks to God, who, through our union with the Christ, leads us in one continual triumph, and uses us to spread the sweet perfume of the knowledge of him in every place.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}For we are the fragrance of Christ ascending to God \uc1\u8211* both among those who are in the path of salvation and among those who are in the path to ruin.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}To the latter we are a stench which arises from death and tells of death; to the former a fragrance which arises from life and tells of life. But who is equal to such a task?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Unlike many people, we are not in the habit of making profit out of God\uc1\u8217*s message; but in all sincerity, and bearing God\uc1\u8217*s commission, we speak before him in union with Christ.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}Are we beginning to commend ourselves again? Or are we like some who need letters of commendation to you, or from you?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}You yourselves are our letter \uc1\u8211* a letter written on our hearts, and one which everybody can read and understand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}All can see that you are a letter from Christ delivered by us, a letter written, not with ink, but with the Spirit of the living God, not on tablets of stone, but on tablets of human hearts.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Ministry of the Apostles

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}This, then, is the confidence in regard to God that we have gained through the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}I do not mean that we are fit to form any judgment by ourselves, as if on our own authority;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}our fitness comes from God, who himself made us fit to be assistants of a new covenant, of which the substance is, not a written Law, but a Spirit. For the written Law means death, but the Spirit gives life.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}If the system of religion which involved death, embodied in a written Law and engraved on stones, began amid such glory, that the Israelites were unable to gaze at the face of Moses because of its glory, though it was but a passing glory,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}will not the religion that confers the Spirit have still greater glory?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For, if there was a glory in the religion that involved condemnation, far greater is the glory of the religion that confers righteousness!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Indeed, that which then had glory has lost its glory, because of the glory which surpasses it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And, if that which was to pass away was attended with glory, far more will that which is to endure be surrounded with glory!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}With such a hope as this, we speak with all plainness;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}unlike Moses, who covered his face with a veil, to prevent the Israelites from gazing at the disappearance of what was passing away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But their minds were slow to learn. Indeed, to this very day, at the public reading of the old covenant, the same veil remains; only for those who are in union with Christ does it pass away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But, even to this day, whenever Moses is read, a veil lies on their hearts.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Yet, whenever someone turns to the Lord, the veil is removed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And the Lord is the Spirit, and, where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is freedom.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And all of us, with faces from which the veil is lifted, seeing, as if reflected in a mirror, the glory of the Lord, are being transformed into his likeness, from glory to glory, as it is given by the Lord, the Spirit.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}Therefore, since it is by God\uc1\u8217*s mercy that we are engaged in this ministry, we do not lose heart.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}No, we have renounced the secrecy prompted by shame, refusing to adopt crafty ways, or to tamper with God\uc1\u8217*s message, and commending ourselves to everyone\uc1\u8217*s conscience, in the sight of God, by our exhibition of the truth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And, even if the good news that we bring is veiled, it is veiled only in the case of those who are on the path to ruin \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}people whose minds have been blinded by the God of this age, unbelievers as they are, so that the light from the good news of the glory of the Christ, who is the incarnation of God, should not shine for them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}(For it is not ourselves that we proclaim, but Christ Jesus, as Lord, and ourselves as your servants for Jesus\uc1\u8217* sake.){\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Indeed, the same God who said \uc1\u8220*Out of darkness light will shine,\uc1\u8221* has shone in on our hearts, so that we should bring out into the light the knowledge of the glory of God, seen in the face of Christ.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}This treasure we have in these earthen vessels, so that its all-prevailing power may be seen to come from God, and not to be our own.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Though hard pressed on every side, we are never hemmed in; though perplexed, never driven to despair;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}though pursued, never abandoned; though struck down, never killed!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}We always bear on our bodies the marks of the death that Jesus died, so that the life also of Jesus may be exhibited in our bodies.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Indeed, we who still live are continually being given over to death for Jesus\uc1\u8217* sake, so that the life also of Jesus may be exhibited in our mortal nature.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And so, while death is at work within us, life is at work within you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But, in the same spirit of faith as that expressed in the words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*I believed, and therefore I spoke,\uc1\u8221* we, also believe, and therefore speak.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For we know that he who raised the Lord Jesus will raise us also with him, and will bring us, with you, into his presence.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}For all this is for your sakes, so that the loving kindness of God, spreading from heart to heart, may cause yet more hearts to overflow with thanksgiving, to his glory.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Therefore, as I said, we do not lose heart. No, even though outwardly we are wasting away, yet inwardly we are being renewed day by day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}The light burden of our momentary trouble is preparing for us a weight of imperishable glory, beyond all measure. {\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}We, all the while, gaze not on what is seen, but on what is unseen. For what is seen is transient, but what is unseen is imperishable.{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}For we know that if our tent \uc1\u8211* that earthly body which is now our home \uc1\u8211* is taken down, we have a house of God\uc1\u8217*s building, a home not made by hands, imperishable, in heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Even while in our present body we sigh, longing to put over it our heavenly house,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}sure that, when we have put it on, we will never be found naked.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For we who are in this tent sigh under our burden, unwilling to take it off, yet wishing to put our heavenly body over it, so that all that is mortal may be absorbed in life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And he who has prepared us for this change is God, who has also given us his Spirit as a pledge.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Therefore we are always confident, knowing that, while our home is in the body, we are absent from our home with the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}For we guide our lives by faith, and not by what we see.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And in this confidence we would gladly leave our home in the body, and make our home with the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Therefore, whether in our home or absent from our home, our one ambition is to please him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For at the court of the Christ we must all appear in our true characters, so that each may reap the results of the life which he has lived in the body, in accordance with his actions \uc1\u8211* whether good or worthless.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Therefore, because we know the fear inspired by the Lord, it is true that we are trying to win people over, but our motives are plain to God; and I hope that in your inmost hearts they are plain to you also.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}We are not \uc1\u8216*commending ourselves\uc1\u8217* again to you, but rather are giving you cause for pride in us, so that you may have an answer ready for those who pride themselves on appearances and not on character.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}For, if we were \uc1\u8216*beside ourselves,\uc1\u8217* it was in God\uc1\u8217*s service! If we are not in our senses, it is in yours!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}It is the love of the Christ which compels us, when we reflect that, as one died for all, therefore all died;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and that he died for all, so that the living should no longer live for themselves, but for him who died and rose for them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}For ourselves, then, from this time forward, we refuse to regard anyone from the world\uc1\u8217*s standpoint. Even if we once thought of Christ from the standpoint of the world, yet now we do so no longer.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Therefore, if anyone is in union with Christ, he is a new being! His old life has passed away; a new life has begun!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}But all this is the work of God, who reconciled us to himself through Christ, and gave us the ministry of reconciliation \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}To proclaim that God, in Christ, was reconciling the world to himself, not reckoning people\uc1\u8217*s offences against them, and that he had entrusted us with the message of this reconciliation.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}It is, then, on Christ\uc1\u8217*s behalf that we are acting as ambassadors, God, as it were, appealing to you through us. We implore you on Christ\uc1\u8217*s behalf \uc1\u8211* Be reconciled to God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}For our sake God made Christ, who was innocent of sin, one with our sinfulness, so that in him we might be made one with the righteousness of God.{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}Therefore, as God\uc1\u8217*s fellow workers, we also appeal to you not to receive his loving kindness in vain.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}For he says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*At the time for acceptance I listened to you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and on the day of deliverance I helped you.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
Now is the time for acceptance! Now is the day of deliverance!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Never do we put an obstacle in anyone\uc1\u8217*s way, so that no fault may be found with our ministry.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}No, we are trying to commend ourselves under all circumstances, as God\uc1\u8217*s assistants should \uc1\u8211* in many an hour of endurance, in troubles, in hardships, in difficulties,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}in floggings, in imprisonments, in riots, in toils, in sleepless nights, in hunger;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}by purity, by knowledge, by patience, by kindliness, by holiness of spirit, by unfeigned love;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}by the message of truth, and by the power of God; by the weapons of righteousness in the right hand and in the left;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}amid honour and disrepute, amid slander and praise; regarded as deceivers, yet proved to be true;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}as unknown, yet well-known; as at death\uc1\u8217*s door, yet, see, we are living; as chastised, yet not killed;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}as saddened, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet enriching many; as having nothing, and yet possessing all things!
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Apostle and his Converts

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}We have been speaking freely to you, dear friends in Corinth; we have opened our heart;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}there is room there for you, yet there is not room, in your love, for us.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Can you not in return \uc1\u8211* I appeal to you as I should to children \uc1\u8211* open your hearts to us?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Do not enter into inconsistent relations with those who reject the faith. For what partnership can there be between righteousness and lawlessness? Or what has light to do with darkness?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}What harmony can there be between Christ and Belial? Or what can those who accept the faith have in common with those who reject it?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}What agreement can there be between a temple of God and idols? And we are a temple of the living God. That is what God meant when he said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will live among them, and walk among them;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I will be their God, and they will be my people.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Therefore \uc1\u8216*Come out from among the nations, and separate yourselves from them,\uc1\u8217* says the Lord,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*And touch nothing impure;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and I will welcome you;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}and I will be a father to you, and you will be my sons and daughters,\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
says the Lord, the Ruler of all.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 7}With these promises, dear friends, let us purify ourselves from everything that pollutes either body or spirit, and, in deepest respect for God, aim at perfect holiness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Make room for us in your hearts. In no instance have we ever wronged, or harmed, or taken advantage of, anyone.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}I am not saying this to condemn you. Indeed, I have already said that you are in our heart, to live and die together.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}I have the utmost confidence in you; I am always boasting about you. I am full of encouragement and, in spite of all our troubles, my heart is overflowing with happiness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Ever since we reached Macedonia, we have had no rest in body or mind; on every side there have been troubles \uc1\u8211* conflicts without, anxieties within.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But God, who encourages the downcast, has encouraged us by the arrival of Titus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And it is not only by his arrival that we are encouraged, but also by the encouragement which he received from you; for he tells us of your strong affection, your penitence, and your zeal on my behalf \uc1\u8211* so that I am happier still.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For, though I caused you sorrow by my letter, I do not regret it. Even if I were inclined to regret it \uc1\u8211* for I see that my letter did cause you sorrow though only for a time \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}I am glad now; not because of the sorrow it caused you, but because your sorrow brought you to repentance. For it was God\uc1\u8217*s will that you should feel sorrow, in order that you should not suffer loss in any way at our hands.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For, when sorrow is in accordance with God\uc1\u8217*s will, it results in a repentance leading to salvation, and which will never be regretted. The sure result of the sorrow that the world knows is death.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}For see what results that other sorrow \uc1\u8211* sorrow in accordance with God\uc1\u8217*s will \uc1\u8211* has had in your case. What earnestness it produced! What explanations! What strong feeling! What alarm! What longing! What eagerness! What readiness to punish! You have proved yourselves altogether free from guilt in that matter.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}So, then, even though I did write to you, it was not for the sake of the wrongdoer, or of the man who was wronged, but to make you conscious, in the sight of God, of your own earnest care for us. And it is this that has encouraged us.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}In addition to the encouragement that this gave us, we were made far happier still by the happiness of Titus for his heart has been cheered by you all.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Although I have been boasting a little to him about you, you did not put me to shame; but, just as every thing we had said to you was true, so our boasting to Titus about you has also proved to be the truth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And his affection for you is all the greater, as he remembers the deference that you all showed him, and recalls how you received him with anxious care.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}I am glad that I can feel perfect confidence in you.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Palestine Famine Fund

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 8}We want to remind you, friends, of the love that God has shown to the churches in Macedonia \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}How, tired though they were by many a trouble, their overflowing happiness, and even their deep poverty, resulted in a flood of generosity.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}I can bear witness that to the full extent of their power, and even beyond their power, spontaneously,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and with many an appeal to us for permission, they showed their love, and contributed their share towards the fund for their fellow Christians.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And that, not only in the way we had expected; but first they gave themselves to the Lord, and to us also, in accordance with God\uc1\u8217*s will.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And this led us to beg Titus, that since he had started the work for you, he should also see to the completion of this expression of your love.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And, remembering how you excel in everything \uc1\u8211* in faith, in teaching, in knowledge, in unfailing earnestness, and in the affection that we have awakened in you \uc1\u8211* I ask you to excel also in this expression of your love.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I am not laying a command on you, but I am making use of the earnestness shown by others to test the genuineness of your affection.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For you do not forget the loving kindness of our Lord Jesus Christ \uc1\u8211* how that for your sakes, although he was rich, he became poor, so that you also might become rich through his poverty.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}I am only making suggestions on this matter; for this is the best course for you, since you were a year before others, not only in taking action, but also in showing your readiness to do so.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And now I want you to complete the work, so that its completion may correspond with your willing readiness \uc1\u8211* in proportion, of course, to your means.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}For, where there is willingness, a person\uc1\u8217*s gift is valued by its comparison with what they have, and not with what they do not have.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}For our object is not to give relief to others and bring distress on you. It is a matter of a fair balance.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}On this occasion what you can spare will supply what they need, at another time what they can spare may supply your need, and so things will be equal.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}As scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Those who had much had nothing over, and those who had little did not lack!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}I thank God for inspiring Titus with the same keen interest in your welfare that I have;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}for Titus has responded to my appeals and, in his great earnestness, is starting to go to you of his own accord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}We are sending with him one of the Lord\uc1\u8217*s followers whose fame in the service of the good news has spread through all the churches;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and not only that, but he has been elected by the churches to accompany us on our journey, in connexion with this expression of your love, which we are personally administering to the honour of the Lord, and to show our deep interest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}What we are specially guarding against is that any fault should be found with us in regard to our administration of this charitable fund;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}for we are trying to make arrangements which will be right, not only in the eyes of the Lord, but also in the eyes of people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}We are also sending with them another of our friends, whose earnestness we have many a time proved in many ways, and whom we now find made even more earnest by his great confidence in you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}If I must say anything about Titus, he is my intimate companion, and he shares my work for you; if it is our friends, they are delegates of the churches, an honour to Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Show them, therefore \uc1\u8211* so that the churches may see it \uc1\u8211* the proof of your affection, and the ground for our boasting to them about you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 9}With reference, indeed, to the fund for your fellow Christians, it is quite superfluous for me to say anything to you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I know, of course, your willingness to help, and I am always boasting of it to the Macedonians. I tell them that you in Greece have been ready for a year past; and it was really your zeal that stimulated most of them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So my reason for sending our friends is to prevent what we said about you from proving, in this particular matter, an empty boast, and to enable you to be as well prepared as I have been saying that you are.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Otherwise, if any Macedonians were to come with me, and find you unprepared, we \uc1\u8211* to say nothing of you \uc1\u8211* should feel ashamed of our present confidence.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Therefore I think it necessary to beg the friends to go to you in advance, and to complete the arrangements for the gift, which you have already promised, so that it may be ready, as a gift, before I come, and not look as if it were being given under pressure.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Remember the saying \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Scanty sowing, scanty harvest; plentiful sowing, plentiful harvest.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Let everyone give as he has determined before hand, not grudgingly or under compulsion; for God loves a cheerful giver.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}God has power to shower all kinds of blessings on you, so that, having, under all circumstances and on all occasions, all that you can need, you may be able to shower all kinds of benefits on others.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}(As scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*He shared freely, he gave to the poor; his righteousness continues for ever.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And he who supplies seed to the sower, and bread for eating, will supply you with seed, and cause it to increase, and will multiply the fruits of your righteousness).{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Rich in all things yourselves, you will be able to show liberality to all, which, with our help, will cause thanksgiving to be offered to God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}For the rendering of a public service such as this, not only relieves the needs of your fellow Christians, but also results in the offering to God of many a thanksgiving.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Through the evidence afforded by the service rendered, you cause people to praise God for your fidelity to your profession of faith in the good news of the Christ, as well as for the liberality of your contributions for them and for all others.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And they also, in their prayers for you, express their longing to see you, because of the surpassing love of God displayed toward you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}All thanks to God for his inestimable gift!
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Apostle\uc1\u8217*s Claims and Authority

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 10}Now, I, Paul, make a personal appeal to you by the meekness and gentleness of the Christ \uc1\u8211* I who, \uc1\u8216*in your presence, am humble in my bearing towards you, but, when absent, am bold in my language to you\uc1\u8217* \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I implore you not to drive me to \uc1\u8216*show my boldness,\uc1\u8217* when I do come, by the confident tone which I expect to have to adopt towards some of you, who are expecting to find us influenced in our conduct by earthly motives.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}For, though we live an earthly life, we do not wage an earthly war.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}The weapons for our warfare are not earthly, but, under God, are powerful enough to pull down strongholds.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}We are engaged in confuting arguments and pulling down every barrier raised against the knowledge of God. We are taking captive every hostile thought, to bring it into submission to the Christ,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and are fully prepared to punish every act of rebellion, when once your submission is complete.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}You look at the outward appearance of things! Let anyone, who is confident that he belongs to Christ, reflect, for himself, again on the fact \uc1\u8211* that we belong to Christ no less than he does.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Even if I boast extravagantly about our authority \uc1\u8211* which the Lord gave us for building up your faith and not for overthrowing it \uc1\u8211* still I have no reason to be ashamed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}I say this so that it doesn\uc1\u8217*t seem as if I am trying to overawe you by my letters.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For people say \uc1\u8216*His letters are impressive and vigorous, but his personal appearance is insignificant and his speaking contemptible.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Let such a person be assured of this \uc1\u8211* that our words in our letters show us to be, when absent, just what our deeds will show us to be, when present.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}We have not indeed the audacity to class or compare ourselves with some of those who indulge in self-commendation! But, when such persons measure themselves by themselves, and compare themselves with themselves, they show a want of wisdom.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}We, however, will not give way to unlimited boasting, but will confine ourselves to the limits of the sphere to which God limited us, when he permitted us to come as far as Corinth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For it is not the case, as it would be if we were not in the habit of coming to you, that we are exceeding our bounds! Why, we were the very first to reach you with the good news of the Christ!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Our boasting, therefore, is not unlimited, nor does it extend to the labours of others; but our hope is that, as your faith grows, our influence among you may be very greatly increased \uc1\u8211* though still confined to our sphere \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}So that we will be able to tell the good news in the districts beyond you, without trespassing on the sphere assigned to others, or boasting of what has been already done.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Let anyone who boasts make their boast of the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For it is not those who commend themselves that stand the test, but those who are commended by the Lord.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 11}I could wish that you would tolerate a little folly in me! But indeed you do tolerate me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I am jealous over you with the jealousy of God. For I promised you in marriage as a pure bride, to one husband - the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Yet I fear that it may turn out that, just as the snake by his craftiness deceived Eve, so your minds may have lost the loyalty and purity due from you to the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For, if some newcomer is proclaiming a Jesus other than him whom we proclaimed, or if you are receiving a Spirit different from the Spirit which you received, or a good news different from that which you welcomed, then you are marvellously tolerant!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}I do not regard myself as in any way inferior to the most eminent apostles!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Though I am no trained orator, yet I am not without knowledge; indeed we made this perfectly clear to you in every way.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Perhaps you say that I did wrong in humbling myself that you might be exalted \uc1\u8211* I mean because I told you God\uc1\u8217*s good news without payment.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I robbed other churches by taking pay from them, so that I might serve you!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}And, when I was with you in need, I did not become a burden to any of you; for our friends, on coming from Macedonia, supplied my needs. I kept myself, and will keep myself from being an expense to you in any way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}As surely as I know anything of the truth of Christ, this boast, as far as I am concerned, will not be stopped in any part of Greece.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Why? Because I do not love you? God knows that I do!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}What I am doing now I will continue to do in order to cut away the ground from under those who are wishing for some ground for attacking me, so that as regards the thing of which they boast they may appear in their true characters, just as we do.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Such people are false apostles, treacherous workers, disguising themselves as apostles of Christ!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And no wonder; for even Satan disguises himself as an angel of light.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}It is not surprising, therefore, if his servants also disguise themselves as servants of righteousness. But their end will be in accordance with their actions.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}I say again \uc1\u8211* Let no one think me a fool! Yet, if you do, at least welcome me as you would a fool, so that I, too may indulge in a little boasting.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}When I speak like this, I am not speaking as the Master would, but as a fool might, in boasting so confidently.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}As so many are boasting of earthly things, I, too, will boast.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}For all your cleverness, you tolerate fools willingly enough!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}You tolerate a person even when they enslave you, when they plunder you, when they get you into their power, when they put on airs of superiority, when they strike you in the face!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}I admit, to my shame, that we have been weak. But whatever the subject on which others are not afraid to boast \uc1\u8211* though it is foolish to say so \uc1\u8211* I am not afraid either!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Are they Hebrews? So am I! Are they Israelites? So am I! Are they descendants of Abraham? So am I!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Are they \uc1\u8220*Servants of Christ\uc1\u8221*? Though it is madness to talk like this, I am more so than they! I have had more of toil, more of imprisonment! I have been flogged times without number. I have been often at death\uc1\u8217*s door.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Five times I received at the hands of my own people forty lashes, all but one.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Three times I was beaten with rods. Once I was stoned. Three times I was shipwrecked. I have spent a whole day and night in the deep.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}My journeys have been many. I have been through dangers from rivers, dangers from robbers, dangers from my own people, dangers from the Gentiles, dangers in towns, dangers in the country, dangers on the sea, dangers among people pretending to be followers of the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}I have been through toil and hardship. I have passed many a sleepless night; I have endured hunger and thirst; I have often been without food; I have known cold and nakedness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}And, not to speak of other things, there is my daily burden of anxiety about all the churches.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Who is weak without my being weak? Who is led astray without my burning with indignation?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}If I must boast, I will boast of things which show my weakness!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}The God and Father of the Lord Jesus \uc1\u8211* he who is for ever blessed \uc1\u8211* knows that I am speaking the truth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}When I was in Damascus, the Governor under King Aretas had the gates of that city guarded, so as to arrest me,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}but I was let down in a basket through a window in the wall, and so escaped his hands.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 12}I must boast! It is unprofitable; but I will pass to visions and revelations given by the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I know a man in union with Christ, who, fourteen years ago \uc1\u8211* whether in the body or out of the body I do not know; God knows \uc1\u8211* was caught up (this man of whom I am speaking) to the third heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And I know that this man \uc1\u8211* whether in the body or separated from the body I do not know; God knows \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Was caught up into Paradise, and heard unspeakable things of which no human being may tell.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}About such a man I will boast, but about myself I will not boast except as regards my weaknesses.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Yet if I choose to boast, I will not be a fool; for I will be speaking no more than the truth. But I refrain, in case anyone should credit me with more than he can see in me or hear from me, and because of the marvellous character of the revelations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}It was for this reason, and to prevent my thinking too highly of myself, that a thorn was sent to pierce my flesh \uc1\u8211* an instrument of Satan to discipline me \uc1\u8211* so that I should not think too highly of myself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}About this I three times entreated the Lord, praying that it might leave me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But his reply has been \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*My help is enough for you; for my strength attains its perfection in the midst of weakness.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
Most gladly, then, will I boast all the more of my weaknesses, so that the strength of the Christ may overshadow me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}That is why I delight in weakness, ill treatment, hardship, persecution, and difficulties, when borne for Christ. For, when I am weak, then it is that I am strong!
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}I have been \uc1\u8216*playing the fool!\uc1\u8217* It is you who drove me to it. For it is you who ought to have been commending me! Although I am nobody, in no respect did I prove inferior to the most eminent apostles.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The marks of the true apostle were exhibited among you in constant endurance, as well as by signs, by marvels, and by miracles.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}In what respect, I ask, were you treated worse than the other churches, unless it was that, for my part, I refused to become a burden to you? Forgive me the wrong I did to you!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Remember, this is the third time that I have made every preparation to come to see you, and I will refuse to be a burden to you; I want, not your money, but you. It is not the duty of children to put by for their parents, but of parents to put by for their children.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}For my part, I will most gladly spend, and be spent, for your welfare. Can it be that the more intensely I love you the less I am to be loved?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}You will admit that I was not a burden to you but you say that I was \uc1\u8216*crafty\uc1\u8217* and caught you \uc1\u8216*by a trick\uc1\u8217*!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Do you assert that I took advantage of you through any of those whom I have sent to you?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}I urged Titus to go, and I sent another follower with him. Did Titus take any advantage of you? Didn\uc1\u8217*t we live in the same Spirit, and tread in the same footsteps?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Have you all this time been fancying that it is to you that we are making our defence? No, it is in the sight of God, and in union with Christ, that we are speaking. And all this, dear friends, is to build up your characters;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}for I am afraid that perhaps, when I come, I may find that you are not what I want you to be, and, on the other hand, that you may find that I am what you do not want me to be. I am afraid that I may find quarrelling, jealousy, ill feeling, rivalry, slandering, backbiting, self-assertion, and disorder.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}I am afraid that, on my next visit, my God may humble me in regard to you, and that I may have to mourn over many who have long been sinning, and have not repented of the impurity, immorality, and sensuality, in which they have indulged.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 13}For the third time I am coming to see you. By the word of two or three witnesses each statement will be established.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I have said it, and I say it again before I come, just as if I were with you on my second visit, though for the moment absent, I say to those who have been long sinning, as well as to all others \uc1\u8211* that if I come again, I will spare no one.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And that will be the proof, which you are looking for, that the Christ speaks through me. There is no weakness in his dealings with you. No, he shows his power among you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For though his crucifixion was due to weakness, his life is due to the power of God. And we, also, are weak in his weakness, but with him we will live for you through the power of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Put yourselves to the test, to see whether you are holding to the faith. Examine yourselves. Surely you recognise this fact about yourselves \uc1\u8211* that Jesus Christ is in you! Unless indeed you cannot stand the test!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But I hope that you will recognise that we can stand the test.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}We pray to God that you may do nothing wrong, not that we may be seen to stand the test, but that you may do what is right, even though we may seem not to stand the test.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}We have no power at all against the truth, but we have power in the service of the truth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}We are glad when we are weak, if you are strong. And what we pray for is that you may become perfect.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}This is my reason for writing as I am now doing, while I am away from you, so that, when I am with you, I may not act harshly in the exercise of the authority which the Lord gave me \uc1\u8211* and gave me for building up and not for pulling down.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And now, friends, goodbye. Aim at perfection; take courage; agree together; live in peace. And then God, the source of all love and peace, will be with you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Greet one another with a sacred kiss.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}All Christ\uc1\u8217*s people here send you their greetings.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}May the blessing of the Lord Jesus Christ, and the love of God, and the communion with the Holy Spirit, be with you all.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Galatians (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs56 Paul\uc1\u8217*s Letter to the

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Galatians

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Introduction

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}To the churches in Galatia, from Paul, an apostle whose commission is not from any human authority and is given, not by human beings, but by Jesus Christ and God the Father who raised him from the dead;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and from all the followers of the Lord here.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}May God, our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ, bless you and give you peace. For Christ, to rescue us from this present wicked age,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}gave himself for our sins, in accordance with the will of our God and Father,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}to whom be ascribed all glory for ever and ever. Amen.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}I am astonished at your so soon deserting him, who called you through the love of Christ, for a different \uc1\u8220*good news,\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}which is really no good news at all. But then, I know that there are people who are harassing you, and who want to pervert the good news of the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Yet even if we \uc1\u8211* or if an angel from heaven were to tell you any other \uc1\u8220*good news\uc1\u8221* than that which we told you, may he be accursed!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}We have said it before, and I repeat it now \uc1\u8211* If anyone tells you a \uc1\u8220*good news\uc1\u8221* other than that which you received, may he be accursed!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Is this, I ask, trying to conciliate people, or God? Am I seeking to please people? If I were still trying to please people, I should not be a servant of Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Independence of the Apostle\uc1\u8217*s Gospel

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}I remind you, friends, that the good news which I told is no mere human invention.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I, at least, did not receive it from any human being, nor was I taught it, but it came to me through a revelation made by Jesus Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}You heard, no doubt, of my conduct when I was devoted to Judaism \uc1\u8211* how I persecuted the church of God to an extent beyond belief, and tried to destroy it,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}and how, in my devotion to Judaism, I surpassed many of my contemporaries among my own people in my intense earnestness in upholding the traditions of my ancestors.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But when God, who had set me apart even before my birth, and who called me by his love,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}saw fit to reveal his Son in me, so that I might tell the good news of him among the Gentiles, then at once, instead of consulting any human being,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}or even going up to Jerusalem to see those who were apostles before me, I went to Arabia, and came back again to Damascus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Three years afterwards I went up to Jerusalem to make the acquaintance of Peter, and I stayed a fortnight with him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}I did not, however, see any other apostle, except James, the Master\uc1\u8217*s brother.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}(As to what I am now writing to you, I call God to witness that I am speaking the truth).{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Afterwards I went to the districts of Syria and Cilicia.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}But I was still unknown even by sight to the Christian churches in Judea;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}all that they had heard was \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*The man who once persecuted us is now telling the good news of the faith of which he once tried to destroy.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And they praised God for my sake.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}Fourteen years afterwards I went up to Jerusalem again with Barnabas, and I took Titus also with me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}It was in obedience to a revelation that I went; and I laid before the apostles the good news that I am proclaiming among the Gentiles. I did this privately before those who are thought highly of because I was afraid that I might possibly be taking, or might have already taken, a course which would prove useless.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Yet even my companion, Titus, though a Greek, was not compelled to be circumcised.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}But, because of those who pretended to be followers who had stolen in, the intruders who had crept in to spy on the liberty which we have through union with Christ Jesus, in order to bring us back to slavery \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Why, we did not for a moment yield submission to them, so that the truth of the good news might be yours always!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Of those who are thought somewhat highly of \uc1\u8211* what they once were makes no difference to me; God does not recognise human distinctions \uc1\u8211* those, I say, who are thought highly of added nothing to my message.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}On the contrary, they saw that I had been entrusted with the good news for the Gentiles, just as Peter had been for the Jews.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For he who gave Peter power for his mission to the Jews gave me, also, power to go to the Gentiles.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Recognising the charge entrusted to me, James, Peter, and John, who were regarded as pillars of the church, openly acknowledged Barnabas and me as fellow workers, agreeing that we should go to the Gentiles, and they to the Jews.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Only we were to remember the poor \uc1\u8211* the thing I was myself anxious to do.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But, when Peter came to Antioch, I opposed him to his face; for he stood self-condemned.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Before certain persons came from James, he had been in the habit of eating with the Gentile converts; but, when they came, he began to withdraw and hold aloof, because he was afraid of offending those who still held to circumcision.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}The rest of the Jewish converts were guilty of the same hypocrisy, so that even Barnabas was led away by it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But, when I saw that they were not dealing straightforwardly with the truth of the good news, I said to Peter, before them all, \uc1\u8216*If you, who were born a Jew, adopt Gentile customs, instead of Jewish, why are you trying to compel the Gentile converts to adopt Jewish customs?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Law and the Gospel

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}We, though we are Jews by birth and not sinners of Gentile origin, know that no one is pronounced righteous as the result of obedience to Law, but only through faith in Christ Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}So we placed our faith in Christ Jesus, in order that we might be pronounced righteous, as the result of faith in Christ, and not of obedience to Law; for such obedience will not result in even one soul\uc1\u8217*s being pronounced righteous.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}If, while seeking to be pronounced righteous through union with Christ, we were ourselves seen to be sinners, would that make Christ an agent of sin? Heaven forbid!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For, if I rebuild the things that I pulled down, I prove myself to have done wrong.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}I, indeed, through Law became dead to Law, in order to live for God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}I have been crucified with Christ. So it is no longer I that live, but it is Christ who lives in me; and, as for my present earthly life, I am living it by faith in the Son of God, who loved me and gave himself for me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}I do not reject the love of God. If righteousness comes through Law, then there was no need for Christ to die!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}Foolish Galatians! Who has been enchanting you \uc1\u8211* you before whose eyes Jesus Christ was depicted on the cross?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Here is the one thing that I want to find out from you \uc1\u8211* Did you receive the Spirit as the result of obedience to Law, or of your having listened with faith?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Can you be so foolish? After beginning with what is spiritual, do you now end with what is external?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Did you go through so much to no purpose? \uc1\u8211* if indeed it really was to no purpose!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}He who supplies you abundantly with his Spirit and endows you with such powers \uc1\u8211* does he do this as the result of obedience to Law? Or as the result of your having listened with faith?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}It is just as it was with Abraham \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
he had faith in God, and his faith was regarded by God as righteousness.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}You see, then, that those whose lives are based on faith are the sons of Abraham.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And scripture, foreseeing that God would pronounce the Gentiles righteous as the result of faith, foretold the good news to Abraham in the words \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Through you all the Gentiles will be blessed.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}And, therefore, those whose lives are based on faith share the blessings bestowed on the faith of Abraham.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}All who rely on obedience to Law are under a curse, for scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Cursed is everyone who does not abide by all that is written in the book of the Law, and do it.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Again, it is evident that no one is pronounced righteous before God through Law, for we read \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Through faith the righteous will find life.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}But the Law is not based on faith; no, its words are \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Those who practice these precepts will find life through them.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Christ ransomed us from the curse pronounced in the Law, by taking the curse on himself for us, for scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Cursed is anyone who is hanged on a tree.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And this he did that the blessing given to Abraham might be extended to the Gentiles through their union with Jesus Christ; that so, through our faith, we also might receive the promised gift of the Spirit.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}To take an illustration, friends, from daily life \uc1\u8211* No one sets aside even an agreement between two people, when once it has been confirmed, nor do they add conditions to it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Now it was to Abraham that the promises were made, \uc1\u8220*and to his offspring.\uc1\u8221* It was not said \uc1\u8220*to his offsprings,\uc1\u8221* as if many persons were meant, but the words were \uc1\u8220*to your offspring,\uc1\u8221* showing that one person was meant \uc1\u8211* and that was Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}My point is this \uc1\u8211* An agreement already confirmed by God cannot be canceled by the Law, which came four hundred and thirty years later, so as to cause the promise to be set aside.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}If our heritage is the result of Law, then it has ceased to be the result of a promise. Yet God conferred it on Abraham by a promise.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}What, then, you ask, was the use of the Law? It was a later addition, to make people conscious of their wrongdoings, and intended to last only until the coming of that offspring to whom the promise had been made; and it was delivered through angels by a mediator.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Now mediation implies more than one person, but God is one only.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Does that set the Law in opposition to God\uc1\u8217*s promises? Heaven forbid! For, if a Law had been given capable of bestowing life, then righteousness would have actually owed its existence to Law.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}But the words of scripture represent the whole world as being in bondage to sin, so that the promised blessing, dependent, as it is, on faith in Jesus Christ, may be given to those who have faith in him.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Before the coming of faith, we were kept under the guard of the Law, in bondage, awaiting the faith that was destined to be revealed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Thus the Law has proved a guide to lead us to Christ, in order that we may be pronounced righteous as the result of faith.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}But now that faith has come we no longer need a guide.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}For you are all sons of God, through your faith in Christ Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}For all of you who were baptized into union with Christ clothed yourselves with Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}All distinctions between Jew and Greek, slave and free, male and female, have vanished; for in union with Christ Jesus you are all one.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}And, since you belong to Christ, it follows that you are Abraham\uc1\u8217*s offspring and, under the promise, sharers in the inheritance.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}My point is this \uc1\u8211* as long as the heir is under age, there is no difference between him and a slave, though he is master of the whole estate.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}He is subject to the control of guardians and stewards, during the period for which his father has power to appoint them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And so is it with us; when we were under age, as it were, we were slaves to the puerile teaching of this world;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}but, when the full time came, God sent his Son \uc1\u8211* born a woman\uc1\u8217*s child, born subject to Law \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}to ransom those who were subject to Law, so that we might take our position as sons.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And it is because you are sons that God sent into our hearts the Spirit of his Son, with the cry \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Abba, our Father.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}You, therefore, are no longer a slave, but a son; and, if a son, then an heir also, by God\uc1\u8217*s appointment.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Yet formerly, in your ignorance of God, you became slaves to \uc1\u8220*gods\uc1\u8221* which were no gods.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But now that you have found God \uc1\u8211* or, rather, have been found by him \uc1\u8211* how is it that you are turning back to that poor and feeble puerile teaching, to which yet once again you are wanting to become slaves?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}You are scrupulous in keeping days and months and seasons and years!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}You make me fear that the labour which I have spent on you may have been wasted.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I entreat you, friends, to become like me, as I became like you. You have never done me any wrong.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}You remember that it was owing to bodily infirmity that on the first occasion I told you the good news.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And as for what must have tried you in my condition, it did not inspire you with scorn or disgust, but you welcomed me as if I had been an angel of God \uc1\u8211* or Christ Jesus himself!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}What has become then, of your blessings? For I can bear witness that, had it been possible, you would have torn out your eyes and given them to me!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Am I to think, then, that I have become your enemy by telling you the truth?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Certain people are seeking your favour, but with no honourable object. No, indeed, they want to isolate you, so that you will have to seek their favour.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}It is always honourable to have your favour sought in an honourable cause, and not only when I am with you, my dear children \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}you for whom I am again enduring a mother\uc1\u8217*s pains, until a likeness to Christ will have been formed in you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But I could wish to be with you now and speak in a different tone, for I am perplexed about you.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Tell me, you who want to be still subject to Law \uc1\u8211* Why don\uc1\u8217*t you listen to the Law?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Scripture says that Abraham had two sons, one the child of the slave-woman and the other the child of the free woman.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}But the child of the slave-woman was born in the course of nature, while the child of the free woman was born in fulfilment of a promise.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}This story may be taken as an allegory. The women stand for two covenants. One covenant, given from Mount Sinai, produces a race of slaves and is represented by Hagar.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Hagar stands for Mount Sinai in Arabia, and represents the Jerusalem of today, for she and her children are in slavery.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}But the Jerusalem above is free, and she it is who is our mother.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}For scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Rejoice, you barren one, who have never given birth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
break into shouts, you who are never in labour,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for many are the children of her who is desolate \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
yes, more than of her who has a husband.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}As for ourselves, friends, we, like Isaac, are children born in fulfilment of a promise.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Yet at that time the child born in the course of nature persecuted the child born by the power of the Spirit; and it is the same now.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}But what does the passage of scripture say?
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Send away the slave-woman and her son; for the slave\uc1\u8217*s son will not be coheir with the son of the free woman.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}And so, friends, we are not children of a slave, but of her who is free.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Gospel in the Daily Life

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}It is for freedom that Christ set us free; stand firm therefore, and do not again be held under the yoke of slavery.
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Understand that I, Paul, myself tell you that if you allow yourselves to be circumcised, Christ will avail you nothing.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}I again declare to everyone who receives circumcision, that he binds himself to obey the whole Law.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}You have severed yourselves from Christ \uc1\u8211* you who are seeking to be pronounced righteous through Law; you have fallen away from love.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}For we, by the help of the Spirit, are eagerly waiting for the fulfilment of our hope \uc1\u8211* that we may be pronounced righteous as the result of faith.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}If we are in union with Christ Jesus, neither is circumcision nor the omission of it anything, but faith, working through love, is everything.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}You were once making good progress! Who has hindered you from obeying the truth?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The persuasion brought to bear on you does not come from him who calls you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}A little yeast leavens all the dough.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}I, through my union with the Lord, am persuaded that you will learn to think with me. But the man who is disturbing your minds will have to bear his punishment, whoever he may be.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}If I, friends, am still proclaiming circumcision, why am I still persecuted? It seems that the cross has ceased to be an obstacle!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I could even wish that the people who are unsettling you would go further still and mutilate themselves.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Remember, friends, to you the call came to give you freedom. Only, do not make your freedom an opportunity for self-indulgence but serve one another in a loving spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Indeed, the whole Law has been summed up in this one precept \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You must love your neighbour as you love yourself.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But, if you are continually wounding and preying on one another, take care that you are not destroyed by one another.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}This is what I have to say \uc1\u8211* Let your steps be guided by the Spirit, and then you will never gratify the cravings of your earthly nature.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}For these cravings of our earthly nature conflict with the Spirit, and the Spirit with our earthly nature \uc1\u8211* they are two contrary principles \uc1\u8211* so that you cannot do what you wish.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}But, if you follow the guidance of the Spirit, you are not subject to Law.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}The sins of our earthly nature are unmistakable. They are sins like these \uc1\u8211* sexual immorality, impurity, indecency,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}idolatry, sorcery, quarrels, strife, jealousy, outbursts of passion, rivalries, dissensions, divisions,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}feelings of envy, drunkenness, revelry, and the like. And I warn you, as I warned you before, that those who indulge in such things will have no place in the kingdom of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}But the fruit produced by the Spirit is love, joy, peace, forbearance, kindliness, generosity, trustfulness, gentleness, self-control.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Against such things there is no law!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And those who belong to Jesus, the Christ, have already crucified their earthly nature, with its passions and its cravings.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Since our life is due to the Spirit, let us rule our conduct also by the Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Do not let us grow vain, and provoke or envy one another.{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}My friends, even if someone should be caught committing a sin, you who are spiritually minded should, in a gentle spirit, help them to recover themselves, taking care that you yourselves are not tempted.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Bear one another\uc1\u8217*s burdens, and so carry out the Law of the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}If a person imagines themselves to be somebody, when they are really nobody, they deceive themselves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Let everyone test their own work, and then their cause for satisfaction will be in themselves and not in a comparison with their neighbour;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}for everyone must bear their own load.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}The person, however, who is being instructed in the message ought always to share their blessings with their teacher.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Do not be deceived. God cannot be mocked. What a person sows that they will reap.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For the person who sows the field of their earthly nature will from that earthly nature reap corruption; while the one who sows the field of the spirit will from that spirit reap eternal life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Let us never tire of doing right, for at the proper season we will reap our harvest, if we do not grow weary.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Therefore, I say, as the opportunity occurs, let us treat everyone with kindness, and especially members of the household of the faith.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Conclusion in the Apostle\uc1\u8217*s own handwriting

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}See in what large letters I am writing with my own hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The people who are trying to compel you to be circumcised are the people who wish to appear to advantage in regard to outward observances. They do it only to avoid being persecuted for the cross of Jesus, the Christ{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Even these men who are circumcised do not themselves keep the Law; yet they want you to be circumcised, so that they may boast of your observance of the rite.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But, for my part, may I never boast of anything except the cross of Jesus Christ, our Master, through whom the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}For neither is circumcision nor the omission of it anything; but a new nature is everything.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}May all who rule their conduct by this principle find peace and mercy \uc1\u8211* they who are the Israel of God.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}For the future let no one trouble me; for I bear the marks of Jesus branded on my body.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}May the blessing of Jesus Christ, our Lord, rest on your souls, friends. Amen.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Ephesians (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs56 Paul\uc1\u8217*s Letter to the

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Ephesians

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Introduction

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}To Christ\uc1\u8217*s people at Ephesus who are faithful to him, from Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus, by the will of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}May God, our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ bless you and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Blessed is the God and Father of Jesus Christ, our Lord, who has blessed us on high with every spiritual blessing, in Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For he chose us in our union with Christ before the creation of the universe, so that we might be holy and blameless in his sight, living in the spirit of love.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}From the first he destined us, in his goodwill towards us, to be adopted as sons through Jesus Christ,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and so to enhance that glorious manifestation of his loving kindness which he gave us in the one he loves;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}for in him, and through the shedding of his blood, we have found redemption in the pardon of our offences.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}All this accords with the loving kindness which God lavished on us, accompanied by countless gifts of wisdom and discernment,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}when he made known to us his hidden purpose. And it also accords with the goodwill which God purposed to exhibit in Christ,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}in view of that divine order which was to mark the completion of the ages, when he should make everything, both in heaven and on earth, centre in him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}In him, I say, for by our union with him we became God\uc1\u8217*s heritage, having from the first been destined for this in the intention of him who, in all that happens, is carrying out his own fixed purpose;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}that we should enhance his glory \uc1\u8211* we who have been the first to rest our hopes on the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And you, too, by your union with him, after you had heard the message of the truth, the good news of your salvation \uc1\u8211* you believed in him and were sealed as his by receiving the holy Spirit, which he had promised.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And the Spirit is a pledge of our future heritage, foreshadowing the full redemption of God\uc1\u8217*s own people \uc1\u8211* to enhance his glory.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The power of God displayed in Christ, the Head of the Church

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And therefore I, ever since I heard of the faith in the Lord Jesus which prevails among you, and of your confidence in all Christ\uc1\u8217*s people,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}have never omitted to thank God on your behalf, whenever I make mention of you in my prayers.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}My prayer is that the God of Jesus Christ our Lord, the all-glorious Father, may inspire you with wisdom and true insight through a fuller knowledge of himself;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}that your minds may be so enlightened that you may realise the hope given by God\uc1\u8217*s call, the wealth of the glory of his heritage among Christ\uc1\u8217*s people,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and the transcendent greatness of the power which he is able to exercise in dealing with us who believe in him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}The same mighty power was exerted on the Christ, when he raised the Christ from the dead and \uc1\u8220*caused him to sit at his right hand\uc1\u8221* on high, exalting him above all angels and archangels of every rank,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}and above every name that can be named, whether in the present age, or in the age to come.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And God placed all things under Christ\uc1\u8217*s feet, and gave him to the church as its supreme head;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}for the church is Christ\uc1\u8217*s body, and is filled by him who fills all things everywhere with his presence.{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}You yourselves were once dead because of your offences and sins.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}For at one time you lived in sin, following the ways of the world, in subjection to the Ruler of the powers of the air \uc1\u8211* the Spirit who is still at work among the disobedient.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And it was among them that we all once lived our lives, indulging the cravings of our earthly nature, and carrying out the desires prompted by that earthly nature and by our own thoughts. Our nature exposed us to the divine wrath, like the rest of humanity.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Yet God, in his abundant compassion, and because of the great love with which he loved us,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}even though we were dead because of our offences, gave life to us in giving life to the Christ. (By God\uc1\u8217*s loving kindness you have been saved.){\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And, through our union with Christ Jesus, God raised us with him, and caused us to sit with him on high,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}in order that, by his goodness to us in Christ Jesus, he might display in the ages to come the boundless wealth of his loving kindness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For it is by God\uc1\u8217*s loving kindness that you have been saved, through your faith. It is not due to yourselves; the gift is God\uc1\u8217*s.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}It is not due to obedience to Law, so that no one can boast.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For we are God\uc1\u8217*s handiwork, created, by our union with Christ Jesus, for the good actions in doing which God had pre-arranged that we should spend our lives.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Remember, therefore, that you were once Gentiles yourselves, as your bodies showed; you were called \uc1\u8220*the Uncircumcised\uc1\u8221* by those who were called \uc1\u8220*the Circumcised\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* circumcised only by human hands!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Remember that you were at that time far from Christ; you were shut out from the citizenship of Israel; you were strangers to the covenants founded on God\uc1\u8217*s promise; you were in the world without hope and without God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But now, through your union with Christ Jesus, you who once were far off have, by the shedding of the blood of the Christ, been brought near.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}He it is who is our peace. He made the two divisions of humanity one, broke down the barrier that separated them,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and in his human nature put an end to the cause of enmity between them \uc1\u8211* the Law with its injunctions and ordinances \uc1\u8211* in order to create, through union with himself, from Jew and Gentile, one new humanity and so make peace.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}And when, on the cross, he had destroyed their mutual enmity, he sought by means of his cross to reconcile them both to God, united in one body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}He came with the good news of peace for you who were far off, and of peace for those who were near;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}for it is through him that we, the Jews and the Gentiles, united in the one Spirit, are now able to approach the Father.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}It follows, then, that you are no longer strangers and foreigners, but are fellow citizens with Christ\uc1\u8217*s people and members of God\uc1\u8217*s household.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}You have been built up on the foundation laid by the apostles and prophets, Christ Jesus himself being the cornerstone.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}United in him, every part of the building, closely joined together, will grow into a temple, consecrated by its union with the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And, through union in him, you also are being built up together, to be a place where God lives through the Spirit.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Apostle\uc1\u8217*s Divine Commission to the Gentiles

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}For this reason I, Paul, the prisoner of Jesus, the Christ, for the sake of you Gentiles \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}For you have heard, I suppose, of the responsible charge with which God entrusted me for your benefit,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and also that it was by direct revelation that the hidden purpose of God was made known to me, as I have already briefly told you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And, by reading what I have written, you will be able to judge how far I understand this hidden purpose of God in Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}In former generations it was not made known to humanity, as fully as it has now been revealed by the Spirit to the apostles and prophets among Christ\uc1\u8217*s people \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}That, by union with Christ Jesus and through the good news, the Gentiles are coheirs with us and members of one body, and that they share with us in God\uc1\u8217*s Promise.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Of this good news I become an assistant, in virtue of the charge with which God entrusted me in the exercise of his power \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Yes, to me, who am less than the least of all Christ\uc1\u8217*s people, was this charge entrusted! \uc1\u8211* to tell the Gentiles the good news of the boundless wealth to be found in the Christ,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}and to make clear what is God\uc1\u8217*s way of working out that hidden purpose which from the first has been concealed in the mind of the Creator of all things;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}so that now to the archangels and to all the powers on high should be made known, through the church, the all-embracing wisdom of God,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}in accordance with that purpose which runs through all the ages and which he has now accomplished in Jesus, the Christ, our Master.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And in union with him, and through our trust in him, we find courage to approach God with confidence.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Therefore I beg you not to be disheartened at the sufferings that I am undergoing for your sakes; for they redound to your honour.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For this reason, then, I kneel before the Father \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}from whom all \uc1\u8220*fatherhood\uc1\u8221* in heaven and on earth derives its name \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}and pray that, in proportion to the wealth of his glory, he will strengthen you with his power by breathing his Spirit into your inmost soul,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}so that the Christ, through your faith, may make his home within your hearts in love; and I pray that you, now firmly rooted and established, may, with all Christ\uc1\u8217*s people,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}have the power to comprehend in all its width and length and height and depth,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and to understand \uc1\u8211* though it surpasses all understanding \uc1\u8211* the love of the Christ; and so be filled with all the fullness of God.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}To him who, through his power which is at work within us, is able to do far more than anything that we can ask or conceive \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}to him be all glory through the church and through Christ Jesus, for all generations, age after age. Amen.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Gospel and Daily Life

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}I beg you, then \uc1\u8211* I who am a prisoner in the Master\uc1\u8217*s cause \uc1\u8211* to live lives worthy of the call that you have received;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}always humble and gentle, patient, bearing lovingly with one another,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and striving to maintain in the bond of peace the unity given by the Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}There is but one body and one Spirit, just as there was but one hope set before you when you received your call.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}There is but one Lord, one faith, one baptism.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}There is but one God and Father of all \uc1\u8211* the God who is over all, pervades all, and is in all.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Everyone of us, however, has been entrusted with some charge, each in accordance with the extent of the gift of the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}That is why it is said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*When he went up on high, he led his captives into captivity. And gave gifts to humanity.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Now surely this \uc1\u8220*going up\uc1\u8221* must imply that he had already gone down into the world beneath.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}He who went down is the same as he who went up \uc1\u8211* up beyond the highest heaven, so that he might fill all things with his presence.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And he it is who gave to the church apostles, prophets, missionaries, pastors, and teachers,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}to fit his people for the work of the ministry, for the building up of the body of the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And this will continue, until we all attain to that unity which is given by faith and by a fuller knowledge of the Son of God; until we reach maturity \uc1\u8211* the full standard of the perfection of the Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Then we will no longer be like infants, tossed backward and forward, blown about by every breath of human teaching and by people\uc1\u8217*s trickery and craftiness;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}but holding the truth in a spirit of love, we will grow into complete union with him who is our head \uc1\u8211* Christ himself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}For from him the whole body, closely joined and knit together by the contact of every part with the source of its life, derives its power to grow, in proportion to the vigour of each individual part; and so is being built up in a spirit of love.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}This, then, as one in union with the Lord, I implore: Do not continue to live such purposeless lives as the Gentiles live,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}with their powers of discernment darkened, cut off from the life of God, owing to the ignorance that prevails among them and to the hardness of their hearts.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Lost to all sense of shame, they have abandoned themselves to licentiousness, in order to practice every kind of impurity without restraint.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But far different is the lesson you learned from the Christ \uc1\u8211* if, that is, you really listened to him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}and through union with him were taught the truth, as it is to be found in Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}For you learned with regard to your former way of living that you must cast off your old nature, which, yielding to deluding passions, grows corrupt;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}that the spirit of your minds must be constantly renewed;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}and that you must clothe yourselves in that new nature which was created to resemble God, with the righteousness and holiness springing from the truth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Since, therefore, you have cast off what is false, you must every one of you speak the truth to your neighbours. For we are united to one another like the parts of a body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Be angry, yet do not sin. Do not let the sun go down on your anger;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}and give no opportunity to the devil.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Let the person who steals steal no longer, but rather they should toil with their hands at honest work, so that they may have something to share with anyone in need.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Never let any foul word pass your lips, but only such good words as the occasion demands, so that they may be a help to those who hear them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}And do not grieve God\uc1\u8217*s Holy Spirit; for it was through that Spirit that God sealed you as his, against the day of redemption.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Let all bitterness, passion, anger, brawling, and abusive language be banished from among you, as well as all malice.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Be kind to one another, tenderhearted, ready to forgive one another, just as God, in Christ, forgave you.{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}Therefore imitate God, as his dear children,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and live a life of love, following the example of the Christ, who loved you and gave himself for you as an offering and a sacrifice to God, that should be fragrant and acceptable.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}As for sexual immorality and every kind of impurity, or greed, do not let them even be mentioned among you, as befits Christ\uc1\u8217*s people,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}nor shameful conduct, nor foolish talk or jesting, for they are wholly out of place among you; but rather thanksgiving.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}For of this you may be sure \uc1\u8211* that no one who is unchaste or impure or greedy of gain (for to be greedy of gain is idolatry) has any place awaiting him in the kingdom of the Christ and God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Do not let anyone deceive you with specious arguments. Those are the sins that bring down the wrath of God on the disobedient.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore have nothing to do with such people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For, although you were once in darkness, now, by your union with the Lord, you are in the light. Live as children of light \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}for the outcome of life in the light may be seen in every form of goodness, righteousness, and sincerity \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}always trying to find out what is pleasing to the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Take no part in deeds of darkness, from which no good can come; on the contrary, expose them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}It is degrading even to speak of the things continually done by them in secret.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}All such actions, when exposed, have their true character made manifest by the light.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For everything that has its true character made manifest is clear as light. And that is why it is said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Sleeper, awake!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Arise from the dead,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the Christ will give you light!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Take great care, then, how you live \uc1\u8211* not unwisely but wisely,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}making the most of every opportunity; for these are evil days.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Therefore do not grow thoughtless, but try to understand what the Lord\uc1\u8217*s will is.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Do not drink wine to excess, for that leads to profligacy; but seek to be filled with the Spirit of God, and speak to one another in psalms and hymns and sacred songs.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Sing and make music in your hearts to the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Always give thanks for everything to our God and Father, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Submit to one another because you honour and respect Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Wives should submit to their husbands as submitting to the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}For a man is the head of his wife, as the Christ is the head of the church \uc1\u8211* being indeed himself the Saviour of his body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}But as the church submits to the Christ, so also should wives submit to their husbands in everything.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Husbands, love your wives, just as the Christ loved the church, and gave himself for her,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}to make her holy, after purifying her by the washing with the water, according to his promise;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}so that he might himself bring the church, in all her beauty, into his own presence, with no spot or wrinkle or blemish of any kind, but that she might be holy and faultless.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}That is how husbands ought to love their wives \uc1\u8211* as if they were their own bodies. A man who loves his wife is really loving himself;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}for no one ever yet hated his own body. But everyone feeds his body and cares for it, just as the Christ for the church;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}for we are members of his body.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}For this cause a man will leave his father and mother, and be united to his wife; and the man and his wife will become one.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}In this there is a profound truth \uc1\u8211* I am speaking of Christ and his church.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}However, for you individually, let each love his wife as if she were himself; and the wife be careful to respect her husband.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}Children, obey your parents, as children of the Lord; for that is but right.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*Honour your father and mother\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* this is the first Commandment with a promise \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8220*so that you may prosper and have a long life on earth.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And fathers, do not irritate your children, but bring them up with Christian discipline and instruction.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Slaves, obey your earthly masters, with anxious care, giving them ungrudging service, as if obeying the Christ;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}not only when their eyes are on you, as if you had merely to please people, but as slaves of Christ, who are trying to carry out the will of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Give your service heartily and cheerfully, as working for the Master and not for people;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}for you know that everyone will be rewarded by the Master for any honest work that he has done, whether he is a slave or free.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}And masters, treat your slaves in the same spirit. Give up threatening them; for you know that he who is both their Master and yours is in heaven, and that before him there is no distinction of rank.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For the future, find strength in your union with the Lord, and in the power which comes from his might.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Put on the full armour of God, so that you may be able to stand your ground against the stratagems of the devil.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}For ours is no struggle against enemies of flesh and blood, but against all the various powers of evil that hold sway in the darkness around us, against the spirits of wickedness on high.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Therefore take up the full armour of God, so that when the evil day comes, you may be able to withstand the attack, and, having fought to the end, still to stand your ground.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Stand your ground, then, with truth for your belt, and with righteousness for your breastplate,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and with the readiness to serve the good news of peace as shoes for your feet.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}At every onslaught take up faith for your shield; for with it you will be able to extinguish all the flaming darts of the evil one.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And receive the helmet of salvation, and the sword of the Spirit \uc1\u8211* which is the message of God \uc1\u8211* always with prayer and supplication.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Pray in spirit at all times. Be intent on this, with unwearying perseverance and supplication for all Christ\uc1\u8217*s people \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and on my behalf also, so that when I begin to speak, words may be given me, so that I may fearlessly make known the inmost truth of the good news,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}on behalf of which I am an ambassador \uc1\u8211* in chains! Pray that, in telling it, I may speak fearlessly as I ought.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}To enable you, as well as others, to know all that concerns me and what I am doing, Tychicus, our dear friend and faithful helper in the Master\uc1\u8217*s cause, will tell you everything.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}I am sending him to you on purpose that you may learn all about us, and that he may cheer your hearts.
