{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 10}The Law, though able to foreshadow the better system which was coming, never had its actual substance. Its priests, with those sacrifices which they offer continuously year after year, can never make those who come to worship perfect.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Otherwise, would not the offering of these sacrifices have been abandoned, as the worshipers, having been once purified, would have had their consciences clear from sins?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}But, on the contrary, these sacrifices recall their sins to mind year after year.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For the blood of bulls and goats is powerless to remove sins.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}That is why, when he was coming into the world, the Christ declared \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Sacrifice and offering you do not desire, but you provide for me a body;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}You take no pleasure in burnt offerings and sacrifices for sin.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}So I said, \uc1\u8216*See, I have come\uc1\u8217* (as is written of me in the pages of the book),
