{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}First come the words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*You do not desire, nor do you take pleasure in, sacrifices, offerings, burnt offerings, and sacrifices for sin\uc1\u8221* (offerings regularly made under the Law),{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}and then there is added \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*See, I have come to do your will.\uc1\u8221* The former sacrifices are set aside to be replaced by the latter.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And it is in the fulfilment of the will of God that we have been purified by the sacrifice, once and for all, of the body of Jesus Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Every other priest stands day after day at his ministrations, and offers the same sacrifices over and over again \uc1\u8211* sacrifices that can never take sins away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}But, this priest, after he had offered one sacrifice for sins, which should serve for all time, \uc1\u8220*took his seat at the right hand of God,\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}and has since then been waiting \uc1\u8220*for his enemies to be put as a stool for his feet.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}By a single offering he has made perfect for all time those who are being purified.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}We have also the testimony of the Holy Spirit. For, after saying \uc1\u8211*
