{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Encouragement and Warning

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Therefore, friends, since we may enter the sanctuary with confidence, in virtue of the blood of Jesus,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}by the way which he inaugurated for us \uc1\u8211* a new and living way, a way through the sanctuary curtain (that is, his human nature);{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}and, since we have in him \uc1\u8220*a great priest set over the house of God,\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}let us draw near to God in all sincerity of heart and in perfect faith, with our hearts purified by the sprinkled blood from all consciousness of wrong, and with our bodies washed with pure water.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Let us maintain the confession of our hope unshaken, for he who has given us his promise will not fail us.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Let us vie with one another in a rivalry of love and noble actions.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And let us not, as some do, cease to meet together; but, on the contrary, let us encourage one another, and all the more, now that you see the day drawing near.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Remember, if we sin wilfully after we have gained a full knowledge of the truth, there can be no further sacrifice for sin;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}there is only a fearful anticipation of judgment, and a burning indignation which will destroy all opponents.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}When someone disregarded the Law of Moses, they were, on the evidence of two or three witnesses, put to death without pity.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}How much worse then, think you, will be the punishment deserved by those who have trampled underfoot the Son of God, who have treated the blood that rendered the covenant valid \uc1\u8211* the blood by which they were purified \uc1\u8211* as if it were not holy, and who have outraged the Spirit of love?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}We know who it was that said \uc1\u8211*
