{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Heroes of Faith

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 11}Faith is the realisation of things hoped for \uc1\u8211* the proof of things not seen.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And it was for faith that the people of old were renowned.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Faith enables us to perceive that the universe was created at the bidding of God \uc1\u8211* so that we know that what we see was not made out of visible things.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Faith made the sacrifice which Abel offered to God a better sacrifice than Cain\uc1\u8217*s, and won him renown as a righteous man, God himself establishing his renown by accepting his gifts; and it is by the example of his faith that Abel, though dead, still speaks.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Faith led to Enoch\uc1\u8217*s removal from earth, so that he might not experience death. \uc1\u8220*He could not be found because God had removed him.\uc1\u8221* For, before his removal, he was renowned as having pleased God;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}but without faith it is impossible to please him, for he who comes to God must believe that God exists, and that he rewards those who seek for him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}It was faith that enabled Noah, after he had received the divine warning about what could not then be foreseen, to build, in reverent obedience, an ark in which to save his family. By his faith he condemned the world, and became possessed of that righteousness which follows on faith.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}It was faith that enabled Abraham to obey the call that he received, and to set out for the place which he was afterwards to obtain as his own; and he set out not knowing where he was going.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}It was faith that made him go to live as an emigrant in the promised land \uc1\u8211* as in a strange country \uc1\u8211* living there in tents with Isaac and Jacob, who shared the promise with him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For he was looking for the city with the sure foundations, whose architect and builder is God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Again, it was faith that enabled Sarah to conceive (though she was past the age for childbearing), because she felt sure that he who had given her the promise would not fail her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And so from one man \uc1\u8211* and that when his powers were dead \uc1\u8211* there sprang a people as numerous \uc1\u8220*as the stars in the heavens or the countless grains of sand on the shore.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}All these died sustained by faith. They did not obtain the promised blessings, but they saw them from a distance and welcomed the sight, and they acknowledged themselves to be only foreigners and strangers on the earth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Those who speak like this show plainly that they are seeking their homeland.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}If they had been thinking of the land that they had left, they could have found opportunities to return.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}But no, they were longing for a better, a heavenly, land! And therefore God was not ashamed to be called their God; indeed he had already prepared them a city.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}It was faith that enabled Abraham, when put to the test, to offer Isaac as a sacrifice \uc1\u8211* he who had received the promises offering up his only son,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}of whom it had been said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*It is through Isaac that there will be descendants to bear your name.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}For he argued that God was even able to raise a man from the dead \uc1\u8211* and indeed, figuratively speaking, Abraham did receive Isaac back from the dead.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}It was faith that enabled Isaac to bless Jacob and Esau, even with regard to the future.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Faith enabled Jacob, when dying, to give his blessing to each of the sons of Joseph, and \uc1\u8220*to bow himself in worship as he leant on the top of his staff.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Faith caused Joseph, when his end was near, to speak of the future migration of the Israelites, and to give instructions with regard to his bones.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Faith caused the parents of Moses to hide the child for three months after his birth, for they saw that he was a beautiful child; and they would not respect the king\uc1\u8217*s order.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}It was faith that caused Moses, when he was grown up, to refuse the title of \uc1\u8220*son of a daughter of Pharaoh.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}He preferred sharing the hardships of God\uc1\u8217*s people to enjoying the short-lived pleasures of sin.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}For he counted \uc1\u8220*the reproaches that are heaped on the Christ\uc1\u8221* of greater value than the treasures of Egypt, looking forward, as he did, to the reward awaiting him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Faith caused him to leave Egypt, though undaunted by the king\uc1\u8217*s anger, for he was strengthened in his endurance by the vision of the invisible God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Faith led him to institute the Passover and the sprinkling of the blood, so that the Destroyer might not touch the eldest children of the Israelites.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Faith enabled the people to cross the Red Sea, as if it had been dry land, while the Egyptians, when they attempted to do so, were drowned.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}Faith caused the walls of Jericho to fall after being encircled for seven days.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Faith saved Rahab, the prostitute, from perishing with the unbelievers, after she had entertained the spies with friendliness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Need I add anything more? Time would fail me if I attempted to relate the stories of Gideon, Barak, Samson, and Jephthah, and those of David, Samuel, and the prophets.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}By their faith they subdued kingdoms, ruled righteously, gained the fulfilment of God\uc1\u8217*s promises, shut the mouths of lions,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}quelled the fury of the flames, escaped the edge of the sword, found strength in the hour of weakness, displayed their prowess in war, and routed hostile armies.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Women received back their dead raised to life. Some were tortured on the wheel, and refused release in order that they might rise to a better life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Others had to face taunts and blows, and even chains and imprisonment.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}They were stoned to death, they were tortured, they were swan asunder, they were put to the sword; they wandered about clothed in the skins of sheep or goats, destitute, persecuted, ill-used \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}people of whom the world was not worthy \uc1\u8211* roaming in lonely places, and on the mountains, and in caves and holes in the ground.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Yet, though they all won renown by their faith, they did not obtain the final fulfilment of God\uc1\u8217*s promise;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}since God had in view some better thing for us, so that they would only reach perfection together with us.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 12}Seeing, therefore, that there is on every side of us such a throng of witnesses, let us also lay aside everything that hinders us, and the sin that clings about us, and run with patient endurance the race that lies before us,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}our eyes fixed on Jesus, the leader and perfect example of our faith, who, for the joy that lay before him, endured the cross, heedless of its shame, and now \uc1\u8220*has taken his seat at the right hand\uc1\u8221* of the throne of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Weigh well the example of him who had to endure such opposition from \uc1\u8220*people who were sinning against themselves,\uc1\u8221* so that you should not grow weary or faint-hearted.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}You have not yet, in your struggle with sin, resisted to the death;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}and you have forgotten the encouraging words which are addressed to you as God\uc1\u8217*s children \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*My child, think not lightly of the Lord\uc1\u8217*s discipline,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
do not despond when he rebukes you;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}For it is him whom he loves that he disciplines,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and he chastises every child whom he acknowledges.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}It is for your discipline that you have to endure all this. God is dealing with you as his children. For where is there a child whom his father does not discipline?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}If you are left without that discipline, in which all children share, it shows that you are bastards, and not true children.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Further, when our earthly fathers disciplined us, we respected them. Should we not, then, much rather yield submission to the Father of souls, and live?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Our fathers disciplined us for only a short time and as seemed best to them; but God disciplines us for our true good, to enable us to share his holiness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}No discipline is pleasant at the time; on the contrary, it is painful. But afterwards its fruit is seen in the peacefulness of a righteous life which is the lot of those who have been trained under it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Therefore \uc1\u8220*lift again the down-dropped hands and straighten the weakened knees;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}make straight paths for your feet,\uc1\u8221* so that the lame limb may not be put out of joint, but rather be cured.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Try earnestly to live at peace with everyone, and to attain to that purity without which no one will see the Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Take care that no one fails to use the loving help of God, \uc1\u8220*that no bitterness is allowed to take root and spring up, and cause trouble,\uc1\u8221* and so poison the whole community.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Take care that no one becomes immoral, or irreligious like Esau, who sold his birthright for a single meal.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}For you know that even afterwards, when he wished to claim his father\uc1\u8217*s blessing, he was rejected \uc1\u8211* for he never found an opportunity to repair his error \uc1\u8211* though he begged for the blessing with tears.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}It is not to tangible \uc1\u8220*flaming fire\uc1\u8221* that you have drawn near, nor to \uc1\u8220*gloom, and darkness, and storm,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and the blast of a trumpet, and an audible voice.\uc1\u8221* Those who heard that voice entreated that they might hear no more,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}for they could not bear to think of the command \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*If even an animal touches the mountain, it is to be stoned to death;\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}and so fearful was the sight that Moses said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*I tremble with fear.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}No, but it is to Mount Zion that you have drawn near, the city of the living God, the heavenly Jerusalem, to countless hosts of angels,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}to the festal gathering and assemblage of God\uc1\u8217*s firstborn whose names are enrolled in heaven, to God the judge of all people, to the spirits of the righteous who have attained perfection,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}to Jesus, the intermediary of a new covenant, and to the sprinkled blood that tells of better things than the blood of Abel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Beware how you refuse to hear him who is speaking. For, if the Israelites did not escape punishment, when they refused to listen to him who taught them on earth the divine will, far worse will it be for us, if we turn away from him who is teaching us from heaven.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Then his voice shook the earth, but now his declaration is \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Still once more I will cause not only the earth to tremble, but also the heavens.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And those words \uc1\u8220*still once more\uc1\u8221* indicate the passing away of all that is shaken \uc1\u8211* that is, of all created things \uc1\u8211* in order that only what is unshaken may remain.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Therefore, let us, who have received a kingdom that cannot be shaken, be thankful, and so offer acceptable worship to God, with awe and the deepest respect.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}For our God is \uc1\u8220*a consuming fire.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 13}Let your love for the Lord\uc1\u8217*s followers continue.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Do not neglect to show hospitality; for, through being hospitable, people have all unawares entertained angels.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Remember the prisoners, as if you were their fellow prisoners, and the oppressed, not forgetting that you also are still in the body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Let marriage be honoured by all and the married life be pure; for God will judge those who are immoral and those who commit adultery.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Do not let your conduct be ruled by the love of money. Be content with what you have, for God himself has said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will never forsake you, nor will I ever abandon you.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Therefore we may say with confidence \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*The Lord is my helper, I will not be afraid.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
What can mere people do to me?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Do not forget your leaders, who told you God\uc1\u8217*s message. Recall the close of their lives, and imitate their faith.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Jesus Christ is the same yesterday and today \uc1\u8211* yes, and for ever!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Do not let yourselves be carried away by the various novel forms of teaching. It is better to rely for spiritual strength on the divine help, than on regulations regarding food; for those whose lives are guided by such regulations have not found them of service.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}We are not without an altar; but it is one at which those who still worship in the tent have no right to eat.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The bodies of those animals whose blood is brought by the high priest into the sanctuary, as an offering for sin, are burnt outside the camp.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And so Jesus, also, to purify the people by his own blood, suffered outside the gate.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Therefore let us go out to him \uc1\u8220*outside the camp,\uc1\u8221* bearing the same reproaches as he;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}for here we have no permanent city, but are looking for the city that is to be.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Through him let us offer, as our sacrifice, continual praise to God \uc1\u8211* an offering from lips that glorify his name.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Never forget to do kindly acts and to share what you have with others, for such sacrifices are acceptable to God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Obey your leaders, and submit to their control, for they are watching over your souls, since they will have to render an account, so that they may do it with joy, and not in sorrow. That would not be to your advantage.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Pray for us, for we are sure that our consciences are clear, since our wish is to be occupied with what is good.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}And I the more earnestly ask for your prayers, so that I may be restored to you the sooner.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}May God, the source of all peace, who brought back from the dead him who, \uc1\u8220*by virtue of the blood that rendered valid the unchangeable covenant, is the great shepherd of God\uc1\u8217*s Sheep,\uc1\u8221* Jesus, our Lord \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}may God make you perfect in everything that is good, so that you may be able to do his will. May he bring out in us all that is pleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ, to whom be all glory for ever and ever. Amen.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}I beg you, friends, to bear with these words of advice. For I have written only very briefly to you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}You will be glad to hear that our friend, Timothy, has been set free. If he comes here soon, we will visit you together.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Give our greeting to all your leaders, and to all Christ\uc1\u8217*s people. Our friends from Italy send their greetings to you.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}May God bless you all.
\par}
