{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}After this I saw that the inmost shrine of the tent of testimony in heaven was opened,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and out of it came the seven angels with the seven curses. They were adorned with precious stones, pure and bright, and had golden girdles round their breasts.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}One of the four creatures gave the seven angels seven golden bowls, filled with the wrath of God who lives for ever and ever.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The Temple was filled with smoke from the glory and majesty of God; and no one could enter the Temple, until the seven curses inflicted by the seven angels were at an end.{\cf1\f1\fs22 16}Then I heard a loud voice, which came from the Temple, saying to the seven angels \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Go and empty the seven bowls of the wrath of God on the earth.\uc1\u8221*
