{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls, and were laden with the seven last curses, came and spoke to me. \uc1\u8220*Come here,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*and I will show you the Bride, the Wife of the Lamb.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}He carried me away in a trance to a great high mountain, and showed me Jerusalem, the Holy City, descending out of heaven from God, filled with the glory of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Its brilliance was like a precious stone, like a jasper, transparent as crystal.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}It had a great high wall, in which were twelve gates; and at these gates there were twelve angels, and there were names inscribed on the gates, the names of the twelve tribes of the Israelites.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}There were three gates on the east, three gates on the north, three gates on the south, and three gates on the west.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}The wall of the city had twelve foundation stones, on which were the twelve names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And the angel who was speaking to me had as a measure a gold rod, with which to measure the city and its gates and its wall.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}The city is square; the length and the breadth are the same. The angel measured with his rod; it was twelve hundred miles; its length, and breadth, and height are equal.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Then he measured the wall; it was two hundred and eighty-eight feet, as people measure, that is as the angel measured.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}The material of the wall of the city was jasper, and the city was built of pure gold, which shone like clear glass.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}The foundations of the wall of the city were ornamented with every kind of precious stone. The first foundation stone was a jasper; the second a sapphire; the third a chalcedony; the fourth an emerald;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}the fifth a sardonyx; the sixth a carnelian; the seventh a chrysolite; the eighth a beryl; the ninth a topaz; the tenth a chrysoprase; the eleventh a hyacinth; and the twelfth an amethyst.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}The twelve gates were made of twelve pearls, each gate of one pearl. The street of the city was of pure gold, transparent as glass.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And I saw no Temple there, for the Lord, our God, the Almighty, and the Lamb are its Temple.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}The city has no need of the sun or the moon to shine on it, for the glory of God illuminated it, and its Lamp was the Lamb.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}The nations walk by the light of it; and the kings of the earth bring their glory into it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Its gates will never be shut by day, and there will be no night there.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}And people will bring the glory and honour of the nations into it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Never will any unhallowed thing enter it, nor they whose life is shameful and false, but only those whose names have been written in the Lamb\uc1\u8217*s book of life.{\cf1\f1\fs22 22}And the angel showed me a river of the water of life, as clear as crystal, issuing from the throne of God and of the Lamb,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}in the middle of the street of the city. On each side of the river was a Tree of life which bore twelve kinds of fruit, yielding its fruit each month; and the leaves of the tree were for the healing of the nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Every thing that is accursed will cease to be. The throne of God and of the Lamb will be within it, and his servants will worship him;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}they will see his face, and his name will be on their foreheads.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Night will cease to be. They have no need of the light of a lamp, nor have they the light of the sun; for the Lord God will be their light, and they will reign for ever and ever.
